64/* Print a warning message and set that we have seen an error. */
65
66#define HSA_SORRY_ATV(location, message, ...) \
67 do \
68 { \
69 hsa_fail_cfun (); \
70 if (warning_at (EXPR_LOCATION (hsa_cfun->m_decl), OPT_Whsa, \
71 HSA_SORRY_MSG)) \
72 inform (location, message, __VA_ARGS__); \
73 } \
74 while (false)
75
76/* Same as previous, but highlight a location. */
77
78#define HSA_SORRY_AT(location, message) \
79 do \
80 { \
81 hsa_fail_cfun (); \
82 if (warning_at (EXPR_LOCATION (hsa_cfun->m_decl), OPT_Whsa, \
83 HSA_SORRY_MSG)) \
84 inform (location, message); \
85 } \
86 while (false)

93 of HSA specification. */

95/* HSA queue packet is shadow structure, originally provided by AMD. */
96
97struct hsa_queue_packet
98{
99 uint16_t header;
100 uint16_t setup;
101 uint16_t workgroup_size_x;
102 uint16_t workgroup_size_y;
103 uint16_t workgroup_size_z;
104 uint16_t reserved0;
105 uint32_t grid_size_x;
106 uint32_t grid_size_y;
107 uint32_t grid_size_z;
108 uint32_t private_segment_size;
109 uint32_t group_segment_size;
110 uint64_t kernel_object;
111 void *kernarg_address;
112 uint64_t reserved2;
113 uint64_t completion_signal;
114};
115
116/* HSA queue is shadow structure, originally provided by AMD. */
117
118struct hsa_queue
119{
120 int type;
121 uint32_t features;
122 void *base_address;
123 uint64_t doorbell_signal;
124 uint32_t size;
125 uint32_t reserved1;
126 uint64_t id;
127};

158unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT
159hsa_symbol::total_byte_size ()
160{
161 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT s
162 = hsa_type_bit_size (~BRIG_TYPE_ARRAY_MASK & m_type);
163 gcc_assert (s % BITS_PER_UNIT == 0);
164 s /= BITS_PER_UNIT;
165
166 if (m_dim)
167 s *= m_dim;
168
169 return s;
170}

172/* Forward declaration. */
173
174static BrigType16_t
175hsa_type_for_tree_type (const_tree type, unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT *dim_p,

178void
179hsa_symbol::fillup_for_decl (tree decl)
180{
181 m_decl = decl;
182 m_type = hsa_type_for_tree_type (TREE_TYPE (decl), &m_dim, false);
183 if (hsa_seen_error ())
184 {
185 m_seen_error = true;
186 return;
187 }
188
189 m_align = MAX (m_align, hsa_natural_alignment (m_type));
190}

192/* Constructor of class representing global HSA function/kernel information and
193 state. FNDECL is function declaration, KERNEL_P is true if the function
194 is going to become a HSA kernel. If the function has body, SSA_NAMES_COUNT
195 should be set to number of SSA names used in the function.
196 MODIFIED_CFG is set to true in case we modified control-flow graph
197 of the function. */
198
199hsa_function_representation::hsa_function_representation
200 (tree fdecl, bool kernel_p, unsigned ssa_names_count, bool modified_cfg)
201 : m_name (NULL),
202 m_reg_count (0), m_input_args (vNULL),
203 m_output_arg (NULL), m_spill_symbols (vNULL), m_global_symbols (vNULL),
204 m_private_variables (vNULL), m_called_functions (vNULL),
205 m_called_internal_fns (vNULL), m_hbb_count (0),
206 m_in_ssa (true), m_kern_p (kernel_p), m_declaration_p (false),
207 m_decl (fdecl), m_internal_fn (NULL), m_shadow_reg (NULL),
208 m_kernel_dispatch_count (0), m_maximum_omp_data_size (0),
209 m_seen_error (false), m_temp_symbol_count (0), m_ssa_map (),
210 m_modified_cfg (modified_cfg)
211{
212 int sym_init_len = (vec_safe_length (cfun->local_decls) / 2) + 1;;
213 m_local_symbols = new hash_table <hsa_noop_symbol_hasher> (sym_init_len);
214 m_ssa_map.safe_grow_cleared (ssa_names_count);
215}

217/* Constructor of class representing HSA function information that
218 is derived for an internal function. */
219hsa_function_representation::hsa_function_representation (hsa_internal_fn *fn)
220 : m_reg_count (0), m_input_args (vNULL),
221 m_output_arg (NULL), m_local_symbols (NULL),
222 m_spill_symbols (vNULL), m_global_symbols (vNULL),
223 m_private_variables (vNULL), m_called_functions (vNULL),
224 m_called_internal_fns (vNULL), m_hbb_count (0),
225 m_in_ssa (true), m_kern_p (false), m_declaration_p (true), m_decl (NULL),
226 m_internal_fn (fn), m_shadow_reg (NULL), m_kernel_dispatch_count (0),
227 m_maximum_omp_data_size (0), m_seen_error (false), m_temp_symbol_count (0),
228 m_ssa_map () {}
229
230/* Destructor of class holding function/kernel-wide information and state. */
231
232hsa_function_representation::~hsa_function_representation ()
233{
234 /* Kernel names are deallocated at the end of BRIG output when deallocating
235 hsa_decl_kernel_mapping. */
236 if (!m_kern_p || m_seen_error)
237 free (m_name);
238
239 for (unsigned i = 0; i < m_input_args.length (); i++)
240 delete m_input_args[i];
241 m_input_args.release ();
242
243 delete m_output_arg;
244 delete m_local_symbols;
245
246 for (unsigned i = 0; i < m_spill_symbols.length (); i++)
247 delete m_spill_symbols[i];
248 m_spill_symbols.release ();
249
250 hsa_symbol *sym;
251 for (unsigned i = 0; i < m_global_symbols.iterate (i, &sym); i++)
252 if (sym->m_linkage != BRIG_ALLOCATION_PROGRAM)
253 delete sym;
254 m_global_symbols.release ();
255
256 for (unsigned i = 0; i < m_private_variables.length (); i++)
257 delete m_private_variables[i];
258 m_private_variables.release ();
259 m_called_functions.release ();
260 m_ssa_map.release ();
261
262 for (unsigned i = 0; i < m_called_internal_fns.length (); i++)
263 delete m_called_internal_fns[i];
264}
265
266hsa_op_reg *
267hsa_function_representation::get_shadow_reg ()
268{
269 /* If we compile a function with kernel dispatch and does not set
270 an optimization level, the function won't be inlined and
271 we return NULL. */
272 if (!m_kern_p)
273 return NULL;
274
275 if (m_shadow_reg)
276 return m_shadow_reg;
277
278 /* Append the shadow argument. */
279 hsa_symbol *shadow = new hsa_symbol (BRIG_TYPE_U64, BRIG_SEGMENT_KERNARG,
280 BRIG_LINKAGE_FUNCTION);
281 m_input_args.safe_push (shadow);
282 shadow->m_name = "hsa_runtime_shadow";
283
284 hsa_op_reg *r = new hsa_op_reg (BRIG_TYPE_U64);
285 hsa_op_address *addr = new hsa_op_address (shadow);
286
287 hsa_insn_mem *mem = new hsa_insn_mem (BRIG_OPCODE_LD, BRIG_TYPE_U64, r, addr);
288 hsa_bb_for_bb (ENTRY_BLOCK_PTR_FOR_FN (cfun))->append_insn (mem);
289 m_shadow_reg = r;
290
291 return r;
292}
293
294bool hsa_function_representation::has_shadow_reg_p ()
295{
296 return m_shadow_reg != NULL;
297}

316hsa_symbol *
317hsa_function_representation::create_hsa_temporary (BrigType16_t type)
318{
319 hsa_symbol *s = new hsa_symbol (type, BRIG_SEGMENT_PRIVATE,
320 BRIG_LINKAGE_FUNCTION);
321 s->m_name_number = m_temp_symbol_count++;
322
323 hsa_cfun->m_private_variables.safe_push (s);
324 return s;

327BrigLinkage8_t
328hsa_function_representation::get_linkage ()
329{
330 if (m_internal_fn)
331 return BRIG_LINKAGE_PROGRAM;
332
333 return m_kern_p || TREE_PUBLIC (m_decl) ?
334 BRIG_LINKAGE_PROGRAM : BRIG_LINKAGE_MODULE;
335}

458/* Allocate HSA structures that we need only while generating with this. */
459
460static void
461hsa_init_data_for_cfun ()
462{
463 hsa_init_compilation_unit_data ();
464 gcc_obstack_init (&hsa_obstack);
465}
466
467/* Deinitialize HSA subsystem and free all allocated memory. */
468
469static void
470hsa_deinit_data_for_cfun (void)
471{
472 basic_block bb;
473
474 FOR_ALL_BB_FN (bb, cfun)
475 if (bb->aux)
476 {
477 hsa_bb *hbb = hsa_bb_for_bb (bb);
478 hbb->~hsa_bb ();
479 bb->aux = NULL;
480 }
481
482 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < hsa_operands.length (); i++)
483 hsa_destroy_operand (hsa_operands[i]);
484
485 hsa_operands.release ();
486
487 for (unsigned i = 0; i < hsa_instructions.length (); i++)
488 hsa_destroy_insn (hsa_instructions[i]);
489
490 hsa_instructions.release ();
491
492 if (omp_simple_builtins != NULL)
493 {
494 delete omp_simple_builtins;
495 omp_simple_builtins = NULL;
496 }
497
498 obstack_free (&hsa_obstack, NULL);
499 delete hsa_cfun;
500}

502/* Return the type which holds addresses in the given SEGMENT. */
503
504static BrigType16_t
505hsa_get_segment_addr_type (BrigSegment8_t segment)
506{
507 switch (segment)
508 {
509 case BRIG_SEGMENT_NONE:
510 gcc_unreachable ();
511
512 case BRIG_SEGMENT_FLAT:
513 case BRIG_SEGMENT_GLOBAL:
514 case BRIG_SEGMENT_READONLY:
515 case BRIG_SEGMENT_KERNARG:
516 return hsa_machine_large_p () ? BRIG_TYPE_U64 : BRIG_TYPE_U32;
517
518 case BRIG_SEGMENT_GROUP:
519 case BRIG_SEGMENT_PRIVATE:
520 case BRIG_SEGMENT_SPILL:
521 case BRIG_SEGMENT_ARG:
522 return BRIG_TYPE_U32;
523 }
524 gcc_unreachable ();
525}
526
527/* Return integer brig type according to provided SIZE in bytes. If SIGN
528 is set to true, return signed integer type. */
529
530static BrigType16_t
531get_integer_type_by_bytes (unsigned size, bool sign)
532{
533 if (sign)
534 switch (size)
535 {
536 case 1:
537 return BRIG_TYPE_S8;
538 case 2:
539 return BRIG_TYPE_S16;
540 case 4:
541 return BRIG_TYPE_S32;
542 case 8:
543 return BRIG_TYPE_S64;
544 default:
545 break;
546 }
547 else
548 switch (size)
549 {
550 case 1:
551 return BRIG_TYPE_U8;
552 case 2:
553 return BRIG_TYPE_U16;
554 case 4:
555 return BRIG_TYPE_U32;
556 case 8:
557 return BRIG_TYPE_U64;
558 default:
559 break;
560 }
561
562 return 0;
563}
564
565/* Return HSA type for tree TYPE, which has to fit into BrigType16_t. Pointers
566 are assumed to use flat addressing. If min32int is true, always expand
567 integer types to one that has at least 32 bits. */
568
569static BrigType16_t
570hsa_type_for_scalar_tree_type (const_tree type, bool min32int)
571{
572 HOST_WIDE_INT bsize;
573 const_tree base;
574 BrigType16_t res = BRIG_TYPE_NONE;
575
576 gcc_checking_assert (TYPE_P (type));
577 gcc_checking_assert (!AGGREGATE_TYPE_P (type));
578 if (POINTER_TYPE_P (type))
579 return hsa_get_segment_addr_type (BRIG_SEGMENT_FLAT);
580
581 if (TREE_CODE (type) == VECTOR_TYPE || TREE_CODE (type) == COMPLEX_TYPE)
582 base = TREE_TYPE (type);
583 else
584 base = type;
585
586 if (!tree_fits_uhwi_p (TYPE_SIZE (base)))
587 {
588 HSA_SORRY_ATV (EXPR_LOCATION (type),
589 "support for HSA does not implement huge or "
590 "variable-sized type %T", type);
591 return res;
592 }
593
594 bsize = tree_to_uhwi (TYPE_SIZE (base));
595 unsigned byte_size = bsize / BITS_PER_UNIT;
596 if (INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (base))
597 res = get_integer_type_by_bytes (byte_size, !TYPE_UNSIGNED (base));
598 else if (SCALAR_FLOAT_TYPE_P (base))
599 {
600 switch (bsize)
601 {
602 case 16:
603 res = BRIG_TYPE_F16;
604 break;
605 case 32:
606 res = BRIG_TYPE_F32;
607 break;
608 case 64:
609 res = BRIG_TYPE_F64;
610 break;
611 default:
612 break;
613 }
614 }
615
616 if (res == BRIG_TYPE_NONE)
617 {
618 HSA_SORRY_ATV (EXPR_LOCATION (type),
619 "support for HSA does not implement type %T", type);
620 return res;
621 }
622
623 if (TREE_CODE (type) == VECTOR_TYPE)
624 {
625 HOST_WIDE_INT tsize = tree_to_uhwi (TYPE_SIZE (type));
626
627 if (bsize == tsize)
628 {
629 HSA_SORRY_ATV (EXPR_LOCATION (type),
630 "support for HSA does not implement a vector type "
631 "where a type and unit size are equal: %T", type);
632 return res;
633 }
634
635 switch (tsize)
636 {
637 case 32:
638 res |= BRIG_TYPE_PACK_32;
639 break;
640 case 64:
641 res |= BRIG_TYPE_PACK_64;
642 break;
643 case 128:
644 res |= BRIG_TYPE_PACK_128;
645 break;
646 default:
647 HSA_SORRY_ATV (EXPR_LOCATION (type),
648 "support for HSA does not implement type %T", type);
649 }
650 }
651
652 if (min32int)
653 {
654 /* Registers/immediate operands can only be 32bit or more except for
655 f16. */
656 if (res == BRIG_TYPE_U8 || res == BRIG_TYPE_U16)
657 res = BRIG_TYPE_U32;
658 else if (res == BRIG_TYPE_S8 || res == BRIG_TYPE_S16)
659 res = BRIG_TYPE_S32;
660 }
661
662 if (TREE_CODE (type) == COMPLEX_TYPE)
663 {
664 unsigned bsize = 2 * hsa_type_bit_size (res);
665 res = hsa_bittype_for_bitsize (bsize);
666 }
667
668 return res;
669}
670
671/* Returns the BRIG type we need to load/store entities of TYPE. */
672
673static BrigType16_t
674mem_type_for_type (BrigType16_t type)
675{
676 /* HSA has non-intuitive constraints on load/store types. If it's
677 a bit-type it _must_ be B128, if it's not a bit-type it must be
678 64bit max. So for loading entities of 128 bits (e.g. vectors)
679 we have to to B128, while for loading the rest we have to use the
680 input type (??? or maybe also flattened to a equally sized non-vector
681 unsigned type?). */
682 if ((type & BRIG_TYPE_PACK_MASK) == BRIG_TYPE_PACK_128)
683 return BRIG_TYPE_B128;
684 else if (hsa_btype_p (type) || hsa_type_packed_p (type))
685 {
686 unsigned bitsize = hsa_type_bit_size (type);
687 if (bitsize < 128)
688 return hsa_uint_for_bitsize (bitsize);
689 else
690 return hsa_bittype_for_bitsize (bitsize);
691 }
692 return type;
693}
694
695/* Return HSA type for tree TYPE. If it cannot fit into BrigType16_t, some
696 kind of array will be generated, setting DIM appropriately. Otherwise, it
697 will be set to zero. */
698
699static BrigType16_t
700hsa_type_for_tree_type (const_tree type, unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT *dim_p = NULL,
701 bool min32int = false)
702{
703 gcc_checking_assert (TYPE_P (type));
704 if (!tree_fits_uhwi_p (TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (type)))
705 {
706 HSA_SORRY_ATV (EXPR_LOCATION (type), "support for HSA does not "
707 "implement huge or variable-sized type %T", type);
708 return BRIG_TYPE_NONE;
709 }
710
711 if (RECORD_OR_UNION_TYPE_P (type))
712 {
713 if (dim_p)
714 *dim_p = tree_to_uhwi (TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (type));
715 return BRIG_TYPE_U8 | BRIG_TYPE_ARRAY;
716 }
717
718 if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE)
719 {
720 /* We try to be nice and use the real base-type when this is an array of
721 scalars and only resort to an array of bytes if the type is more
722 complex. */
723
724 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT dim = 1;
725
726 while (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE)
727 {
728 tree domain = TYPE_DOMAIN (type);
729 if (!TYPE_MIN_VALUE (domain)
730 || !TYPE_MAX_VALUE (domain)
731 || !tree_fits_shwi_p (TYPE_MIN_VALUE (domain))
732 || !tree_fits_shwi_p (TYPE_MAX_VALUE (domain)))
733 {
734 HSA_SORRY_ATV (EXPR_LOCATION (type),
735 "support for HSA does not implement array %T with "
736 "unknown bounds", type);
737 return BRIG_TYPE_NONE;
738 }
739 HOST_WIDE_INT min = tree_to_shwi (TYPE_MIN_VALUE (domain));
740 HOST_WIDE_INT max = tree_to_shwi (TYPE_MAX_VALUE (domain));
741 dim = dim * (unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT) (max - min + 1);
742 type = TREE_TYPE (type);
743 }
744
745 BrigType16_t res;
746 if (RECORD_OR_UNION_TYPE_P (type))
747 {
748 dim = dim * tree_to_uhwi (TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (type));
749 res = BRIG_TYPE_U8;
750 }
751 else
752 res = hsa_type_for_scalar_tree_type (type, false);
753
754 if (dim_p)
755 *dim_p = dim;
756 return res | BRIG_TYPE_ARRAY;
757 }
758
759 /* Scalar case: */
760 if (dim_p)
761 *dim_p = 0;
762
763 return hsa_type_for_scalar_tree_type (type, min32int);
764}
765
766/* Returns true if converting from STYPE into DTYPE needs the _CVT
767 opcode. If false a normal _MOV is enough. */
768
769static bool
770hsa_needs_cvt (BrigType16_t dtype, BrigType16_t stype)
771{
772 if (hsa_btype_p (dtype))
773 return false;
774
775 /* float <-> int conversions are real converts. */
776 if (hsa_type_float_p (dtype) != hsa_type_float_p (stype))
777 return true;
778 /* When both types have different size, then we need CVT as well. */
779 if (hsa_type_bit_size (dtype) != hsa_type_bit_size (stype))
780 return true;
781 return false;
782}
783
784/* Return declaration name if it exists or create one from UID if it does not.
785 If DECL is a local variable, make UID part of its name. */
786
787const char *
788hsa_get_declaration_name (tree decl)
789{
790 if (!DECL_NAME (decl))
791 {
792 char buf[64];
793 snprintf (buf, 64, "__hsa_anon_%u", DECL_UID (decl));
794 size_t len = strlen (buf);
795 char *copy = (char *) obstack_alloc (&hsa_obstack, len + 1);
796 memcpy (copy, buf, len + 1);
797 return copy;
798 }
799
800 tree name_tree;
801 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL
802 || (TREE_CODE (decl) == VAR_DECL && is_global_var (decl)))
803 name_tree = DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME (decl);
804 else
805 name_tree = DECL_NAME (decl);
806
807 const char *name = IDENTIFIER_POINTER (name_tree);
808 /* User-defined assembly names have prepended asterisk symbol. */
809 if (name[0] == '*')
810 name++;
811
812 if ((TREE_CODE (decl) == VAR_DECL)
813 && decl_function_context (decl))
814 {
815 size_t len = strlen (name);
816 char *buf = (char *) alloca (len + 32);
817 snprintf (buf, len + 32, "%s_%u", name, DECL_UID (decl));
818 len = strlen (buf);
819 char *copy = (char *) obstack_alloc (&hsa_obstack, len + 1);
820 memcpy (copy, buf, len + 1);
821 return copy;
822 }
823 else
824 return name;
825}
826
827/* Lookup or create the associated hsa_symbol structure with a given VAR_DECL
828 or lookup the hsa_structure corresponding to a PARM_DECL. */
829
830static hsa_symbol *
831get_symbol_for_decl (tree decl)
832{
833 hsa_symbol **slot;
834 hsa_symbol dummy (BRIG_TYPE_NONE, BRIG_SEGMENT_NONE, BRIG_LINKAGE_NONE);
835
836 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (decl) == PARM_DECL
837 || TREE_CODE (decl) == RESULT_DECL
838 || TREE_CODE (decl) == VAR_DECL
839 || TREE_CODE (decl) == CONST_DECL);
840
841 dummy.m_decl = decl;
842
843 bool is_in_global_vars = ((TREE_CODE (decl) == VAR_DECL)
844 && !decl_function_context (decl));
845
846 if (is_in_global_vars)
847 slot = hsa_global_variable_symbols->find_slot (&dummy, INSERT);
848 else
849 slot = hsa_cfun->m_local_symbols->find_slot (&dummy, INSERT);
850
851 gcc_checking_assert (slot);
852 if (*slot)
853 {
854 hsa_symbol *sym = (*slot);
855
856 /* If the symbol is problematic, mark current function also as
857 problematic. */
858 if (sym->m_seen_error)
859 hsa_fail_cfun ();
860
861 /* PR hsa/70234: If a global variable was marked to be emitted,
862 but HSAIL generation of a function using the variable fails,
863 we should retry to emit the variable in context of a different
864 function.
865
866 Iterate elements whether a symbol is already in m_global_symbols
867 of not. */
868 if (is_in_global_vars && !sym->m_emitted_to_brig)
869 {
870 for (unsigned i = 0; i < hsa_cfun->m_global_symbols.length (); i++)
871 if (hsa_cfun->m_global_symbols[i] == sym)
872 return *slot;
873 hsa_cfun->m_global_symbols.safe_push (sym);
874 }
875
876 return *slot;
877 }
878 else
879 {
880 hsa_symbol *sym;
881 /* PARM_DECLs and RESULT_DECL should be already in m_local_symbols. */
882 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (decl) == VAR_DECL
883 || TREE_CODE (decl) == CONST_DECL);
884 BrigAlignment8_t align = hsa_object_alignment (decl);
885
886 if (is_in_global_vars)
887 {
888 gcc_checking_assert (TREE_CODE (decl) != CONST_DECL);
889 sym = new hsa_symbol (BRIG_TYPE_NONE, BRIG_SEGMENT_GLOBAL,
890 BRIG_LINKAGE_PROGRAM, true,
891 BRIG_ALLOCATION_PROGRAM, align);
892 hsa_cfun->m_global_symbols.safe_push (sym);
893 sym->fillup_for_decl (decl);
894 if (sym->m_align > align)
895 {
896 sym->m_seen_error = true;
897 HSA_SORRY_ATV (EXPR_LOCATION (decl),
898 "HSA specification requires that %E is at least "
899 "naturally aligned", decl);
900 }
901 }
902 else
903 {
904 /* As generation of efficient memory copy instructions relies
905 on alignment greater or equal to 8 bytes,
906 we need to increase alignment of all aggregate types.. */
907 if (AGGREGATE_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (decl)))
908 align = MAX ((BrigAlignment8_t) BRIG_ALIGNMENT_8, align);
909
910 BrigAllocation allocation = BRIG_ALLOCATION_AUTOMATIC;
911 BrigSegment8_t segment;
912 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == CONST_DECL)
913 {
914 segment = BRIG_SEGMENT_READONLY;
915 allocation = BRIG_ALLOCATION_AGENT;
916 }
917 else if (lookup_attribute ("hsa_group_segment",
918 DECL_ATTRIBUTES (decl)))
919 segment = BRIG_SEGMENT_GROUP;
920 else if (TREE_STATIC (decl))
921 {
922 segment = BRIG_SEGMENT_GLOBAL;
923 allocation = BRIG_ALLOCATION_PROGRAM;
924 }
925 else if (lookup_attribute ("hsa_global_segment",
926 DECL_ATTRIBUTES (decl)))
927 segment = BRIG_SEGMENT_GLOBAL;
928 else
929 segment = BRIG_SEGMENT_PRIVATE;
930
931 sym = new hsa_symbol (BRIG_TYPE_NONE, segment, BRIG_LINKAGE_FUNCTION,
932 false, allocation, align);
933 sym->fillup_for_decl (decl);
934 hsa_cfun->m_private_variables.safe_push (sym);
935 }
936
937 sym->m_name = hsa_get_declaration_name (decl);
938 *slot = sym;
939 return sym;
940 }
941}
942
943/* For a given HSA function declaration, return a host
944 function declaration. */
945
946tree
947hsa_get_host_function (tree decl)
948{
949 hsa_function_summary *s
950 = hsa_summaries->get (cgraph_node::get_create (decl));
951 gcc_assert (s->m_kind != HSA_NONE);
952 gcc_assert (s->m_gpu_implementation_p);
953
954 return s->m_bound_function ? s->m_bound_function->decl : NULL;
955}
956
957/* Return true if function DECL has a host equivalent function. */
958
959static char *
960get_brig_function_name (tree decl)
961{
962 tree d = decl;
963
964 hsa_function_summary *s = hsa_summaries->get (cgraph_node::get_create (d));
965 if (s->m_kind != HSA_NONE
966 && s->m_gpu_implementation_p
967 && s->m_bound_function)
968 d = s->m_bound_function->decl;
969
970 /* IPA split can create a function that has no host equivalent. */
971 if (d == NULL)
972 d = decl;
973
974 char *name = xstrdup (hsa_get_declaration_name (d));
975 hsa_sanitize_name (name);
976
977 return name;
978}

1010 hsa_cfun->m_string_constants_map.put (string_cst, sym);
1011 return sym;

1028{

1030
1031hsa_op_with_type *
1032hsa_op_with_type::get_in_type (BrigType16_t dtype, hsa_bb *hbb)
1033{
1034 if (m_type == dtype)
1035 return this;
1036
1037 hsa_op_reg *dest;
1038
1039 if (hsa_needs_cvt (dtype, m_type))
1040 {
1041 dest = new hsa_op_reg (dtype);
1042 hbb->append_insn (new hsa_insn_cvt (dest, this));
1043 }
1044 else if (is_a <hsa_op_reg *> (this))
1045 {
1046 /* In the end, HSA registers do not really have types, only sizes, so if
1047 the sizes match, we can use the register directly. */
1048 gcc_checking_assert (hsa_type_bit_size (dtype)
1049 == hsa_type_bit_size (m_type));
1050 return this;
1051 }
1052 else
1053 {
1054 dest = new hsa_op_reg (m_type);
1055 hbb->append_insn (new hsa_insn_basic (2, BRIG_OPCODE_MOV,
1056 dest->m_type, dest, this));
1057
1058 /* We cannot simply for instance: 'mov_u32 $_3, 48 (s32)' because
1059 type of the operand must be same as type of the instruction. */
1060 dest->m_type = dtype;
1061 }
1062
1063 return dest;
1064}

1066/* Constructor of class representing HSA immediate values. TREE_VAL is the
1067 tree representation of the immediate value. If min32int is true,
1068 always expand integer types to one that has at least 32 bits. */

1070hsa_op_immed::hsa_op_immed (tree tree_val, bool min32int)
1071 : hsa_op_with_type (BRIG_KIND_OPERAND_CONSTANT_BYTES,
1072 hsa_type_for_tree_type (TREE_TYPE (tree_val), NULL,

1092 "HSA ctor should have only constants");

1094 }
1095 }

1154/* Verify register operand. */
1155
1156void
1157hsa_op_reg::verify_ssa ()
1158{
1159 /* Verify that each HSA register has a definition assigned.
1160 Exceptions are VAR_DECL and PARM_DECL that are a default
1161 definition. */
1162 gcc_checking_assert (m_def_insn
1163 || (m_gimple_ssa != NULL
1164 && (!SSA_NAME_VAR (m_gimple_ssa)
1165 || (TREE_CODE (SSA_NAME_VAR (m_gimple_ssa))
1166 != PARM_DECL))
1167 && SSA_NAME_IS_DEFAULT_DEF (m_gimple_ssa)));
1168
1169 /* Verify that every use of the register is really present
1170 in an instruction. */
1171 for (unsigned i = 0; i < m_uses.length (); i++)
1172 {
1173 hsa_insn_basic *use = m_uses[i];
1174
1175 bool is_visited = false;
1176 for (unsigned j = 0; j < use->operand_count (); j++)
1177 {
1178 hsa_op_base *u = use->get_op (j);
1179 hsa_op_address *addr; addr = dyn_cast <hsa_op_address *> (u);
1180 if (addr && addr->m_reg)
1181 u = addr->m_reg;
1182
1183 if (u == this)
1184 {
1185 bool r = !addr && use->op_output_p (j);
1186
1187 if (r)
1188 {
1189 error ("HSA SSA name defined by instruction that is supposed "
1190 "to be using it");
1191 debug_hsa_operand (this);
1192 debug_hsa_insn (use);
1193 internal_error ("HSA SSA verification failed");
1194 }
1195
1196 is_visited = true;
1197 }
1198 }
1199
1200 if (!is_visited)
1201 {
1202 error ("HSA SSA name not among operands of instruction that is "
1203 "supposed to use it");
1204 debug_hsa_operand (this);
1205 debug_hsa_insn (use);
1206 internal_error ("HSA SSA verification failed");
1207 }
1208 }
1209}

1286
1287hsa_op_reg *
1288hsa_function_representation::reg_for_gimple_ssa (tree ssa)
1289{
1290 hsa_op_reg *hreg;
1291
1292 gcc_checking_assert (TREE_CODE (ssa) == SSA_NAME);
1293 if (m_ssa_map[SSA_NAME_VERSION (ssa)])
1294 return m_ssa_map[SSA_NAME_VERSION (ssa)];
1295
1296 hreg = new hsa_op_reg (hsa_type_for_scalar_tree_type (TREE_TYPE (ssa),
1297 true));
1298 hreg->m_gimple_ssa = ssa;
1299 m_ssa_map[SSA_NAME_VERSION (ssa)] = hreg;
1300
1301 return hreg;
1302}

1304void
1305hsa_op_reg::set_definition (hsa_insn_basic *insn)
1306{
1307 if (hsa_cfun->m_in_ssa)
1308 {
1309 gcc_checking_assert (!m_def_insn);
1310 m_def_insn = insn;
1311 }
1312 else
1313 m_def_insn = NULL;
1314}

1316/* Constructor of the class which is the bases of all instructions and directly
1317 represents the most basic ones. NOPS is the number of operands that the
1318 operand vector will contain (and which will be cleared). OP is the opcode
1319 of the instruction. This constructor does not set type. */
1320
1321hsa_insn_basic::hsa_insn_basic (unsigned nops, int opc)
1322 : m_prev (NULL),
1323 m_next (NULL), m_bb (NULL), m_opcode (opc), m_number (0),
1324 m_type (BRIG_TYPE_NONE), m_brig_offset (0)
1325{
1326 if (nops > 0)
1327 m_operands.safe_grow_cleared (nops);
1328
1329 hsa_instructions.safe_push (this);
1330}
1331
1332/* Make OP the operand number INDEX of operands of this instruction. If OP is a
1333 register or an address containing a register, then either set the definition
1334 of the register to this instruction if it an output operand or add this
1335 instruction to the uses if it is an input one. */
1336
1337void
1338hsa_insn_basic::set_op (int index, hsa_op_base *op)
1339{
1340 /* Each address operand is always use. */
1341 hsa_op_address *addr = dyn_cast <hsa_op_address *> (op);
1342 if (addr && addr->m_reg)
1343 addr->m_reg->m_uses.safe_push (this);
1344 else
1345 {
1346 hsa_op_reg *reg = dyn_cast <hsa_op_reg *> (op);
1347 if (reg)
1348 {
1349 if (op_output_p (index))
1350 reg->set_definition (this);
1351 else
1352 reg->m_uses.safe_push (this);
1353 }
1354 }
1355
1356 m_operands[index] = op;
1357}
1358
1359/* Get INDEX-th operand of the instruction. */
1360
1361hsa_op_base *
1362hsa_insn_basic::get_op (int index)
1363{
1364 return m_operands[index];
1365}
1366
1367/* Get address of INDEX-th operand of the instruction. */
1368
1369hsa_op_base **
1370hsa_insn_basic::get_op_addr (int index)
1371{
1372 return &m_operands[index];
1373}

1382/* Constructor of the class which is the bases of all instructions and directly
1383 represents the most basic ones. NOPS is the number of operands that the
1384 operand vector will contain (and which will be cleared). OPC is the opcode
1385 of the instruction, T is the type of the instruction. */
1386
1387hsa_insn_basic::hsa_insn_basic (unsigned nops, int opc, BrigType16_t t,
1388 hsa_op_base *arg0, hsa_op_base *arg1,
1389 hsa_op_base *arg2, hsa_op_base *arg3)
1390 : m_prev (NULL), m_next (NULL), m_bb (NULL), m_opcode (opc),m_number (0),
1391 m_type (t), m_brig_offset (0)
1392{
1393 if (nops > 0)
1394 m_operands.safe_grow_cleared (nops);
1395
1396 if (arg0 != NULL)
1397 {
1398 gcc_checking_assert (nops >= 1);
1399 set_op (0, arg0);
1400 }
1401
1402 if (arg1 != NULL)
1403 {
1404 gcc_checking_assert (nops >= 2);
1405 set_op (1, arg1);
1406 }
1407
1408 if (arg2 != NULL)
1409 {
1410 gcc_checking_assert (nops >= 3);
1411 set_op (2, arg2);
1412 }
1413
1414 if (arg3 != NULL)
1415 {
1416 gcc_checking_assert (nops >= 4);
1417 set_op (3, arg3);
1418 }
1419
1420 hsa_instructions.safe_push (this);
1421}

1430
1431/* Verify the instruction. */
1432
1433void
1434hsa_insn_basic::verify ()
1435{
1436 hsa_op_address *addr;
1437 hsa_op_reg *reg;
1438
1439 /* Iterate all register operands and verify that the instruction
1440 is set in uses of the register. */
1441 for (unsigned i = 0; i < operand_count (); i++)
1442 {
1443 hsa_op_base *use = get_op (i);
1444
1445 if ((addr = dyn_cast <hsa_op_address *> (use)) && addr->m_reg)
1446 {
1447 gcc_assert (addr->m_reg->m_def_insn != this);
1448 use = addr->m_reg;
1449 }
1450
1451 if ((reg = dyn_cast <hsa_op_reg *> (use)) && !op_output_p (i))
1452 {
1453 unsigned j;
1454 for (j = 0; j < reg->m_uses.length (); j++)
1455 {
1456 if (reg->m_uses[j] == this)
1457 break;
1458 }
1459
1460 if (j == reg->m_uses.length ())
1461 {
1462 error ("HSA instruction uses a register but is not among "
1463 "recorded register uses");
1464 debug_hsa_operand (reg);
1465 debug_hsa_insn (this);
1466 internal_error ("HSA instruction verification failed");
1467 }
1468 }
1469 }
1470}

1717/* Append an instruction INSN into the basic block. */
1718
1719void
1720hsa_bb::append_insn (hsa_insn_basic *insn)
1721{
1722 gcc_assert (insn->m_opcode != 0 || insn->operand_count () == 0);
1723 gcc_assert (!insn->m_bb);
1724
1725 insn->m_bb = m_bb;
1726 insn->m_prev = m_last_insn;
1727 insn->m_next = NULL;
1728 if (m_last_insn)
1729 m_last_insn->m_next = insn;
1730 m_last_insn = insn;
1731 if (!m_first_insn)
1732 m_first_insn = insn;
1733}

1749/* Insert HSA instruction NEW_INSN immediately before an existing instruction
1750 OLD_INSN. */
1751
1752static void
1753hsa_insert_insn_before (hsa_insn_basic *new_insn, hsa_insn_basic *old_insn)
1754{
1755 hsa_bb *hbb = hsa_bb_for_bb (old_insn->m_bb);
1756
1757 if (hbb->m_first_insn == old_insn)
1758 hbb->m_first_insn = new_insn;
1759 new_insn->m_prev = old_insn->m_prev;
1760 new_insn->m_next = old_insn;
1761 if (old_insn->m_prev)
1762 old_insn->m_prev->m_next = new_insn;
1763 old_insn->m_prev = new_insn;
1764}
1765
1766/* Append HSA instruction NEW_INSN immediately after an existing instruction
1767 OLD_INSN. */
1768
1769static void
1770hsa_append_insn_after (hsa_insn_basic *new_insn, hsa_insn_basic *old_insn)
1771{
1772 hsa_bb *hbb = hsa_bb_for_bb (old_insn->m_bb);
1773
1774 if (hbb->m_last_insn == old_insn)
1775 hbb->m_last_insn = new_insn;
1776 new_insn->m_prev = old_insn;
1777 new_insn->m_next = old_insn->m_next;
1778 if (old_insn->m_next)
1779 old_insn->m_next->m_prev = new_insn;
1780 old_insn->m_next = new_insn;
1781}
1782
1783/* Return a register containing the calculated value of EXP which must be an
1784 expression consisting of PLUS_EXPRs, MULT_EXPRs, NOP_EXPRs, SSA_NAMEs and
1785 integer constants as returned by get_inner_reference.
1786 Newly generated HSA instructions will be appended to HBB.
1787 Perform all calculations in ADDRTYPE. */
1788
1789static hsa_op_with_type *
1790gen_address_calculation (tree exp, hsa_bb *hbb, BrigType16_t addrtype)
1791{
1792 int opcode;
1793
1794 if (TREE_CODE (exp) == NOP_EXPR)
1795 exp = TREE_OPERAND (exp, 0);
1796
1797 switch (TREE_CODE (exp))
1798 {
1799 case SSA_NAME:
1800 return hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (exp)->get_in_type (addrtype, hbb);
1801
1802 case INTEGER_CST:
1803 {
1804 hsa_op_immed *imm = new hsa_op_immed (exp);
1805 if (addrtype != imm->m_type)
1806 imm->m_type = addrtype;
1807 return imm;
1808 }
1809
1810 case PLUS_EXPR:
1811 opcode = BRIG_OPCODE_ADD;
1812 break;
1813
1814 case MULT_EXPR:
1815 opcode = BRIG_OPCODE_MUL;
1816 break;
1817
1818 default:
1819 gcc_unreachable ();
1820 }
1821
1822 hsa_op_reg *res = new hsa_op_reg (addrtype);
1823 hsa_insn_basic *insn = new hsa_insn_basic (3, opcode, addrtype);
1824 insn->set_op (0, res);
1825
1826 hsa_op_with_type *op1 = gen_address_calculation (TREE_OPERAND (exp, 0), hbb,
1827 addrtype);
1828 hsa_op_with_type *op2 = gen_address_calculation (TREE_OPERAND (exp, 1), hbb,
1829 addrtype);
1830 insn->set_op (1, op1);
1831 insn->set_op (2, op2);
1832
1833 hbb->append_insn (insn);
1834 return res;
1835}
1836
1837/* If R1 is NULL, just return R2, otherwise append an instruction adding them
1838 to HBB and return the register holding the result. */
1839
1840static hsa_op_reg *
1841add_addr_regs_if_needed (hsa_op_reg *r1, hsa_op_reg *r2, hsa_bb *hbb)
1842{
1843 gcc_checking_assert (r2);
1844 if (!r1)
1845 return r2;
1846
1847 hsa_op_reg *res = new hsa_op_reg (r1->m_type);
1848 gcc_assert (!hsa_needs_cvt (r1->m_type, r2->m_type));
1849 hsa_insn_basic *insn = new hsa_insn_basic (3, BRIG_OPCODE_ADD, res->m_type);
1850 insn->set_op (0, res);
1851 insn->set_op (1, r1);
1852 insn->set_op (2, r2);
1853 hbb->append_insn (insn);
1854 return res;
1855}
1856
1857/* Helper of gen_hsa_addr. Update *SYMBOL, *ADDRTYPE, *REG and *OFFSET to
1858 reflect BASE which is the first operand of a MEM_REF or a TARGET_MEM_REF. */
1859
1860static void
1861process_mem_base (tree base, hsa_symbol **symbol, BrigType16_t *addrtype,
1862 hsa_op_reg **reg, offset_int *offset, hsa_bb *hbb)
1863{
1864 if (TREE_CODE (base) == SSA_NAME)
1865 {
1866 gcc_assert (!*reg);
1867 hsa_op_with_type *ssa
1868 = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (base)->get_in_type (*addrtype, hbb);
1869 *reg = dyn_cast <hsa_op_reg *> (ssa);
1870 }
1871 else if (TREE_CODE (base) == ADDR_EXPR)
1872 {
1873 tree decl = TREE_OPERAND (base, 0);
1874
1875 if (!DECL_P (decl) || TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL)
1876 {
1877 HSA_SORRY_AT (EXPR_LOCATION (base),
1878 "support for HSA does not implement a memory reference "
1879 "to a non-declaration type");
1880 return;
1881 }
1882
1883 gcc_assert (!*symbol);
1884
1885 *symbol = get_symbol_for_decl (decl);
1886 *addrtype = hsa_get_segment_addr_type ((*symbol)->m_segment);
1887 }
1888 else if (TREE_CODE (base) == INTEGER_CST)
1889 *offset += wi::to_offset (base);
1890 else
1891 gcc_unreachable ();
1892}

1894/* Forward declaration of a function. */
1895
1896static void
1897gen_hsa_addr_insns (tree val, hsa_op_reg *dest, hsa_bb *hbb);

1899/* Generate HSA address operand for a given tree memory reference REF. If
1900 instructions need to be created to calculate the address, they will be added
1901 to the end of HBB. If a caller provider OUTPUT_BITSIZE and OUTPUT_BITPOS,
1902 the function assumes that the caller will handle possible
1903 bit-field references. Otherwise if we reference a bit-field, sorry message
1904 is displayed. */
1905
1906static hsa_op_address *
1907gen_hsa_addr (tree ref, hsa_bb *hbb, HOST_WIDE_INT *output_bitsize = NULL,
1908 HOST_WIDE_INT *output_bitpos = NULL)
1909{
1910 hsa_symbol *symbol = NULL;
1911 hsa_op_reg *reg = NULL;
1912 offset_int offset = 0;
1913 tree origref = ref;
1914 tree varoffset = NULL_TREE;
1915 BrigType16_t addrtype = hsa_get_segment_addr_type (BRIG_SEGMENT_FLAT);
1916 HOST_WIDE_INT bitsize = 0, bitpos = 0;
1917 BrigType16_t flat_addrtype = hsa_get_segment_addr_type (BRIG_SEGMENT_FLAT);
1918
1919 if (TREE_CODE (ref) == STRING_CST)
1920 {
1921 symbol = hsa_get_string_cst_symbol (ref);
1922 goto out;
1923 }
1924 else if (TREE_CODE (ref) == BIT_FIELD_REF
1925 && ((tree_to_uhwi (TREE_OPERAND (ref, 1)) % BITS_PER_UNIT) != 0
1926 || (tree_to_uhwi (TREE_OPERAND (ref, 2)) % BITS_PER_UNIT) != 0))
1927 {
1928 HSA_SORRY_ATV (EXPR_LOCATION (origref),
1929 "support for HSA does not implement "
1930 "bit field references such as %E", ref);
1931 goto out;
1932 }
1933
1934 if (handled_component_p (ref))
1935 {
1936 enum machine_mode mode;
1937 int unsignedp, volatilep, preversep;
1938
1939 ref = get_inner_reference (ref, &bitsize, &bitpos, &varoffset, &mode,
1940 &unsignedp, &preversep, &volatilep);
1941
1942 offset = bitpos;
1943 offset = wi::rshift (offset, LOG2_BITS_PER_UNIT, SIGNED);
1944 }
1945
1946 switch (TREE_CODE (ref))
1947 {
1948 case ADDR_EXPR:
1949 {
1950 addrtype = hsa_get_segment_addr_type (BRIG_SEGMENT_PRIVATE);
1951 symbol = hsa_cfun->create_hsa_temporary (flat_addrtype);
1952 hsa_op_reg *r = new hsa_op_reg (flat_addrtype);
1953 gen_hsa_addr_insns (ref, r, hbb);
1954 hbb->append_insn (new hsa_insn_mem (BRIG_OPCODE_ST, r->m_type,
1955 r, new hsa_op_address (symbol)));
1956
1957 break;
1958 }
1959 case SSA_NAME:
1960 {
1961 addrtype = hsa_get_segment_addr_type (BRIG_SEGMENT_PRIVATE);
1962 symbol = hsa_cfun->create_hsa_temporary (flat_addrtype);
1963 hsa_op_reg *r = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (ref);
1964
1965 hbb->append_insn (new hsa_insn_mem (BRIG_OPCODE_ST, r->m_type,
1966 r, new hsa_op_address (symbol)));
1967
1968 break;
1969 }
1970 case PARM_DECL:
1971 case VAR_DECL:
1972 case RESULT_DECL:
1973 case CONST_DECL:
1974 gcc_assert (!symbol);
1975 symbol = get_symbol_for_decl (ref);
1976 addrtype = hsa_get_segment_addr_type (symbol->m_segment);
1977 break;
1978
1979 case MEM_REF:
1980 process_mem_base (TREE_OPERAND (ref, 0), &symbol, &addrtype, &reg,
1981 &offset, hbb);
1982
1983 if (!integer_zerop (TREE_OPERAND (ref, 1)))
1984 offset += wi::to_offset (TREE_OPERAND (ref, 1));
1985 break;
1986
1987 case TARGET_MEM_REF:
1988 process_mem_base (TMR_BASE (ref), &symbol, &addrtype, &reg, &offset, hbb);
1989 if (TMR_INDEX (ref))
1990 {
1991 hsa_op_reg *disp1;
1992 hsa_op_base *idx = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa
1993 (TMR_INDEX (ref))->get_in_type (addrtype, hbb);
1994 if (TMR_STEP (ref) && !integer_onep (TMR_STEP (ref)))
1995 {
1996 disp1 = new hsa_op_reg (addrtype);
1997 hsa_insn_basic *insn = new hsa_insn_basic (3, BRIG_OPCODE_MUL,
1998 addrtype);
1999
2000 /* As step must respect addrtype, we overwrite the type
2001 of an immediate value. */
2002 hsa_op_immed *step = new hsa_op_immed (TMR_STEP (ref));
2003 step->m_type = addrtype;
2004
2005 insn->set_op (0, disp1);
2006 insn->set_op (1, idx);
2007 insn->set_op (2, step);
2008 hbb->append_insn (insn);
2009 }
2010 else
2011 disp1 = as_a <hsa_op_reg *> (idx);
2012 reg = add_addr_regs_if_needed (reg, disp1, hbb);
2013 }
2014 if (TMR_INDEX2 (ref))
2015 {
2016 if (TREE_CODE (TMR_INDEX2 (ref)) == SSA_NAME)
2017 {
2018 hsa_op_base *disp2 = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa
2019 (TMR_INDEX2 (ref))->get_in_type (addrtype, hbb);
2020 reg = add_addr_regs_if_needed (reg, as_a <hsa_op_reg *> (disp2),
2021 hbb);
2022 }
2023 else if (TREE_CODE (TMR_INDEX2 (ref)) == INTEGER_CST)
2024 offset += wi::to_offset (TMR_INDEX2 (ref));
2025 else
2026 gcc_unreachable ();
2027 }
2028 offset += wi::to_offset (TMR_OFFSET (ref));
2029 break;
2030 case FUNCTION_DECL:
2031 HSA_SORRY_AT (EXPR_LOCATION (origref),
2032 "support for HSA does not implement function pointers");
2033 goto out;
2034 default:
2035 HSA_SORRY_ATV (EXPR_LOCATION (origref), "support for HSA does "
2036 "not implement memory access to %E", origref);
2037 goto out;
2038 }
2039
2040 if (varoffset)
2041 {
2042 if (TREE_CODE (varoffset) == INTEGER_CST)
2043 offset += wi::to_offset (varoffset);
2044 else
2045 {
2046 hsa_op_base *off_op = gen_address_calculation (varoffset, hbb,
2047 addrtype);
2048 reg = add_addr_regs_if_needed (reg, as_a <hsa_op_reg *> (off_op),
2049 hbb);
2050 }
2051 }
2052
2053 gcc_checking_assert ((symbol
2054 && addrtype
2055 == hsa_get_segment_addr_type (symbol->m_segment))
2056 || (!symbol
2057 && addrtype
2058 == hsa_get_segment_addr_type (BRIG_SEGMENT_FLAT)));
2059out:
2060 HOST_WIDE_INT hwi_offset = offset.to_shwi ();
2061
2062 /* Calculate remaining bitsize offset (if presented). */
2063 bitpos %= BITS_PER_UNIT;
2064 /* If bitsize is a power of two that is greater or equal to BITS_PER_UNIT, it
2065 is not a reason to think this is a bit-field access. */
2066 if (bitpos == 0
2067 && (bitsize >= BITS_PER_UNIT)
2068 && !(bitsize & (bitsize - 1)))
2069 bitsize = 0;
2070
2071 if ((bitpos || bitsize) && (output_bitpos == NULL || output_bitsize == NULL))
2072 HSA_SORRY_ATV (EXPR_LOCATION (origref), "support for HSA does not "
2073 "implement unhandled bit field reference such as %E", ref);
2074
2075 if (output_bitsize != NULL && output_bitpos != NULL)
2076 {
2077 *output_bitsize = bitsize;
2078 *output_bitpos = bitpos;
2079 }
2080
2081 return new hsa_op_address (symbol, reg, hwi_offset);
2082}
2083
2084/* Generate HSA address operand for a given tree memory reference REF. If
2085 instructions need to be created to calculate the address, they will be added
2086 to the end of HBB. OUTPUT_ALIGN is alignment of the created address. */
2087
2088static hsa_op_address *
2089gen_hsa_addr_with_align (tree ref, hsa_bb *hbb, BrigAlignment8_t *output_align)
2090{
2091 hsa_op_address *addr = gen_hsa_addr (ref, hbb);
2092 if (addr->m_reg || !addr->m_symbol)
2093 *output_align = hsa_object_alignment (ref);
2094 else
2095 {
2096 /* If the address consists only of a symbol and an offset, we
2097 compute the alignment ourselves to take into account any alignment
2098 promotions we might have done for the HSA symbol representation. */
2099 unsigned align = hsa_byte_alignment (addr->m_symbol->m_align);
2100 unsigned misalign = addr->m_imm_offset & (align - 1);
2101 if (misalign)
2102 align = least_bit_hwi (misalign);
2103 *output_align = hsa_alignment_encoding (BITS_PER_UNIT * align);
2104 }
2105 return addr;
2106}

2108/* Generate HSA address for a function call argument of given TYPE.
2109 INDEX is used to generate corresponding name of the arguments.
2110 Special value -1 represents fact that result value is created. */
2111
2112static hsa_op_address *
2113gen_hsa_addr_for_arg (tree tree_type, int index)
2114{
2115 hsa_symbol *sym = new hsa_symbol (BRIG_TYPE_NONE, BRIG_SEGMENT_ARG,
2116 BRIG_LINKAGE_ARG);
2117 sym->m_type = hsa_type_for_tree_type (tree_type, &sym->m_dim);
2118
2119 if (index == -1) /* Function result. */
2120 sym->m_name = "res";
2121 else /* Function call arguments. */
2122 {
2123 sym->m_name = NULL;
2124 sym->m_name_number = index;
2125 }
2126
2127 return new hsa_op_address (sym);
2128}

2130/* Generate HSA instructions that process all necessary conversions
2131 of an ADDR to flat addressing and place the result into DEST.
2132 Instructions are appended to HBB. */
2133
2134static void
2135convert_addr_to_flat_segment (hsa_op_address *addr, hsa_op_reg *dest,
2136 hsa_bb *hbb)
2137{
2138 hsa_insn_basic *insn = new hsa_insn_basic (2, BRIG_OPCODE_LDA);
2139 insn->set_op (1, addr);
2140 if (addr->m_symbol && addr->m_symbol->m_segment != BRIG_SEGMENT_GLOBAL)
2141 {
2142 /* LDA produces segment-relative address, we need to convert
2143 it to the flat one. */
2144 hsa_op_reg *tmp;
2145 tmp = new hsa_op_reg (hsa_get_segment_addr_type
2146 (addr->m_symbol->m_segment));
2147 hsa_insn_seg *seg;
2148 seg = new hsa_insn_seg (BRIG_OPCODE_STOF,
2149 hsa_get_segment_addr_type (BRIG_SEGMENT_FLAT),
2150 tmp->m_type, addr->m_symbol->m_segment, dest,
2151 tmp);
2152
2153 insn->set_op (0, tmp);
2154 insn->m_type = tmp->m_type;
2155 hbb->append_insn (insn);
2156 hbb->append_insn (seg);
2157 }
2158 else
2159 {
2160 insn->set_op (0, dest);
2161 insn->m_type = hsa_get_segment_addr_type (BRIG_SEGMENT_FLAT);
2162 hbb->append_insn (insn);
2163 }
2164}
2165
2166/* Generate HSA instructions that calculate address of VAL including all
2167 necessary conversions to flat addressing and place the result into DEST.
2168 Instructions are appended to HBB. */
2169
2170static void
2171gen_hsa_addr_insns (tree val, hsa_op_reg *dest, hsa_bb *hbb)
2172{
2173 /* Handle cases like tmp = NULL, where we just emit a move instruction
2174 to a register. */
2175 if (TREE_CODE (val) == INTEGER_CST)
2176 {
2177 hsa_op_immed *c = new hsa_op_immed (val);
2178 hsa_insn_basic *insn = new hsa_insn_basic (2, BRIG_OPCODE_MOV,
2179 dest->m_type, dest, c);
2180 hbb->append_insn (insn);
2181 return;
2182 }
2183
2184 hsa_op_address *addr;
2185
2186 gcc_assert (dest->m_type == hsa_get_segment_addr_type (BRIG_SEGMENT_FLAT));
2187 if (TREE_CODE (val) == ADDR_EXPR)
2188 val = TREE_OPERAND (val, 0);
2189 addr = gen_hsa_addr (val, hbb);
2190
2191 if (TREE_CODE (val) == CONST_DECL
2192 && is_gimple_reg_type (TREE_TYPE (val)))
2193 {
2194 gcc_assert (addr->m_symbol
2195 && addr->m_symbol->m_segment == BRIG_SEGMENT_READONLY);
2196 /* CONST_DECLs are in readonly segment which however does not have
2197 addresses convertible to flat segments. So copy it to a private one
2198 and take address of that. */
2199 BrigType16_t csttype
2200 = mem_type_for_type (hsa_type_for_scalar_tree_type (TREE_TYPE (val),
2201 false));
2202 hsa_op_reg *r = new hsa_op_reg (csttype);
2203 hbb->append_insn (new hsa_insn_mem (BRIG_OPCODE_LD, csttype, r,
2204 new hsa_op_address (addr->m_symbol)));
2205 hsa_symbol *copysym = hsa_cfun->create_hsa_temporary (csttype);
2206 hbb->append_insn (new hsa_insn_mem (BRIG_OPCODE_ST, csttype, r,
2207 new hsa_op_address (copysym)));
2208 addr->m_symbol = copysym;
2209 }
2210 else if (addr->m_symbol && addr->m_symbol->m_segment == BRIG_SEGMENT_READONLY)
2211 {
2212 HSA_SORRY_ATV (EXPR_LOCATION (val), "support for HSA does "
2213 "not implement taking addresses of complex "
2214 "CONST_DECLs such as %E", val);
2215 return;
2216 }
2217
2218
2219 convert_addr_to_flat_segment (addr, dest, hbb);
2220}

2222/* Return an HSA register or HSA immediate value operand corresponding to
2223 gimple operand OP. */
2224
2225static hsa_op_with_type *
2226hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (tree op, hsa_bb *hbb)
2227{
2228 hsa_op_reg *tmp;
2229
2230 if (TREE_CODE (op) == SSA_NAME)
2231 tmp = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (op);
2232 else if (!POINTER_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (op)))
2233 return new hsa_op_immed (op);
2234 else
2235 {
2236 tmp = new hsa_op_reg (hsa_get_segment_addr_type (BRIG_SEGMENT_FLAT));
2237 gen_hsa_addr_insns (op, tmp, hbb);
2238 }
2239 return tmp;
2240}

2242/* Create a simple movement instruction with register destination DEST and
2243 register or immediate source SRC and append it to the end of HBB. */
2244
2245void
2246hsa_build_append_simple_mov (hsa_op_reg *dest, hsa_op_base *src, hsa_bb *hbb)
2247{
2248 /* Moves of packed data between registers need to adhere to the same type
2249 rules like when dealing with memory. */
2250 BrigType16_t tp = mem_type_for_type (dest->m_type);
2251 hsa_insn_basic *insn = new hsa_insn_basic (2, BRIG_OPCODE_MOV, tp, dest, src);
2252 if (hsa_op_reg *sreg = dyn_cast <hsa_op_reg *> (src))
2253 gcc_assert (hsa_type_bit_size (dest->m_type)
2254 == hsa_type_bit_size (sreg->m_type));
2255 else
2256 gcc_assert (hsa_type_bit_size (dest->m_type)
2257 == hsa_type_bit_size (as_a <hsa_op_immed *> (src)->m_type));
2258
2259 hbb->append_insn (insn);
2260}

2262/* Generate HSAIL instructions loading a bit field into register DEST.
2263 VALUE_REG is a register of a SSA name that is used in the bit field
2264 reference. To identify a bit field BITPOS is offset to the loaded memory
2265 and BITSIZE is number of bits of the bit field.
2266 Add instructions to HBB. */
2267
2268static void
2269gen_hsa_insns_for_bitfield (hsa_op_reg *dest, hsa_op_reg *value_reg,
2270 HOST_WIDE_INT bitsize, HOST_WIDE_INT bitpos,
2271 hsa_bb *hbb)
2272{
2273 unsigned type_bitsize = hsa_type_bit_size (dest->m_type);
2274 unsigned left_shift = type_bitsize - (bitsize + bitpos);
2275 unsigned right_shift = left_shift + bitpos;
2276
2277 if (left_shift)
2278 {
2279 hsa_op_reg *value_reg_2 = new hsa_op_reg (dest->m_type);
2280 hsa_op_immed *c = new hsa_op_immed (left_shift, BRIG_TYPE_U32);
2281
2282 hsa_insn_basic *lshift
2283 = new hsa_insn_basic (3, BRIG_OPCODE_SHL, value_reg_2->m_type,
2284 value_reg_2, value_reg, c);
2285
2286 hbb->append_insn (lshift);
2287
2288 value_reg = value_reg_2;
2289 }
2290
2291 if (right_shift)
2292 {
2293 hsa_op_reg *value_reg_2 = new hsa_op_reg (dest->m_type);
2294 hsa_op_immed *c = new hsa_op_immed (right_shift, BRIG_TYPE_U32);
2295
2296 hsa_insn_basic *rshift
2297 = new hsa_insn_basic (3, BRIG_OPCODE_SHR, value_reg_2->m_type,
2298 value_reg_2, value_reg, c);
2299
2300 hbb->append_insn (rshift);
2301
2302 value_reg = value_reg_2;
2303 }
2304
2305 hsa_insn_basic *assignment
2306 = new hsa_insn_basic (2, BRIG_OPCODE_MOV, dest->m_type, dest, value_reg);
2307 hbb->append_insn (assignment);
2308}

2311/* Generate HSAIL instructions loading a bit field into register DEST. ADDR is
2312 prepared memory address which is used to load the bit field. To identify a
2313 bit field BITPOS is offset to the loaded memory and BITSIZE is number of
2314 bits of the bit field. Add instructions to HBB. Load must be performed in
2315 alignment ALIGN. */
2316
2317static void
2318gen_hsa_insns_for_bitfield_load (hsa_op_reg *dest, hsa_op_address *addr,
2319 HOST_WIDE_INT bitsize, HOST_WIDE_INT bitpos,
2320 hsa_bb *hbb, BrigAlignment8_t align)
2321{
2322 hsa_op_reg *value_reg = new hsa_op_reg (dest->m_type);
2323 hsa_insn_mem *mem = new hsa_insn_mem (BRIG_OPCODE_LD, dest->m_type, value_reg,
2324 addr);
2325 mem->set_align (align);
2326 hbb->append_insn (mem);
2327 gen_hsa_insns_for_bitfield (dest, value_reg, bitsize, bitpos, hbb);
2328}
2329
2330/* Return the alignment of base memory accesses we issue to perform bit-field
2331 memory access REF. */
2332
2333static BrigAlignment8_t
2334hsa_bitmemref_alignment (tree ref)
2335{
2336 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT bit_offset = 0;
2337
2338 while (true)
2339 {
2340 if (TREE_CODE (ref) == BIT_FIELD_REF)
2341 {
2342 if (!tree_fits_uhwi_p (TREE_OPERAND (ref, 2)))
2343 return BRIG_ALIGNMENT_1;
2344 bit_offset += tree_to_uhwi (TREE_OPERAND (ref, 2));
2345 }
2346 else if (TREE_CODE (ref) == COMPONENT_REF
2347 && DECL_BIT_FIELD (TREE_OPERAND (ref, 1)))
2348 bit_offset += int_bit_position (TREE_OPERAND (ref, 1));
2349 else
2350 break;
2351 ref = TREE_OPERAND (ref, 0);
2352 }
2353
2354 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT bits = bit_offset % BITS_PER_UNIT;
2355 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT byte_bits = bit_offset - bits;
2356 BrigAlignment8_t base = hsa_object_alignment (ref);
2357 if (byte_bits == 0)
2358 return base;
2359 return MIN (base, hsa_alignment_encoding (least_bit_hwi (byte_bits)));
2360}
2361
2362/* Generate HSAIL instructions loading something into register DEST. RHS is
2363 tree representation of the loaded data, which are loaded as type TYPE. Add
2364 instructions to HBB. */
2365
2366static void
2367gen_hsa_insns_for_load (hsa_op_reg *dest, tree rhs, tree type, hsa_bb *hbb)
2368{
2369 /* The destination SSA name will give us the type. */
2370 if (TREE_CODE (rhs) == VIEW_CONVERT_EXPR)
2371 rhs = TREE_OPERAND (rhs, 0);
2372
2373 if (TREE_CODE (rhs) == SSA_NAME)
2374 {
2375 hsa_op_reg *src = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (rhs);
2376 hsa_build_append_simple_mov (dest, src, hbb);
2377 }
2378 else if (is_gimple_min_invariant (rhs)
2379 || TREE_CODE (rhs) == ADDR_EXPR)
2380 {
2381 if (POINTER_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (rhs)))
2382 {
2383 if (dest->m_type != hsa_get_segment_addr_type (BRIG_SEGMENT_FLAT))
2384 {
2385 HSA_SORRY_ATV (EXPR_LOCATION (rhs),
2386 "support for HSA does not implement conversion "
2387 "of %E to the requested non-pointer type.", rhs);
2388 return;
2389 }
2390
2391 gen_hsa_addr_insns (rhs, dest, hbb);
2392 }
2393 else if (TREE_CODE (rhs) == COMPLEX_CST)
2394 {
2395 hsa_op_immed *real_part = new hsa_op_immed (TREE_REALPART (rhs));
2396 hsa_op_immed *imag_part = new hsa_op_immed (TREE_IMAGPART (rhs));
2397
2398 hsa_op_reg *real_part_reg
2399 = new hsa_op_reg (hsa_type_for_scalar_tree_type (TREE_TYPE (type),
2400 true));
2401 hsa_op_reg *imag_part_reg
2402 = new hsa_op_reg (hsa_type_for_scalar_tree_type (TREE_TYPE (type),
2403 true));
2404
2405 hsa_build_append_simple_mov (real_part_reg, real_part, hbb);
2406 hsa_build_append_simple_mov (imag_part_reg, imag_part, hbb);
2407
2408 BrigType16_t src_type = hsa_bittype_for_type (real_part_reg->m_type);
2409
2410 hsa_insn_packed *insn
2411 = new hsa_insn_packed (3, BRIG_OPCODE_COMBINE, dest->m_type,
2412 src_type, dest, real_part_reg,
2413 imag_part_reg);
2414 hbb->append_insn (insn);
2415 }
2416 else
2417 {
2418 hsa_op_immed *imm = new hsa_op_immed (rhs);
2419 hsa_build_append_simple_mov (dest, imm, hbb);
2420 }
2421 }
2422 else if (TREE_CODE (rhs) == REALPART_EXPR || TREE_CODE (rhs) == IMAGPART_EXPR)
2423 {
2424 tree pack_type = TREE_TYPE (TREE_OPERAND (rhs, 0));
2425
2426 hsa_op_reg *packed_reg
2427 = new hsa_op_reg (hsa_type_for_scalar_tree_type (pack_type, true));
2428
2429 tree complex_rhs = TREE_OPERAND (rhs, 0);
2430 gen_hsa_insns_for_load (packed_reg, complex_rhs, TREE_TYPE (complex_rhs),
2431 hbb);
2432
2433 hsa_op_reg *real_reg
2434 = new hsa_op_reg (hsa_type_for_scalar_tree_type (type, true));
2435
2436 hsa_op_reg *imag_reg
2437 = new hsa_op_reg (hsa_type_for_scalar_tree_type (type, true));
2438
2439 BrigKind16_t brig_type = packed_reg->m_type;
2440 hsa_insn_packed *packed
2441 = new hsa_insn_packed (3, BRIG_OPCODE_EXPAND,
2442 hsa_bittype_for_type (real_reg->m_type),
2443 brig_type, real_reg, imag_reg, packed_reg);
2444
2445 hbb->append_insn (packed);
2446
2447 hsa_op_reg *source = TREE_CODE (rhs) == REALPART_EXPR ?
2448 real_reg : imag_reg;
2449
2450 hsa_insn_basic *insn = new hsa_insn_basic (2, BRIG_OPCODE_MOV,
2451 dest->m_type, dest, source);
2452
2453 hbb->append_insn (insn);
2454 }
2455 else if (TREE_CODE (rhs) == BIT_FIELD_REF
2456 && TREE_CODE (TREE_OPERAND (rhs, 0)) == SSA_NAME)
2457 {
2458 tree ssa_name = TREE_OPERAND (rhs, 0);
2459 HOST_WIDE_INT bitsize = tree_to_uhwi (TREE_OPERAND (rhs, 1));
2460 HOST_WIDE_INT bitpos = tree_to_uhwi (TREE_OPERAND (rhs, 2));
2461
2462 hsa_op_reg *imm_value = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (ssa_name);
2463 gen_hsa_insns_for_bitfield (dest, imm_value, bitsize, bitpos, hbb);
2464 }
2465 else if (DECL_P (rhs) || TREE_CODE (rhs) == MEM_REF
2466 || TREE_CODE (rhs) == TARGET_MEM_REF
2467 || handled_component_p (rhs))
2468 {
2469 HOST_WIDE_INT bitsize, bitpos;
2470
2471 /* Load from memory. */
2472 hsa_op_address *addr;
2473 addr = gen_hsa_addr (rhs, hbb, &bitsize, &bitpos);
2474
2475 /* Handle load of a bit field. */
2476 if (bitsize > 64)
2477 {
2478 HSA_SORRY_AT (EXPR_LOCATION (rhs),
2479 "support for HSA does not implement load from a bit "
2480 "field bigger than 64 bits");
2481 return;
2482 }
2483
2484 if (bitsize || bitpos)
2485 gen_hsa_insns_for_bitfield_load (dest, addr, bitsize, bitpos, hbb,
2486 hsa_bitmemref_alignment (rhs));
2487 else
2488 {
2489 BrigType16_t mtype;
2490 /* Not dest->m_type, that's possibly extended. */
2491 mtype = mem_type_for_type (hsa_type_for_scalar_tree_type (type,
2492 false));
2493 hsa_insn_mem *mem = new hsa_insn_mem (BRIG_OPCODE_LD, mtype, dest,
2494 addr);
2495 mem->set_align (hsa_object_alignment (rhs));
2496 hbb->append_insn (mem);
2497 }
2498 }
2499 else
2500 HSA_SORRY_ATV (EXPR_LOCATION (rhs),
2501 "support for HSA does not implement loading "
2502 "of expression %E",
2503 rhs);
2504}
2505
2506/* Return number of bits necessary for representation of a bit field,
2507 starting at BITPOS with size of BITSIZE. */
2508
2509static unsigned
2510get_bitfield_size (unsigned bitpos, unsigned bitsize)
2511{
2512 unsigned s = bitpos + bitsize;
2513 unsigned sizes[] = {8, 16, 32, 64};
2514
2515 for (unsigned i = 0; i < 4; i++)
2516 if (s <= sizes[i])
2517 return sizes[i];
2518
2519 gcc_unreachable ();
2520 return 0;
2521}
2522
2523/* Generate HSAIL instructions storing into memory. LHS is the destination of
2524 the store, SRC is the source operand. Add instructions to HBB. */
2525
2526static void
2527gen_hsa_insns_for_store (tree lhs, hsa_op_base *src, hsa_bb *hbb)
2528{
2529 HOST_WIDE_INT bitsize = 0, bitpos = 0;
2530 BrigAlignment8_t req_align;
2531 BrigType16_t mtype;
2532 mtype = mem_type_for_type (hsa_type_for_scalar_tree_type (TREE_TYPE (lhs),
2533 false));
2534 hsa_op_address *addr;
2535 addr = gen_hsa_addr (lhs, hbb, &bitsize, &bitpos);
2536
2537 /* Handle store to a bit field. */
2538 if (bitsize > 64)
2539 {
2540 HSA_SORRY_AT (EXPR_LOCATION (lhs),
2541 "support for HSA does not implement store to a bit field "
2542 "bigger than 64 bits");
2543 return;
2544 }
2545
2546 unsigned type_bitsize = get_bitfield_size (bitpos, bitsize);
2547
2548 /* HSAIL does not support MOV insn with 16-bits integers. */
2549 if (type_bitsize < 32)
2550 type_bitsize = 32;
2551
2552 if (bitpos || (bitsize && type_bitsize != bitsize))
2553 {
2554 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT mask = 0;
2555 BrigType16_t mem_type
2556 = get_integer_type_by_bytes (type_bitsize / BITS_PER_UNIT,
2557 !TYPE_UNSIGNED (TREE_TYPE (lhs)));
2558
2559 for (unsigned i = 0; i < type_bitsize; i++)
2560 if (i < bitpos || i >= bitpos + bitsize)
2561 mask |= ((unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT)1 << i);
2562
2563 hsa_op_reg *value_reg = new hsa_op_reg (mem_type);
2564
2565 req_align = hsa_bitmemref_alignment (lhs);
2566 /* Load value from memory. */
2567 hsa_insn_mem *mem = new hsa_insn_mem (BRIG_OPCODE_LD, mem_type,
2568 value_reg, addr);
2569 mem->set_align (req_align);
2570 hbb->append_insn (mem);
2571
2572 /* AND the loaded value with prepared mask. */
2573 hsa_op_reg *cleared_reg = new hsa_op_reg (mem_type);
2574
2575 BrigType16_t t
2576 = get_integer_type_by_bytes (type_bitsize / BITS_PER_UNIT, false);
2577 hsa_op_immed *c = new hsa_op_immed (mask, t);
2578
2579 hsa_insn_basic *clearing
2580 = new hsa_insn_basic (3, BRIG_OPCODE_AND, mem_type, cleared_reg,
2581 value_reg, c);
2582 hbb->append_insn (clearing);
2583
2584 /* Shift to left a value that is going to be stored. */
2585 hsa_op_reg *new_value_reg = new hsa_op_reg (mem_type);
2586
2587 hsa_insn_basic *basic = new hsa_insn_basic (2, BRIG_OPCODE_MOV, mem_type,
2588 new_value_reg, src);
2589 hbb->append_insn (basic);
2590
2591 if (bitpos)
2592 {
2593 hsa_op_reg *shifted_value_reg = new hsa_op_reg (mem_type);
2594 c = new hsa_op_immed (bitpos, BRIG_TYPE_U32);
2595
2596 hsa_insn_basic *basic
2597 = new hsa_insn_basic (3, BRIG_OPCODE_SHL, mem_type,
2598 shifted_value_reg, new_value_reg, c);
2599 hbb->append_insn (basic);
2600
2601 new_value_reg = shifted_value_reg;
2602 }
2603
2604 /* OR the prepared value with prepared chunk loaded from memory. */
2605 hsa_op_reg *prepared_reg= new hsa_op_reg (mem_type);
2606 basic = new hsa_insn_basic (3, BRIG_OPCODE_OR, mem_type, prepared_reg,
2607 new_value_reg, cleared_reg);
2608 hbb->append_insn (basic);
2609
2610 src = prepared_reg;
2611 mtype = mem_type;
2612 }
2613 else
2614 req_align = hsa_object_alignment (lhs);
2615
2616 hsa_insn_mem *mem = new hsa_insn_mem (BRIG_OPCODE_ST, mtype, src, addr);
2617 mem->set_align (req_align);
2618
2619 /* The HSAIL verifier has another constraint: if the source is an immediate
2620 then it must match the destination type. If it's a register the low bits
2621 will be used for sub-word stores. We're always allocating new operands so
2622 we can modify the above in place. */
2623 if (hsa_op_immed *imm = dyn_cast <hsa_op_immed *> (src))
2624 {
2625 if (!hsa_type_packed_p (imm->m_type))
2626 imm->m_type = mem->m_type;
2627 else
2628 {
2629 /* ...and all vector immediates apparently need to be vectors of
2630 unsigned bytes. */
2631 unsigned bs = hsa_type_bit_size (imm->m_type);
2632 gcc_assert (bs == hsa_type_bit_size (mem->m_type));
2633 switch (bs)
2634 {
2635 case 32:
2636 imm->m_type = BRIG_TYPE_U8X4;
2637 break;
2638 case 64:
2639 imm->m_type = BRIG_TYPE_U8X8;
2640 break;
2641 case 128:
2642 imm->m_type = BRIG_TYPE_U8X16;
2643 break;
2644 default:
2645 gcc_unreachable ();
2646 }
2647 }
2648 }
2649
2650 hbb->append_insn (mem);
2651}
2652
2653/* Generate memory copy instructions that are going to be used
2654 for copying a SRC memory to TARGET memory,
2655 represented by pointer in a register. MIN_ALIGN is minimal alignment
2656 of provided HSA addresses. */
2657
2658static void
2659gen_hsa_memory_copy (hsa_bb *hbb, hsa_op_address *target, hsa_op_address *src,
2660 unsigned size, BrigAlignment8_t min_align)
2661{
2662 hsa_op_address *addr;
2663 hsa_insn_mem *mem;
2664
2665 unsigned offset = 0;
2666 unsigned min_byte_align = hsa_byte_alignment (min_align);
2667
2668 while (size)
2669 {
2670 unsigned s;
2671 if (size >= 8)
2672 s = 8;
2673 else if (size >= 4)
2674 s = 4;
2675 else if (size >= 2)
2676 s = 2;
2677 else
2678 s = 1;
2679
2680 if (s > min_byte_align)
2681 s = min_byte_align;
2682
2683 BrigType16_t t = get_integer_type_by_bytes (s, false);
2684
2685 hsa_op_reg *tmp = new hsa_op_reg (t);
2686 addr = new hsa_op_address (src->m_symbol, src->m_reg,
2687 src->m_imm_offset + offset);
2688 mem = new hsa_insn_mem (BRIG_OPCODE_LD, t, tmp, addr);
2689 hbb->append_insn (mem);
2690
2691 addr = new hsa_op_address (target->m_symbol, target->m_reg,
2692 target->m_imm_offset + offset);
2693 mem = new hsa_insn_mem (BRIG_OPCODE_ST, t, tmp, addr);
2694 hbb->append_insn (mem);
2695 offset += s;
2696 size -= s;
2697 }
2698}
2699
2700/* Create a memset mask that is created by copying a CONSTANT byte value
2701 to an integer of BYTE_SIZE bytes. */
2702
2703static unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT
2704build_memset_value (unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT constant, unsigned byte_size)
2705{
2706 if (constant == 0)
2707 return 0;
2708
2709 HOST_WIDE_INT v = constant;
2710
2711 for (unsigned i = 1; i < byte_size; i++)
2712 v |= constant << (8 * i);
2713
2714 return v;
2715}
2716
2717/* Generate memory set instructions that are going to be used
2718 for setting a CONSTANT byte value to TARGET memory of SIZE bytes.
2719 MIN_ALIGN is minimal alignment of provided HSA addresses. */
2720
2721static void
2722gen_hsa_memory_set (hsa_bb *hbb, hsa_op_address *target,
2723 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT constant,
2724 unsigned size, BrigAlignment8_t min_align)
2725{
2726 hsa_op_address *addr;
2727 hsa_insn_mem *mem;
2728
2729 unsigned offset = 0;
2730 unsigned min_byte_align = hsa_byte_alignment (min_align);
2731
2732 while (size)
2733 {
2734 unsigned s;
2735 if (size >= 8)
2736 s = 8;
2737 else if (size >= 4)
2738 s = 4;
2739 else if (size >= 2)
2740 s = 2;
2741 else
2742 s = 1;
2743
2744 if (s > min_byte_align)
2745 s = min_byte_align;
2746
2747 addr = new hsa_op_address (target->m_symbol, target->m_reg,
2748 target->m_imm_offset + offset);
2749
2750 BrigType16_t t = get_integer_type_by_bytes (s, false);
2751 HOST_WIDE_INT c = build_memset_value (constant, s);
2752
2753 mem = new hsa_insn_mem (BRIG_OPCODE_ST, t, new hsa_op_immed (c, t),
2754 addr);
2755 hbb->append_insn (mem);
2756 offset += s;
2757 size -= s;
2758 }
2759}

2761/* Generate HSAIL instructions for a single assignment
2762 of an empty constructor to an ADDR_LHS. Constructor is passed as a
2763 tree RHS and all instructions are appended to HBB. ALIGN is
2764 alignment of the address. */
2765
2766void
2767gen_hsa_ctor_assignment (hsa_op_address *addr_lhs, tree rhs, hsa_bb *hbb,
2768 BrigAlignment8_t align)
2769{
2770 if (CONSTRUCTOR_NELTS (rhs))
2771 {
2772 HSA_SORRY_AT (EXPR_LOCATION (rhs),
2773 "support for HSA does not implement load from constructor");
2774 return;
2775 }
2776
2777 unsigned size = tree_to_uhwi (TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (TREE_TYPE (rhs)));
2778 gen_hsa_memory_set (hbb, addr_lhs, 0, size, align);
2779}
2780
2781/* Generate HSA instructions for a single assignment of RHS to LHS.
2782 HBB is the basic block they will be appended to. */
2783
2784static void
2785gen_hsa_insns_for_single_assignment (tree lhs, tree rhs, hsa_bb *hbb)
2786{
2787 if (TREE_CODE (lhs) == SSA_NAME)
2788 {
2789 hsa_op_reg *dest = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (lhs);
2790 if (hsa_seen_error ())
2791 return;
2792
2793 gen_hsa_insns_for_load (dest, rhs, TREE_TYPE (lhs), hbb);
2794 }
2795 else if (TREE_CODE (rhs) == SSA_NAME
2796 || (is_gimple_min_invariant (rhs) && TREE_CODE (rhs) != STRING_CST))
2797 {
2798 /* Store to memory. */
2799 hsa_op_base *src = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (rhs, hbb);
2800 if (hsa_seen_error ())
2801 return;
2802
2803 gen_hsa_insns_for_store (lhs, src, hbb);
2804 }
2805 else
2806 {
2807 BrigAlignment8_t lhs_align;
2808 hsa_op_address *addr_lhs = gen_hsa_addr_with_align (lhs, hbb,
2809 &lhs_align);
2810
2811 if (TREE_CODE (rhs) == CONSTRUCTOR)
2812 gen_hsa_ctor_assignment (addr_lhs, rhs, hbb, lhs_align);
2813 else
2814 {
2815 BrigAlignment8_t rhs_align;
2816 hsa_op_address *addr_rhs = gen_hsa_addr_with_align (rhs, hbb,
2817 &rhs_align);
2818
2819 unsigned size = tree_to_uhwi (TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (TREE_TYPE (rhs)));
2820 gen_hsa_memory_copy (hbb, addr_lhs, addr_rhs, size,
2821 MIN (lhs_align, rhs_align));
2822 }
2823 }
2824}

2826/* Prepend before INSN a load from spill symbol of SPILL_REG. Return the
2827 register into which we loaded. If this required another register to convert
2828 from a B1 type, return it in *PTMP2, otherwise store NULL into it. We
2829 assume we are out of SSA so the returned register does not have its
2830 definition set. */
2831
2832hsa_op_reg *
2833hsa_spill_in (hsa_insn_basic *insn, hsa_op_reg *spill_reg, hsa_op_reg **ptmp2)
2834{
2835 hsa_symbol *spill_sym = spill_reg->m_spill_sym;
2836 hsa_op_reg *reg = new hsa_op_reg (spill_sym->m_type);
2837 hsa_op_address *addr = new hsa_op_address (spill_sym);
2838
2839 hsa_insn_mem *mem = new hsa_insn_mem (BRIG_OPCODE_LD, spill_sym->m_type,
2840 reg, addr);
2841 hsa_insert_insn_before (mem, insn);
2842
2843 *ptmp2 = NULL;
2844 if (spill_reg->m_type == BRIG_TYPE_B1)
2845 {
2846 hsa_insn_basic *cvtinsn;
2847 *ptmp2 = reg;
2848 reg = new hsa_op_reg (spill_reg->m_type);
2849
2850 cvtinsn = new hsa_insn_cvt (reg, *ptmp2);
2851 hsa_insert_insn_before (cvtinsn, insn);
2852 }
2853 return reg;
2854}
2855
2856/* Append after INSN a store to spill symbol of SPILL_REG. Return the register
2857 from which we stored. If this required another register to convert to a B1
2858 type, return it in *PTMP2, otherwise store NULL into it. We assume we are
2859 out of SSA so the returned register does not have its use updated. */
2860
2861hsa_op_reg *
2862hsa_spill_out (hsa_insn_basic *insn, hsa_op_reg *spill_reg, hsa_op_reg **ptmp2)
2863{
2864 hsa_symbol *spill_sym = spill_reg->m_spill_sym;
2865 hsa_op_reg *reg = new hsa_op_reg (spill_sym->m_type);
2866 hsa_op_address *addr = new hsa_op_address (spill_sym);
2867 hsa_op_reg *returnreg;
2868
2869 *ptmp2 = NULL;
2870 returnreg = reg;
2871 if (spill_reg->m_type == BRIG_TYPE_B1)
2872 {
2873 hsa_insn_basic *cvtinsn;
2874 *ptmp2 = new hsa_op_reg (spill_sym->m_type);
2875 reg->m_type = spill_reg->m_type;
2876
2877 cvtinsn = new hsa_insn_cvt (*ptmp2, returnreg);
2878 hsa_append_insn_after (cvtinsn, insn);
2879 insn = cvtinsn;
2880 reg = *ptmp2;
2881 }
2882
2883 hsa_insn_mem *mem = new hsa_insn_mem (BRIG_OPCODE_ST, spill_sym->m_type, reg,
2884 addr);
2885 hsa_append_insn_after (mem, insn);
2886 return returnreg;
2887}

2889/* Generate a comparison instruction that will compare LHS and RHS with
2890 comparison specified by CODE and put result into register DEST. DEST has to
2891 have its type set already but must not have its definition set yet.
2892 Generated instructions will be added to HBB. */
2893
2894static void
2895gen_hsa_cmp_insn_from_gimple (enum tree_code code, tree lhs, tree rhs,
2896 hsa_op_reg *dest, hsa_bb *hbb)
2897{
2898 BrigCompareOperation8_t compare;
2899
2900 switch (code)
2901 {
2902 case LT_EXPR:
2903 compare = BRIG_COMPARE_LT;
2904 break;
2905 case LE_EXPR:
2906 compare = BRIG_COMPARE_LE;
2907 break;
2908 case GT_EXPR:
2909 compare = BRIG_COMPARE_GT;
2910 break;
2911 case GE_EXPR:
2912 compare = BRIG_COMPARE_GE;
2913 break;
2914 case EQ_EXPR:
2915 compare = BRIG_COMPARE_EQ;
2916 break;
2917 case NE_EXPR:
2918 compare = BRIG_COMPARE_NE;
2919 break;
2920 case UNORDERED_EXPR:
2921 compare = BRIG_COMPARE_NAN;
2922 break;
2923 case ORDERED_EXPR:
2924 compare = BRIG_COMPARE_NUM;
2925 break;
2926 case UNLT_EXPR:
2927 compare = BRIG_COMPARE_LTU;
2928 break;
2929 case UNLE_EXPR:
2930 compare = BRIG_COMPARE_LEU;
2931 break;
2932 case UNGT_EXPR:
2933 compare = BRIG_COMPARE_GTU;
2934 break;
2935 case UNGE_EXPR:
2936 compare = BRIG_COMPARE_GEU;
2937 break;
2938 case UNEQ_EXPR:
2939 compare = BRIG_COMPARE_EQU;
2940 break;
2941 case LTGT_EXPR:
2942 compare = BRIG_COMPARE_NEU;
2943 break;
2944
2945 default:
2946 HSA_SORRY_ATV (EXPR_LOCATION (lhs),
2947 "support for HSA does not implement comparison tree "
2948 "code %s\n", get_tree_code_name (code));
2949 return;
2950 }
2951
2952 /* CMP instruction returns e.g. 0xffffffff (for a 32-bit with integer)
2953 as a result of comparison. */
2954
2955 BrigType16_t dest_type = hsa_type_integer_p (dest->m_type)
2956 ? (BrigType16_t) BRIG_TYPE_B1 : dest->m_type;
2957
2958 hsa_insn_cmp *cmp = new hsa_insn_cmp (compare, dest_type);
2959 cmp->set_op (1, hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (lhs, hbb));
2960 cmp->set_op (2, hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (rhs, hbb));
2961
2962 hbb->append_insn (cmp);
2963 cmp->set_output_in_type (dest, 0, hbb);
2964}
2965
2966/* Generate an unary instruction with OPCODE and append it to a basic block
2967 HBB. The instruction uses DEST as a destination and OP1
2968 as a single operand. */
2969
2970static void
2971gen_hsa_unary_operation (BrigOpcode opcode, hsa_op_reg *dest,
2972 hsa_op_with_type *op1, hsa_bb *hbb)
2973{
2974 gcc_checking_assert (dest);
2975 hsa_insn_basic *insn;
2976
2977 if (opcode == BRIG_OPCODE_MOV && hsa_needs_cvt (dest->m_type, op1->m_type))
2978 insn = new hsa_insn_cvt (dest, op1);
2979 else if (opcode == BRIG_OPCODE_FIRSTBIT || opcode == BRIG_OPCODE_LASTBIT)
2980 {
2981 BrigType16_t srctype = hsa_type_integer_p (op1->m_type) ? op1->m_type
2982 : hsa_unsigned_type_for_type (op1->m_type);
2983 insn = new hsa_insn_srctype (2, opcode, BRIG_TYPE_U32, srctype, NULL,
2984 op1);
2985 }
2986 else
2987 {
2988 insn = new hsa_insn_basic (2, opcode, dest->m_type, dest, op1);
2989
2990 if (opcode == BRIG_OPCODE_ABS || opcode == BRIG_OPCODE_NEG)
2991 {
2992 /* ABS and NEG only exist in _s form :-/ */
2993 if (insn->m_type == BRIG_TYPE_U32)
2994 insn->m_type = BRIG_TYPE_S32;
2995 else if (insn->m_type == BRIG_TYPE_U64)
2996 insn->m_type = BRIG_TYPE_S64;
2997 }
2998 }
2999
3000 hbb->append_insn (insn);
3001
3002 if (opcode == BRIG_OPCODE_FIRSTBIT || opcode == BRIG_OPCODE_LASTBIT)
3003 insn->set_output_in_type (dest, 0, hbb);
3004}
3005
3006/* Generate a binary instruction with OPCODE and append it to a basic block
3007 HBB. The instruction uses DEST as a destination and operands OP1
3008 and OP2. */
3009
3010static void
3011gen_hsa_binary_operation (int opcode, hsa_op_reg *dest,
3012 hsa_op_base *op1, hsa_op_base *op2, hsa_bb *hbb)
3013{
3014 gcc_checking_assert (dest);
3015
3016 if ((opcode == BRIG_OPCODE_SHL || opcode == BRIG_OPCODE_SHR)
3017 && is_a <hsa_op_immed *> (op2))
3018 {
3019 hsa_op_immed *i = dyn_cast <hsa_op_immed *> (op2);
3020 i->set_type (BRIG_TYPE_U32);
3021 }
3022 if ((opcode == BRIG_OPCODE_OR
3023 || opcode == BRIG_OPCODE_XOR
3024 || opcode == BRIG_OPCODE_AND)
3025 && is_a <hsa_op_immed *> (op2))
3026 {
3027 hsa_op_immed *i = dyn_cast <hsa_op_immed *> (op2);
3028 i->set_type (hsa_unsigned_type_for_type (i->m_type));
3029 }
3030
3031 hsa_insn_basic *insn = new hsa_insn_basic (3, opcode, dest->m_type, dest,
3032 op1, op2);
3033 hbb->append_insn (insn);
3034}
3035
3036/* Generate HSA instructions for a single assignment. HBB is the basic block
3037 they will be appended to. */
3038
3039static void
3040gen_hsa_insns_for_operation_assignment (gimple *assign, hsa_bb *hbb)
3041{
3042 tree_code code = gimple_assign_rhs_code (assign);
3043 gimple_rhs_class rhs_class = get_gimple_rhs_class (gimple_expr_code (assign));
3044
3045 tree lhs = gimple_assign_lhs (assign);
3046 tree rhs1 = gimple_assign_rhs1 (assign);
3047 tree rhs2 = gimple_assign_rhs2 (assign);
3048 tree rhs3 = gimple_assign_rhs3 (assign);
3049
3050 BrigOpcode opcode;
3051
3052 switch (code)
3053 {
3054 CASE_CONVERT:
3055 case FLOAT_EXPR:
3056 /* The opcode is changed to BRIG_OPCODE_CVT if BRIG types
3057 needs a conversion. */
3058 opcode = BRIG_OPCODE_MOV;
3059 break;
3060
3061 case PLUS_EXPR:
3062 case POINTER_PLUS_EXPR:
3063 opcode = BRIG_OPCODE_ADD;
3064 break;
3065 case MINUS_EXPR:
3066 opcode = BRIG_OPCODE_SUB;
3067 break;
3068 case MULT_EXPR:
3069 opcode = BRIG_OPCODE_MUL;
3070 break;
3071 case MULT_HIGHPART_EXPR:
3072 opcode = BRIG_OPCODE_MULHI;
3073 break;
3074 case RDIV_EXPR:
3075 case TRUNC_DIV_EXPR:
3076 case EXACT_DIV_EXPR:
3077 opcode = BRIG_OPCODE_DIV;
3078 break;
3079 case CEIL_DIV_EXPR:
3080 case FLOOR_DIV_EXPR:
3081 case ROUND_DIV_EXPR:
3082 HSA_SORRY_AT (gimple_location (assign),
3083 "support for HSA does not implement CEIL_DIV_EXPR, "
3084 "FLOOR_DIV_EXPR or ROUND_DIV_EXPR");
3085 return;
3086 case TRUNC_MOD_EXPR:
3087 opcode = BRIG_OPCODE_REM;
3088 break;
3089 case CEIL_MOD_EXPR:
3090 case FLOOR_MOD_EXPR:
3091 case ROUND_MOD_EXPR:
3092 HSA_SORRY_AT (gimple_location (assign),
3093 "support for HSA does not implement CEIL_MOD_EXPR, "
3094 "FLOOR_MOD_EXPR or ROUND_MOD_EXPR");
3095 return;
3096 case NEGATE_EXPR:
3097 opcode = BRIG_OPCODE_NEG;
3098 break;
3099 case FMA_EXPR:
3100 /* There is a native HSA instruction for scalar FMAs but not for vector
3101 ones. */
3102 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (lhs)) == VECTOR_TYPE)
3103 {
3104 hsa_op_reg *dest
3105 = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (gimple_assign_lhs (assign));
3106 hsa_op_with_type *op1 = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (rhs1, hbb);
3107 hsa_op_with_type *op2 = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (rhs2, hbb);
3108 hsa_op_with_type *op3 = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (rhs3, hbb);
3109 hsa_op_reg *tmp = new hsa_op_reg (dest->m_type);
3110 gen_hsa_binary_operation (BRIG_OPCODE_MUL, tmp, op1, op2, hbb);
3111 gen_hsa_binary_operation (BRIG_OPCODE_ADD, dest, tmp, op3, hbb);
3112 return;
3113 }
3114 opcode = BRIG_OPCODE_MAD;
3115 break;
3116 case MIN_EXPR:
3117 opcode = BRIG_OPCODE_MIN;
3118 break;
3119 case MAX_EXPR:
3120 opcode = BRIG_OPCODE_MAX;
3121 break;
3122 case ABS_EXPR:
3123 opcode = BRIG_OPCODE_ABS;
3124 break;
3125 case LSHIFT_EXPR:
3126 opcode = BRIG_OPCODE_SHL;
3127 break;
3128 case RSHIFT_EXPR:
3129 opcode = BRIG_OPCODE_SHR;
3130 break;
3131 case LROTATE_EXPR:
3132 case RROTATE_EXPR:
3133 {
3134 hsa_insn_basic *insn = NULL;
3135 int code1 = code == LROTATE_EXPR ? BRIG_OPCODE_SHL : BRIG_OPCODE_SHR;
3136 int code2 = code != LROTATE_EXPR ? BRIG_OPCODE_SHL : BRIG_OPCODE_SHR;
3137 BrigType16_t btype = hsa_type_for_scalar_tree_type (TREE_TYPE (lhs),
3138 true);
3139
3140 hsa_op_with_type *src = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (rhs1, hbb);
3141 hsa_op_reg *op1 = new hsa_op_reg (btype);
3142 hsa_op_reg *op2 = new hsa_op_reg (btype);
3143 hsa_op_with_type *shift1 = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (rhs2, hbb);
3144
3145 tree type = TREE_TYPE (rhs2);
3146 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT bitsize = TREE_INT_CST_LOW (TYPE_SIZE (type));
3147
3148 hsa_op_with_type *shift2 = NULL;
3149 if (TREE_CODE (rhs2) == INTEGER_CST)
3150 shift2 = new hsa_op_immed (bitsize - tree_to_uhwi (rhs2),
3151 BRIG_TYPE_U32);
3152 else if (TREE_CODE (rhs2) == SSA_NAME)
3153 {
3154 hsa_op_reg *s = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (rhs2);
3155 hsa_op_reg *d = new hsa_op_reg (s->m_type);
3156 hsa_op_immed *size_imm = new hsa_op_immed (bitsize, BRIG_TYPE_U32);
3157
3158 insn = new hsa_insn_basic (3, BRIG_OPCODE_SUB, d->m_type,
3159 d, s, size_imm);
3160 hbb->append_insn (insn);
3161
3162 shift2 = d;
3163 }
3164 else
3165 gcc_unreachable ();
3166
3167 hsa_op_reg *dest = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (lhs);
3168 gen_hsa_binary_operation (code1, op1, src, shift1, hbb);
3169 gen_hsa_binary_operation (code2, op2, src, shift2, hbb);
3170 gen_hsa_binary_operation (BRIG_OPCODE_OR, dest, op1, op2, hbb);
3171
3172 return;
3173 }
3174 case BIT_IOR_EXPR:
3175 opcode = BRIG_OPCODE_OR;
3176 break;
3177 case BIT_XOR_EXPR:
3178 opcode = BRIG_OPCODE_XOR;
3179 break;
3180 case BIT_AND_EXPR:
3181 opcode = BRIG_OPCODE_AND;
3182 break;
3183 case BIT_NOT_EXPR:
3184 opcode = BRIG_OPCODE_NOT;
3185 break;
3186 case FIX_TRUNC_EXPR:
3187 {
3188 hsa_op_reg *dest = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (lhs);
3189 hsa_op_with_type *v = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (rhs1, hbb);
3190
3191 if (hsa_needs_cvt (dest->m_type, v->m_type))
3192 {
3193 hsa_op_reg *tmp = new hsa_op_reg (v->m_type);
3194
3195 hsa_insn_basic *insn = new hsa_insn_basic (2, BRIG_OPCODE_TRUNC,
3196 tmp->m_type, tmp, v);
3197 hbb->append_insn (insn);
3198
3199 hsa_insn_basic *cvtinsn = new hsa_insn_cvt (dest, tmp);
3200 hbb->append_insn (cvtinsn);
3201 }
3202 else
3203 {
3204 hsa_insn_basic *insn = new hsa_insn_basic (2, BRIG_OPCODE_TRUNC,
3205 dest->m_type, dest, v);
3206 hbb->append_insn (insn);
3207 }
3208
3209 return;
3210 }
3211 opcode = BRIG_OPCODE_TRUNC;
3212 break;
3213
3214 case LT_EXPR:
3215 case LE_EXPR:
3216 case GT_EXPR:
3217 case GE_EXPR:
3218 case EQ_EXPR:
3219 case NE_EXPR:
3220 case UNORDERED_EXPR:
3221 case ORDERED_EXPR:
3222 case UNLT_EXPR:
3223 case UNLE_EXPR:
3224 case UNGT_EXPR:
3225 case UNGE_EXPR:
3226 case UNEQ_EXPR:
3227 case LTGT_EXPR:
3228 {
3229 hsa_op_reg *dest
3230 = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (gimple_assign_lhs (assign));
3231
3232 gen_hsa_cmp_insn_from_gimple (code, rhs1, rhs2, dest, hbb);
3233 return;
3234 }
3235 case COND_EXPR:
3236 {
3237 hsa_op_reg *dest
3238 = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (gimple_assign_lhs (assign));
3239 hsa_op_with_type *ctrl = NULL;
3240 tree cond = rhs1;
3241
3242 if (CONSTANT_CLASS_P (cond) || TREE_CODE (cond) == SSA_NAME)
3243 ctrl = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (cond, hbb);
3244 else
3245 {
3246 hsa_op_reg *r = new hsa_op_reg (BRIG_TYPE_B1);
3247
3248 gen_hsa_cmp_insn_from_gimple (TREE_CODE (cond),
3249 TREE_OPERAND (cond, 0),
3250 TREE_OPERAND (cond, 1),
3251 r, hbb);
3252
3253 ctrl = r;
3254 }
3255
3256 hsa_op_with_type *op2 = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (rhs2, hbb);
3257 hsa_op_with_type *op3 = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (rhs3, hbb);
3258
3259 BrigType16_t utype = hsa_unsigned_type_for_type (dest->m_type);
3260 if (is_a <hsa_op_immed *> (op2))
3261 op2->m_type = utype;
3262 if (is_a <hsa_op_immed *> (op3))
3263 op3->m_type = utype;
3264
3265 hsa_insn_basic *insn
3266 = new hsa_insn_basic (4, BRIG_OPCODE_CMOV,
3267 hsa_bittype_for_type (dest->m_type),
3268 dest, ctrl, op2, op3);
3269
3270 hbb->append_insn (insn);
3271 return;
3272 }
3273 case COMPLEX_EXPR:
3274 {
3275 hsa_op_reg *dest
3276 = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (gimple_assign_lhs (assign));
3277 hsa_op_with_type *rhs1_reg = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (rhs1, hbb);
3278 hsa_op_with_type *rhs2_reg = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (rhs2, hbb);
3279
3280 if (hsa_seen_error ())
3281 return;
3282
3283 BrigType16_t src_type = hsa_bittype_for_type (rhs1_reg->m_type);
3284 rhs1_reg = rhs1_reg->get_in_type (src_type, hbb);
3285 rhs2_reg = rhs2_reg->get_in_type (src_type, hbb);
3286
3287 hsa_insn_packed *insn
3288 = new hsa_insn_packed (3, BRIG_OPCODE_COMBINE, dest->m_type, src_type,
3289 dest, rhs1_reg, rhs2_reg);
3290 hbb->append_insn (insn);
3291
3292 return;
3293 }
3294 default:
3295 /* Implement others as we come across them. */
3296 HSA_SORRY_ATV (gimple_location (assign),
3297 "support for HSA does not implement operation %s",
3298 get_tree_code_name (code));
3299 return;
3300 }
3301
3302
3303 hsa_op_reg *dest = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (gimple_assign_lhs (assign));
3304
3305 hsa_op_with_type *op1 = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (rhs1, hbb);
3306 hsa_op_with_type *op2 = rhs2 != NULL_TREE ?
3307 hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (rhs2, hbb) : NULL;
3308
3309 if (hsa_seen_error ())
3310 return;
3311
3312 switch (rhs_class)
3313 {
3314 case GIMPLE_TERNARY_RHS:
3315 {
3316 hsa_op_with_type *op3 = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (rhs3, hbb);
3317 hsa_insn_basic *insn = new hsa_insn_basic (4, opcode, dest->m_type, dest,
3318 op1, op2, op3);
3319 hbb->append_insn (insn);
3320 }
3321 return;
3322
3323 case GIMPLE_BINARY_RHS:
3324 gen_hsa_binary_operation (opcode, dest, op1, op2, hbb);
3325 break;
3326
3327 case GIMPLE_UNARY_RHS:
3328 gen_hsa_unary_operation (opcode, dest, op1, hbb);
3329 break;
3330 default:
3331 gcc_unreachable ();
3332 }
3333}
