3335/* Generate HSA instructions for a given gimple condition statement COND.
3336 Instructions will be appended to HBB, which also needs to be the
3337 corresponding structure to the basic_block of COND. */
3338
3339static void
3340gen_hsa_insns_for_cond_stmt (gimple *cond, hsa_bb *hbb)
3341{
3342 hsa_op_reg *ctrl = new hsa_op_reg (BRIG_TYPE_B1);
3343 hsa_insn_cbr *cbr;
3344
3345 gen_hsa_cmp_insn_from_gimple (gimple_cond_code (cond),
3346 gimple_cond_lhs (cond),
3347 gimple_cond_rhs (cond),
3348 ctrl, hbb);
3349
3350 cbr = new hsa_insn_cbr (ctrl);
3351 hbb->append_insn (cbr);
3352}
3353
3354/* Maximum number of elements in a jump table for an HSA SBR instruction. */
3355
3356#define HSA_MAXIMUM_SBR_LABELS 16
3357
3358/* Return lowest value of a switch S that is handled in a non-default
3359 label. */
3360
3361static tree
3362get_switch_low (gswitch *s)
3363{
3364 unsigned labels = gimple_switch_num_labels (s);
3365 gcc_checking_assert (labels >= 1);
3366
3367 return CASE_LOW (gimple_switch_label (s, 1));
3368}
3369
3370/* Return highest value of a switch S that is handled in a non-default
3371 label. */
3372
3373static tree
3374get_switch_high (gswitch *s)
3375{
3376 unsigned labels = gimple_switch_num_labels (s);
3377
3378 /* Compare last label to maximum number of labels. */
3379 tree label = gimple_switch_label (s, labels - 1);
3380 tree low = CASE_LOW (label);
3381 tree high = CASE_HIGH (label);
3382
3383 return high != NULL_TREE ? high : low;
3384}
3385
3386static tree
3387get_switch_size (gswitch *s)
3388{
3389 return int_const_binop (MINUS_EXPR, get_switch_high (s), get_switch_low (s));
3390}
3391
3392/* Generate HSA instructions for a given gimple switch.
3393 Instructions will be appended to HBB. */
3394
3395static void
3396gen_hsa_insns_for_switch_stmt (gswitch *s, hsa_bb *hbb)
3397{
3398 gimple_stmt_iterator it = gsi_for_stmt (s);
3399 gsi_prev (&it);
3400
3401 /* Create preambule that verifies that index - lowest_label >= 0. */
3402 edge e = split_block (hbb->m_bb, gsi_stmt (it));
3403 e->flags &= ~EDGE_FALLTHRU;
3404 e->flags |= EDGE_TRUE_VALUE;
3405
3406 function *func = DECL_STRUCT_FUNCTION (current_function_decl);
3407 tree index_tree = gimple_switch_index (s);
3408 tree lowest = get_switch_low (s);
3409 tree highest = get_switch_high (s);
3410
3411 hsa_op_reg *index = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (index_tree);
3412
3413 hsa_op_reg *cmp1_reg = new hsa_op_reg (BRIG_TYPE_B1);
3414 hsa_op_immed *cmp1_immed = new hsa_op_immed (lowest);
3415 hbb->append_insn (new hsa_insn_cmp (BRIG_COMPARE_GE, cmp1_reg->m_type,
3416 cmp1_reg, index, cmp1_immed));
3417
3418 hsa_op_reg *cmp2_reg = new hsa_op_reg (BRIG_TYPE_B1);
3419 hsa_op_immed *cmp2_immed = new hsa_op_immed (highest);
3420 hbb->append_insn (new hsa_insn_cmp (BRIG_COMPARE_LE, cmp2_reg->m_type,
3421 cmp2_reg, index, cmp2_immed));
3422
3423 hsa_op_reg *cmp_reg = new hsa_op_reg (BRIG_TYPE_B1);
3424 hbb->append_insn (new hsa_insn_basic (3, BRIG_OPCODE_AND, cmp_reg->m_type,
3425 cmp_reg, cmp1_reg, cmp2_reg));
3426
3427 hbb->append_insn (new hsa_insn_cbr (cmp_reg));
3428
3429 tree default_label = gimple_switch_default_label (s);
3430 basic_block default_label_bb = label_to_block_fn (func,
3431 CASE_LABEL (default_label));
3432
3433 if (!gimple_seq_empty_p (phi_nodes (default_label_bb)))
3434 {
3435 default_label_bb = split_edge (find_edge (e->dest, default_label_bb));
3436 hsa_init_new_bb (default_label_bb);
3437 }
3438
3439 make_edge (e->src, default_label_bb, EDGE_FALSE_VALUE);
3440
3441 hsa_cfun->m_modified_cfg = true;
3442
3443 /* Basic block with the SBR instruction. */
3444 hbb = hsa_init_new_bb (e->dest);
3445
3446 hsa_op_reg *sub_index = new hsa_op_reg (index->m_type);
3447 hbb->append_insn (new hsa_insn_basic (3, BRIG_OPCODE_SUB, sub_index->m_type,
3448 sub_index, index,
3449 new hsa_op_immed (lowest)));
3450
3451 hsa_op_base *tmp = sub_index->get_in_type (BRIG_TYPE_U64, hbb);
3452 sub_index = as_a <hsa_op_reg *> (tmp);
3453 unsigned labels = gimple_switch_num_labels (s);
3454 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT size = tree_to_uhwi (get_switch_size (s));
3455
3456 hsa_insn_sbr *sbr = new hsa_insn_sbr (sub_index, size + 1);
3457
3458 /* Prepare array with default label destination. */
3459 for (unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT i = 0; i <= size; i++)
3460 sbr->m_jump_table.safe_push (default_label_bb);
3461
3462 /* Iterate all labels and fill up the jump table. */
3463 for (unsigned i = 1; i < labels; i++)
3464 {
3465 tree label = gimple_switch_label (s, i);
3466 basic_block bb = label_to_block_fn (func, CASE_LABEL (label));
3467
3468 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT sub_low
3469 = tree_to_uhwi (int_const_binop (MINUS_EXPR, CASE_LOW (label), lowest));
3470
3471 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT sub_high = sub_low;
3472 tree high = CASE_HIGH (label);
3473 if (high != NULL)
3474 sub_high = tree_to_uhwi (int_const_binop (MINUS_EXPR, high, lowest));
3475
3476 for (unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT j = sub_low; j <= sub_high; j++)
3477 sbr->m_jump_table[j] = bb;
3478 }
3479
3480 hbb->append_insn (sbr);
3481}

3483/* Verify that the function DECL can be handled by HSA. */
3484
3485static void
3486verify_function_arguments (tree decl)
3487{
3488 tree type = TREE_TYPE (decl);
3489 if (DECL_STATIC_CHAIN (decl))
3490 {
3491 HSA_SORRY_ATV (EXPR_LOCATION (decl),
3492 "HSA does not support nested functions: %D", decl);
3493 return;
3494 }
3495 else if (!TYPE_ARG_TYPES (type) || stdarg_p (type))
3496 {
3497 HSA_SORRY_ATV (EXPR_LOCATION (decl),
3498 "HSA does not support functions with variadic arguments "
3499 "(or unknown return type): %D", decl);
3500 return;
3501 }
3502}
3503
3504/* Return BRIG type for FORMAL_ARG_TYPE. If the formal argument type is NULL,
3505 return ACTUAL_ARG_TYPE. */
3506
3507static BrigType16_t
3508get_format_argument_type (tree formal_arg_type, BrigType16_t actual_arg_type)
3509{
3510 if (formal_arg_type == NULL)
3511 return actual_arg_type;
3512
3513 BrigType16_t decl_type
3514 = hsa_type_for_scalar_tree_type (formal_arg_type, false);
3515 return mem_type_for_type (decl_type);
3516}
3517
3518/* Generate HSA instructions for a direct call instruction.
3519 Instructions will be appended to HBB, which also needs to be the
3520 corresponding structure to the basic_block of STMT.
3521 If ASSIGN_LHS is false, do not copy HSA function result argument into the
3522 corresponding HSA representation of the gimple statement LHS. */
3523
3524static void
3525gen_hsa_insns_for_direct_call (gimple *stmt, hsa_bb *hbb,
3526 bool assign_lhs = true)
3527{
3528 tree decl = gimple_call_fndecl (stmt);
3529 verify_function_arguments (decl);
3530 if (hsa_seen_error ())
3531 return;
3532
3533 hsa_insn_call *call_insn = new hsa_insn_call (decl);
3534 hsa_cfun->m_called_functions.safe_push (call_insn->m_called_function);
3535
3536 /* Argument block start. */
3537 hsa_insn_arg_block *arg_start
3538 = new hsa_insn_arg_block (BRIG_KIND_DIRECTIVE_ARG_BLOCK_START, call_insn);
3539 hbb->append_insn (arg_start);
3540
3541 tree parm_type_chain = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (gimple_call_fntype (stmt));
3542
3543 /* Preparation of arguments that will be passed to function. */
3544 const unsigned args = gimple_call_num_args (stmt);
3545 for (unsigned i = 0; i < args; ++i)
3546 {
3547 tree parm = gimple_call_arg (stmt, (int)i);
3548 tree parm_decl_type = parm_type_chain != NULL_TREE
3549 ? TREE_VALUE (parm_type_chain) : NULL_TREE;
3550 hsa_op_address *addr;
3551
3552 if (AGGREGATE_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (parm)))
3553 {
3554 addr = gen_hsa_addr_for_arg (TREE_TYPE (parm), i);
3555 BrigAlignment8_t align;
3556 hsa_op_address *src = gen_hsa_addr_with_align (parm, hbb, &align);
3557 gen_hsa_memory_copy (hbb, addr, src,
3558 addr->m_symbol->total_byte_size (), align);
3559 }
3560 else
3561 {
3562 hsa_op_with_type *src = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (parm, hbb);
3563
3564 if (parm_decl_type != NULL && AGGREGATE_TYPE_P (parm_decl_type))
3565 {
3566 HSA_SORRY_AT (gimple_location (stmt),
3567 "support for HSA does not implement an aggregate "
3568 "formal argument in a function call, while actual "
3569 "argument is not an aggregate");
3570 return;
3571 }
3572
3573 BrigType16_t formal_arg_type
3574 = get_format_argument_type (parm_decl_type, src->m_type);
3575 if (hsa_seen_error ())
3576 return;
3577
3578 if (src->m_type != formal_arg_type)
3579 src = src->get_in_type (formal_arg_type, hbb);
3580
3581 addr
3582 = gen_hsa_addr_for_arg (parm_decl_type != NULL_TREE ?
3583 parm_decl_type: TREE_TYPE (parm), i);
3584 hsa_insn_mem *mem = new hsa_insn_mem (BRIG_OPCODE_ST, formal_arg_type,
3585 src, addr);
3586
3587 hbb->append_insn (mem);
3588 }
3589
3590 call_insn->m_input_args.safe_push (addr->m_symbol);
3591 if (parm_type_chain)
3592 parm_type_chain = TREE_CHAIN (parm_type_chain);
3593 }
3594
3595 call_insn->m_args_code_list = new hsa_op_code_list (args);
3596 hbb->append_insn (call_insn);
3597
3598 tree result_type = TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (decl));
3599
3600 tree result = gimple_call_lhs (stmt);
3601 hsa_insn_mem *result_insn = NULL;
3602 if (!VOID_TYPE_P (result_type))
3603 {
3604 hsa_op_address *addr = gen_hsa_addr_for_arg (result_type, -1);
3605
3606 /* Even if result of a function call is unused, we have to emit
3607 declaration for the result. */
3608 if (result && assign_lhs)
3609 {
3610 tree lhs_type = TREE_TYPE (result);
3611
3612 if (hsa_seen_error ())
3613 return;
3614
3615 if (AGGREGATE_TYPE_P (lhs_type))
3616 {
3617 BrigAlignment8_t align;
3618 hsa_op_address *result_addr
3619 = gen_hsa_addr_with_align (result, hbb, &align);
3620 gen_hsa_memory_copy (hbb, result_addr, addr,
3621 addr->m_symbol->total_byte_size (), align);
3622 }
3623 else
3624 {
3625 BrigType16_t mtype
3626 = mem_type_for_type (hsa_type_for_scalar_tree_type (lhs_type,
3627 false));
3628
3629 hsa_op_reg *dst = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (result);
3630 result_insn = new hsa_insn_mem (BRIG_OPCODE_LD, mtype, dst, addr);
3631 hbb->append_insn (result_insn);
3632 }
3633 }
3634
3635 call_insn->m_output_arg = addr->m_symbol;
3636 call_insn->m_result_code_list = new hsa_op_code_list (1);
3637 }
3638 else
3639 {
3640 if (result)
3641 {
3642 HSA_SORRY_AT (gimple_location (stmt),
3643 "support for HSA does not implement an assignment of "
3644 "return value from a void function");
3645 return;
3646 }
3647
3648 call_insn->m_result_code_list = new hsa_op_code_list (0);
3649 }
3650
3651 /* Argument block end. */
3652 hsa_insn_arg_block *arg_end
3653 = new hsa_insn_arg_block (BRIG_KIND_DIRECTIVE_ARG_BLOCK_END, call_insn);
3654 hbb->append_insn (arg_end);
3655}
3656
3657/* Generate HSA instructions for a direct call of an internal fn.
3658 Instructions will be appended to HBB, which also needs to be the
3659 corresponding structure to the basic_block of STMT. */
3660
3661static void
3662gen_hsa_insns_for_call_of_internal_fn (gimple *stmt, hsa_bb *hbb)
3663{
3664 tree lhs = gimple_call_lhs (stmt);
3665 if (!lhs)
3666 return;
3667
3668 tree lhs_type = TREE_TYPE (lhs);
3669 tree rhs1 = gimple_call_arg (stmt, 0);
3670 tree rhs1_type = TREE_TYPE (rhs1);
3671 enum internal_fn fn = gimple_call_internal_fn (stmt);
3672 hsa_internal_fn *ifn
3673 = new hsa_internal_fn (fn, tree_to_uhwi (TYPE_SIZE (rhs1_type)));
3674 hsa_insn_call *call_insn = new hsa_insn_call (ifn);
3675
3676 gcc_checking_assert (FLOAT_TYPE_P (rhs1_type));
3677
3678 if (!hsa_emitted_internal_decls->find (call_insn->m_called_internal_fn))
3679 hsa_cfun->m_called_internal_fns.safe_push (call_insn->m_called_internal_fn);
3680
3681 hsa_insn_arg_block *arg_start
3682 = new hsa_insn_arg_block (BRIG_KIND_DIRECTIVE_ARG_BLOCK_START, call_insn);
3683 hbb->append_insn (arg_start);
3684
3685 unsigned num_args = gimple_call_num_args (stmt);
3686
3687 /* Function arguments. */
3688 for (unsigned i = 0; i < num_args; i++)
3689 {
3690 tree parm = gimple_call_arg (stmt, (int)i);
3691 hsa_op_with_type *src = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (parm, hbb);
3692
3693 hsa_op_address *addr = gen_hsa_addr_for_arg (TREE_TYPE (parm), i);
3694 hsa_insn_mem *mem = new hsa_insn_mem (BRIG_OPCODE_ST, src->m_type,
3695 src, addr);
3696
3697 call_insn->m_input_args.safe_push (addr->m_symbol);
3698 hbb->append_insn (mem);
3699 }
3700
3701 call_insn->m_args_code_list = new hsa_op_code_list (num_args);
3702 hbb->append_insn (call_insn);
3703
3704 /* Assign returned value. */
3705 hsa_op_address *addr = gen_hsa_addr_for_arg (lhs_type, -1);
3706
3707 call_insn->m_output_arg = addr->m_symbol;
3708 call_insn->m_result_code_list = new hsa_op_code_list (1);
3709
3710 /* Argument block end. */
3711 hsa_insn_arg_block *arg_end
3712 = new hsa_insn_arg_block (BRIG_KIND_DIRECTIVE_ARG_BLOCK_END, call_insn);
3713 hbb->append_insn (arg_end);
3714}
3715
3716/* Generate HSA instructions for a return value instruction.
3717 Instructions will be appended to HBB, which also needs to be the
3718 corresponding structure to the basic_block of STMT. */
3719
3720static void
3721gen_hsa_insns_for_return (greturn *stmt, hsa_bb *hbb)
3722{
3723 tree retval = gimple_return_retval (stmt);
3724 if (retval)
3725 {
3726 hsa_op_address *addr = new hsa_op_address (hsa_cfun->m_output_arg);
3727
3728 if (AGGREGATE_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (retval)))
3729 {
3730 BrigAlignment8_t align;
3731 hsa_op_address *retval_addr = gen_hsa_addr_with_align (retval, hbb,
3732 &align);
3733 gen_hsa_memory_copy (hbb, addr, retval_addr,
3734 hsa_cfun->m_output_arg->total_byte_size (),
3735 align);
3736 }
3737 else
3738 {
3739 BrigType16_t t = hsa_type_for_scalar_tree_type (TREE_TYPE (retval),
3740 false);
3741 BrigType16_t mtype = mem_type_for_type (t);
3742
3743 /* Store of return value. */
3744 hsa_op_with_type *src = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (retval, hbb);
3745 src = src->get_in_type (mtype, hbb);
3746 hsa_insn_mem *mem = new hsa_insn_mem (BRIG_OPCODE_ST, mtype, src,
3747 addr);
3748 hbb->append_insn (mem);
3749 }
3750 }
3751
3752 /* HSAIL return instruction emission. */
3753 hsa_insn_basic *ret = new hsa_insn_basic (0, BRIG_OPCODE_RET);
3754 hbb->append_insn (ret);
3755}
3756
3757/* Set OP_INDEX-th operand of the instruction to DEST, as the DEST
3758 can have a different type, conversion instructions are possibly
3759 appended to HBB. */
3760
3761void
3762hsa_insn_basic::set_output_in_type (hsa_op_reg *dest, unsigned op_index,
3763 hsa_bb *hbb)
3764{
3765 hsa_insn_basic *insn;
3766 gcc_checking_assert (op_output_p (op_index));
3767
3768 if (dest->m_type == m_type)
3769 {
3770 set_op (op_index, dest);
3771 return;
3772 }
3773
3774 hsa_op_reg *tmp = new hsa_op_reg (m_type);
3775 set_op (op_index, tmp);
3776
3777 if (hsa_needs_cvt (dest->m_type, m_type))
3778 insn = new hsa_insn_cvt (dest, tmp);
3779 else
3780 insn = new hsa_insn_basic (2, BRIG_OPCODE_MOV, dest->m_type,
3781 dest, tmp->get_in_type (dest->m_type, hbb));
3782
3783 hbb->append_insn (insn);
3784}

3788 HBB. */

3791query_hsa_grid_dim (hsa_op_reg *dest, int opcode, hsa_op_immed *dimension,
3792 hsa_bb *hbb)

3797 insn->set_output_in_type (dest, 0, hbb);
3798}

3800/* Generate instruction OPCODE to query a property of HSA grid along the given
3801 dimension which is an immediate in first argument of STMT. Store result
3802 into the register corresponding to LHS of STMT and append the instruction to
3803 HBB. */
3804
3805static void
3806query_hsa_grid_dim (gimple *stmt, int opcode, hsa_bb *hbb)
3807{
3808 tree lhs = gimple_call_lhs (dyn_cast <gcall *> (stmt));
3809 if (lhs == NULL_TREE)
3810 return;
3811
3812 tree arg = gimple_call_arg (stmt, 0);
3813 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT dim = 5;
3814 if (tree_fits_uhwi_p (arg))
3815 dim = tree_to_uhwi (arg);
3816 if (dim > 2)
3817 {
3818 HSA_SORRY_AT (gimple_location (stmt),
3819 "HSA grid query dimension must be immediate constant 0, 1 "
3820 "or 2");
3821 return;
3822 }
3823
3824 hsa_op_immed *hdim = new hsa_op_immed (dim, (BrigKind16_t) BRIG_TYPE_U32);
3825 hsa_op_reg *dest = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (lhs);
3826 query_hsa_grid_dim (dest, opcode, hdim, hbb);
3827}

3833static void
3834query_hsa_grid_nodim (gimple *stmt, BrigOpcode16_t opcode, hsa_bb *hbb)

3840 BrigType16_t brig_type = hsa_unsigned_type_for_type (dest->m_type);
3841 hsa_insn_basic *insn = new hsa_insn_basic (1, opcode, brig_type, dest);
3842 hbb->append_insn (insn);
3843}

3862/* Return byte offset of a FIELD_NAME in GOMP_hsa_kernel_dispatch which
3863 is defined in plugin-hsa.c. */
3864
3865static HOST_WIDE_INT
3866get_hsa_kernel_dispatch_offset (const char *field_name)
3867{
3868 tree *hsa_kernel_dispatch_type = hsa_get_kernel_dispatch_type ();
3869 if (*hsa_kernel_dispatch_type == NULL)
3870 {
3871 /* Collection of information needed for a dispatch of a kernel from a
3872 kernel. Keep in sync with libgomp's plugin-hsa.c. */
3873
3874 *hsa_kernel_dispatch_type = make_node (RECORD_TYPE);
3875 tree id_f1 = build_decl (BUILTINS_LOCATION, FIELD_DECL,
3876 get_identifier ("queue"), ptr_type_node);
3877 DECL_CHAIN (id_f1) = NULL_TREE;
3878 tree id_f2 = build_decl (BUILTINS_LOCATION, FIELD_DECL,
3879 get_identifier ("omp_data_memory"),
3880 ptr_type_node);
3881 DECL_CHAIN (id_f2) = id_f1;
3882 tree id_f3 = build_decl (BUILTINS_LOCATION, FIELD_DECL,
3883 get_identifier ("kernarg_address"),
3884 ptr_type_node);
3885 DECL_CHAIN (id_f3) = id_f2;
3886 tree id_f4 = build_decl (BUILTINS_LOCATION, FIELD_DECL,
3887 get_identifier ("object"),
3888 uint64_type_node);
3889 DECL_CHAIN (id_f4) = id_f3;
3890 tree id_f5 = build_decl (BUILTINS_LOCATION, FIELD_DECL,
3891 get_identifier ("signal"),
3892 uint64_type_node);
3893 DECL_CHAIN (id_f5) = id_f4;
3894 tree id_f6 = build_decl (BUILTINS_LOCATION, FIELD_DECL,
3895 get_identifier ("private_segment_size"),
3896 uint32_type_node);
3897 DECL_CHAIN (id_f6) = id_f5;
3898 tree id_f7 = build_decl (BUILTINS_LOCATION, FIELD_DECL,
3899 get_identifier ("group_segment_size"),
3900 uint32_type_node);
3901 DECL_CHAIN (id_f7) = id_f6;
3902 tree id_f8 = build_decl (BUILTINS_LOCATION, FIELD_DECL,
3903 get_identifier ("kernel_dispatch_count"),
3904 uint64_type_node);
3905 DECL_CHAIN (id_f8) = id_f7;
3906 tree id_f9 = build_decl (BUILTINS_LOCATION, FIELD_DECL,
3907 get_identifier ("debug"),
3908 uint64_type_node);
3909 DECL_CHAIN (id_f9) = id_f8;
3910 tree id_f10 = build_decl (BUILTINS_LOCATION, FIELD_DECL,
3911 get_identifier ("omp_level"),
3912 uint64_type_node);
3913 DECL_CHAIN (id_f10) = id_f9;
3914 tree id_f11 = build_decl (BUILTINS_LOCATION, FIELD_DECL,
3915 get_identifier ("children_dispatches"),
3916 ptr_type_node);
3917 DECL_CHAIN (id_f11) = id_f10;
3918 tree id_f12 = build_decl (BUILTINS_LOCATION, FIELD_DECL,
3919 get_identifier ("omp_num_threads"),
3920 uint32_type_node);
3921 DECL_CHAIN (id_f12) = id_f11;
3922
3923
3924 finish_builtin_struct (*hsa_kernel_dispatch_type, "__hsa_kernel_dispatch",
3925 id_f12, NULL_TREE);
3926 TYPE_ARTIFICIAL (*hsa_kernel_dispatch_type) = 1;
3927 }
3928
3929 for (tree chain = TYPE_FIELDS (*hsa_kernel_dispatch_type);
3930 chain != NULL_TREE; chain = TREE_CHAIN (chain))
3931 if (strcmp (field_name, IDENTIFIER_POINTER (DECL_NAME (chain))) == 0)
3932 return int_byte_position (chain);
3933
3934 gcc_unreachable ();
3935}
3936
3937/* Return an HSA register that will contain number of threads for
3938 a future dispatched kernel. Instructions are added to HBB. */
3939
3940static hsa_op_reg *
3941gen_num_threads_for_dispatch (hsa_bb *hbb)
3942{
3943 /* Step 1) Assign to number of threads:
3944 MIN (HSA_DEFAULT_NUM_THREADS, hsa_num_threads). */
3945 hsa_op_reg *threads = new hsa_op_reg (hsa_num_threads->m_type);
3946 hsa_op_address *addr = new hsa_op_address (hsa_num_threads);
3947
3948 hbb->append_insn (new hsa_insn_mem (BRIG_OPCODE_LD, threads->m_type,
3949 threads, addr));
3950
3951 hsa_op_immed *limit = new hsa_op_immed (HSA_DEFAULT_NUM_THREADS,
3952 BRIG_TYPE_U32);
3953 hsa_op_reg *r = new hsa_op_reg (BRIG_TYPE_B1);
3954 hsa_insn_cmp * cmp
3955 = new hsa_insn_cmp (BRIG_COMPARE_LT, r->m_type, r, threads, limit);
3956 hbb->append_insn (cmp);
3957
3958 BrigType16_t btype = hsa_bittype_for_type (threads->m_type);
3959 hsa_op_reg *tmp = new hsa_op_reg (threads->m_type);
3960
3961 hbb->append_insn (new hsa_insn_basic (4, BRIG_OPCODE_CMOV, btype, tmp, r,
3962 threads, limit));
3963
3964 /* Step 2) If the number is equal to zero,
3965 return shadow->omp_num_threads. */
3966 hsa_op_reg *shadow_reg_ptr = hsa_cfun->get_shadow_reg ();
3967
3968 hsa_op_reg *shadow_thread_count = new hsa_op_reg (BRIG_TYPE_U32);
3969 addr
3970 = new hsa_op_address (shadow_reg_ptr,
3971 get_hsa_kernel_dispatch_offset ("omp_num_threads"));
3972 hsa_insn_basic *basic
3973 = new hsa_insn_mem (BRIG_OPCODE_LD, shadow_thread_count->m_type,
3974 shadow_thread_count, addr);
3975 hbb->append_insn (basic);
3976
3977 hsa_op_reg *tmp2 = new hsa_op_reg (threads->m_type);
3978 r = new hsa_op_reg (BRIG_TYPE_B1);
3979 hsa_op_immed *imm = new hsa_op_immed (0, shadow_thread_count->m_type);
3980 hbb->append_insn (new hsa_insn_cmp (BRIG_COMPARE_EQ, r->m_type, r, tmp, imm));
3981 hbb->append_insn (new hsa_insn_basic (4, BRIG_OPCODE_CMOV, btype, tmp2, r,
3982 shadow_thread_count, tmp));
3983
3984 hsa_op_base *dest = tmp2->get_in_type (BRIG_TYPE_U16, hbb);
3985
3986 return as_a <hsa_op_reg *> (dest);
3987}

3989/* Build OPCODE query for all three hsa dimensions, multiply them and store the
3990 result into DEST. */
3991
3992static void
3993multiply_grid_dim_characteristics (hsa_op_reg *dest, int opcode, hsa_bb *hbb)
3994{
3995 hsa_op_reg *dimx = new hsa_op_reg (BRIG_TYPE_U32);
3996 query_hsa_grid_dim (dimx, opcode,
3997 new hsa_op_immed (0, (BrigKind16_t) BRIG_TYPE_U32), hbb);
3998 hsa_op_reg *dimy = new hsa_op_reg (BRIG_TYPE_U32);
3999 query_hsa_grid_dim (dimy, opcode,
4000 new hsa_op_immed (1, (BrigKind16_t) BRIG_TYPE_U32), hbb);
4001 hsa_op_reg *dimz = new hsa_op_reg (BRIG_TYPE_U32);
4002 query_hsa_grid_dim (dimz, opcode,
4003 new hsa_op_immed (2, (BrigKind16_t) BRIG_TYPE_U32), hbb);
4004 hsa_op_reg *tmp = new hsa_op_reg (dest->m_type);
4005 gen_hsa_binary_operation (BRIG_OPCODE_MUL, tmp,
4006 dimx->get_in_type (dest->m_type, hbb),
4007 dimy->get_in_type (dest->m_type, hbb), hbb);
4008 gen_hsa_binary_operation (BRIG_OPCODE_MUL, dest, tmp,
4009 dimz->get_in_type (dest->m_type, hbb), hbb);
4010}

4141/* Emit instructions that implement alloca builtin gimple STMT.
4142 Instructions are appended to basic block HBB. */
4143
4144static void
4145gen_hsa_alloca (gcall *call, hsa_bb *hbb)
4146{
4147 tree lhs = gimple_call_lhs (call);
4148 if (lhs == NULL_TREE)
4149 return;
4150
4151 built_in_function fn = DECL_FUNCTION_CODE (gimple_call_fndecl (call));
4152
4153 gcc_checking_assert (fn == BUILT_IN_ALLOCA
4154 || fn == BUILT_IN_ALLOCA_WITH_ALIGN);
4155
4156 unsigned bit_alignment = 0;
4157
4158 if (fn == BUILT_IN_ALLOCA_WITH_ALIGN)
4159 {
4160 tree alignment_tree = gimple_call_arg (call, 1);
4161 if (TREE_CODE (alignment_tree) != INTEGER_CST)
4162 {
4163 HSA_SORRY_ATV (gimple_location (call),
4164 "support for HSA does not implement "
4165 "__builtin_alloca_with_align with a non-constant "
4166 "alignment: %E", alignment_tree);
4167 }
4168
4169 bit_alignment = tree_to_uhwi (alignment_tree);
4170 }
4171
4172 tree rhs1 = gimple_call_arg (call, 0);
4173 hsa_op_with_type *size = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (rhs1, hbb)
4174 ->get_in_type (BRIG_TYPE_U32, hbb);
4175 hsa_op_with_type *dest = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (lhs);
4176
4177 hsa_op_reg *tmp
4178 = new hsa_op_reg (hsa_get_segment_addr_type (BRIG_SEGMENT_PRIVATE));
4179 hsa_insn_alloca *a = new hsa_insn_alloca (tmp, size, bit_alignment);
4180 hbb->append_insn (a);
4181
4182 hsa_insn_seg *seg
4183 = new hsa_insn_seg (BRIG_OPCODE_STOF,
4184 hsa_get_segment_addr_type (BRIG_SEGMENT_FLAT),
4185 tmp->m_type, BRIG_SEGMENT_PRIVATE, dest, tmp);
4186 hbb->append_insn (seg);
4187}

4189/* Emit instructions that implement clrsb builtin STMT:
4190 Returns the number of leading redundant sign bits in x, i.e. the number
4191 of bits following the most significant bit that are identical to it.
4192 There are no special cases for 0 or other values.
4193 Instructions are appended to basic block HBB. */
4194
4195static void
4196gen_hsa_clrsb (gcall *call, hsa_bb *hbb)
4197{
4198 tree lhs = gimple_call_lhs (call);
4199 if (lhs == NULL_TREE)
4200 return;
4201
4202 hsa_op_reg *dest = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (lhs);
4203 tree rhs1 = gimple_call_arg (call, 0);
4204 hsa_op_with_type *arg = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (rhs1, hbb);
4205 BrigType16_t bittype = hsa_bittype_for_type (arg->m_type);
4206 unsigned bitsize = tree_to_uhwi (TYPE_SIZE (TREE_TYPE (rhs1)));
4207
4208 /* FIRSTBIT instruction is defined just for 32 and 64-bits wide integers. */
4209 gcc_checking_assert (bitsize == 32 || bitsize == 64);
4210
4211 /* Set true to MOST_SIG if the most significant bit is set to one. */
4212 hsa_op_immed *c = new hsa_op_immed (1ul << (bitsize - 1),
4213 hsa_uint_for_bitsize (bitsize));
4214
4215 hsa_op_reg *and_reg = new hsa_op_reg (bittype);
4216 gen_hsa_binary_operation (BRIG_OPCODE_AND, and_reg, arg, c, hbb);
4217
4218 hsa_op_reg *most_sign = new hsa_op_reg (BRIG_TYPE_B1);
4219 hsa_insn_cmp *cmp
4220 = new hsa_insn_cmp (BRIG_COMPARE_EQ, most_sign->m_type, most_sign,
4221 and_reg, c);
4222 hbb->append_insn (cmp);
4223
4224 /* If the most significant bit is one, negate the input. Otherwise
4225 shift the input value to left by one bit. */
4226 hsa_op_reg *arg_neg = new hsa_op_reg (arg->m_type);
4227 gen_hsa_unary_operation (BRIG_OPCODE_NEG, arg_neg, arg, hbb);
4228
4229 hsa_op_reg *shifted_arg = new hsa_op_reg (arg->m_type);
4230 gen_hsa_binary_operation (BRIG_OPCODE_SHL, shifted_arg, arg,
4231 new hsa_op_immed (1, BRIG_TYPE_U64), hbb);
4232
4233 /* Assign the value that can be used for FIRSTBIT instruction according
4234 to the most significant bit. */
4235 hsa_op_reg *tmp = new hsa_op_reg (bittype);
4236 hsa_insn_basic *cmov
4237 = new hsa_insn_basic (4, BRIG_OPCODE_CMOV, bittype, tmp, most_sign,
4238 arg_neg, shifted_arg);
4239 hbb->append_insn (cmov);
4240
4241 hsa_op_reg *leading_bits = new hsa_op_reg (BRIG_TYPE_S32);
4242 gen_hsa_unary_operation (BRIG_OPCODE_FIRSTBIT, leading_bits,
4243 tmp->get_in_type (hsa_uint_for_bitsize (bitsize),
4244 hbb), hbb);
4245
4246 /* Set flag if the input value is equal to zero. */
4247 hsa_op_reg *is_zero = new hsa_op_reg (BRIG_TYPE_B1);
4248 cmp = new hsa_insn_cmp (BRIG_COMPARE_EQ, is_zero->m_type, is_zero, arg,
4249 new hsa_op_immed (0, arg->m_type));
4250 hbb->append_insn (cmp);
4251
4252 /* Return the number of leading bits,
4253 or (bitsize - 1) if the input value is zero. */
4254 cmov = new hsa_insn_basic (4, BRIG_OPCODE_CMOV, BRIG_TYPE_B32, NULL, is_zero,
4255 new hsa_op_immed (bitsize - 1, BRIG_TYPE_U32),
4256 leading_bits->get_in_type (BRIG_TYPE_B32, hbb));
4257 hbb->append_insn (cmov);
4258 cmov->set_output_in_type (dest, 0, hbb);
4259}

4261/* Emit instructions that implement ffs builtin STMT:
4262 Returns one plus the index of the least significant 1-bit of x,
4263 or if x is zero, returns zero.
4264 Instructions are appended to basic block HBB. */
4265
4266static void
4267gen_hsa_ffs (gcall *call, hsa_bb *hbb)
4268{
4269 tree lhs = gimple_call_lhs (call);
4270 if (lhs == NULL_TREE)
4271 return;
4272
4273 hsa_op_reg *dest = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (lhs);
4274
4275 tree rhs1 = gimple_call_arg (call, 0);
4276 hsa_op_with_type *arg = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (rhs1, hbb);
4277
4278 hsa_op_reg *tmp = new hsa_op_reg (BRIG_TYPE_U32);
4279 hsa_insn_srctype *insn = new hsa_insn_srctype (2, BRIG_OPCODE_LASTBIT,
4280 tmp->m_type, arg->m_type,
4281 tmp, arg);
4282 hbb->append_insn (insn);
4283
4284 hsa_insn_basic *addition
4285 = new hsa_insn_basic (3, BRIG_OPCODE_ADD, tmp->m_type, NULL, tmp,
4286 new hsa_op_immed (1, tmp->m_type));
4287 hbb->append_insn (addition);
4288 addition->set_output_in_type (dest, 0, hbb);
4289}

4291static void
4292gen_hsa_popcount_to_dest (hsa_op_reg *dest, hsa_op_with_type *arg, hsa_bb *hbb)
4293{
4294 gcc_checking_assert (hsa_type_integer_p (arg->m_type));
4295
4296 if (hsa_type_bit_size (arg->m_type) < 32)
4297 arg = arg->get_in_type (BRIG_TYPE_B32, hbb);
4298
4299 BrigType16_t srctype = hsa_bittype_for_type (arg->m_type);
4300 if (!hsa_btype_p (arg->m_type))
4301 arg = arg->get_in_type (srctype, hbb);
4302
4303 hsa_insn_srctype *popcount
4304 = new hsa_insn_srctype (2, BRIG_OPCODE_POPCOUNT, BRIG_TYPE_U32,

4306 hbb->append_insn (popcount);
4307 popcount->set_output_in_type (dest, 0, hbb);

4352/* Emit instructions that implement DIVMOD builtin STMT.
4353 Instructions are appended to basic block HBB. */
4354
4355static void
4356gen_hsa_divmod (gcall *call, hsa_bb *hbb)
4357{
4358 tree lhs = gimple_call_lhs (call);
4359 if (lhs == NULL_TREE)
4360 return;
4361
4362 tree rhs0 = gimple_call_arg (call, 0);
4363 tree rhs1 = gimple_call_arg (call, 1);
4364
4365 hsa_op_with_type *arg0 = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (rhs0, hbb);
4366 hsa_op_with_type *arg1 = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (rhs1, hbb);
4367
4368 hsa_op_reg *dest0 = new hsa_op_reg (arg0->m_type);
4369 hsa_op_reg *dest1 = new hsa_op_reg (arg1->m_type);
4370
4371 hsa_insn_basic *insn = new hsa_insn_basic (3, BRIG_OPCODE_DIV, dest0->m_type,
4372 dest0, arg0, arg1);
4373 hbb->append_insn (insn);
4374 insn = new hsa_insn_basic (3, BRIG_OPCODE_REM, dest1->m_type, dest1, arg0,
4375 arg1);
4376 hbb->append_insn (insn);
4377
4378 hsa_op_reg *dest = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (lhs);
4379 BrigType16_t src_type = hsa_bittype_for_type (dest0->m_type);
4380
4381 insn = new hsa_insn_packed (3, BRIG_OPCODE_COMBINE, dest->m_type,
4382 src_type, dest, dest0, dest1);
4383 hbb->append_insn (insn);
4384}

4404void
4405omp_simple_builtin::generate (gimple *stmt, hsa_bb *hbb)
4406{
4407 if (m_sorry)
4408 {
4409 if (m_warning_message)
4410 HSA_SORRY_AT (gimple_location (stmt), m_warning_message);
4411 else
4412 HSA_SORRY_ATV (gimple_location (stmt),
4413 "Support for HSA does not implement calls to %s\n",
4414 m_name);
4415 }
4416 else if (m_warning_message != NULL)
4417 warning_at (gimple_location (stmt), OPT_Whsa, m_warning_message);
4418
4419 if (m_return_value != NULL)
4420 {
4421 tree lhs = gimple_call_lhs (stmt);
4422 if (!lhs)
4423 return;
4424
4425 hbb->append_insn (new hsa_insn_comment (m_name));
4426
4427 hsa_op_reg *dest = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (lhs);
4428 hsa_op_with_type *op = m_return_value->get_in_type (dest->m_type, hbb);
4429 hsa_build_append_simple_mov (dest, op, hbb);
4430 }
4431}

4433/* If STMT is a call of a known library function, generate code to perform
4434 it and return true. */
4435
4436static bool
4437gen_hsa_insns_for_known_library_call (gimple *stmt, hsa_bb *hbb)
4438{
4439 bool handled = false;
4440 const char *name = hsa_get_declaration_name (gimple_call_fndecl (stmt));
4441
4442 char *copy = NULL;
4443 size_t len = strlen (name);
4444 if (len > 0 && name[len - 1] == '_')
4445 {
4446 copy = XNEWVEC (char, len + 1);
4447 strcpy (copy, name);
4448 copy[len - 1] = '\0';
4449 name = copy;
4450 }
4451
4452 /* Handle omp_* routines. */
4453 if (strstr (name, "omp_") == name)
4454 {
4455 hsa_init_simple_builtins ();
4456 omp_simple_builtin *builtin = omp_simple_builtins->get (name);
4457 if (builtin)
4458 {
4459 builtin->generate (stmt, hbb);
4460 return true;
4461 }
4462
4463 handled = true;
4464 if (strcmp (name, "omp_set_num_threads") == 0)
4465 gen_set_num_threads (gimple_call_arg (stmt, 0), hbb);
4466 else if (strcmp (name, "omp_get_thread_num") == 0)
4467 {
4468 hbb->append_insn (new hsa_insn_comment (name));
4469 query_hsa_grid_nodim (stmt, BRIG_OPCODE_WORKITEMFLATABSID, hbb);
4470 }
4471 else if (strcmp (name, "omp_get_num_threads") == 0)
4472 {
4473 hbb->append_insn (new hsa_insn_comment (name));
4474 gen_get_num_threads (stmt, hbb);
4475 }
4476 else if (strcmp (name, "omp_get_num_teams") == 0)
4477 gen_get_num_teams (stmt, hbb);
4478 else if (strcmp (name, "omp_get_team_num") == 0)
4479 gen_get_team_num (stmt, hbb);
4480 else if (strcmp (name, "omp_get_level") == 0)
4481 gen_get_level (stmt, hbb);
4482 else if (strcmp (name, "omp_get_active_level") == 0)
4483 gen_get_level (stmt, hbb);
4484 else if (strcmp (name, "omp_in_parallel") == 0)
4485 gen_get_level (stmt, hbb);
4486 else if (strcmp (name, "omp_get_max_threads") == 0)
4487 gen_get_max_threads (stmt, hbb);
4488 else
4489 handled = false;
4490
4491 if (handled)
4492 {
4493 if (copy)
4494 free (copy);
4495 return true;
4496 }
4497 }
4498
4499 if (strcmp (name, "__hsa_set_debug_value") == 0)
4500 {
4501 handled = true;
4502 if (hsa_cfun->has_shadow_reg_p ())
4503 {
4504 tree rhs1 = gimple_call_arg (stmt, 0);
4505 hsa_op_with_type *src = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (rhs1, hbb);
4506
4507 src = src->get_in_type (BRIG_TYPE_U64, hbb);
4508 set_debug_value (hbb, src);
4509 }
4510 }
4511
4512 if (copy)
4513 free (copy);
4514 return handled;
4515}

4517/* Helper functions to create a single unary HSA operations out of calls to
4518 builtins. OPCODE is the HSA operation to be generated. STMT is a gimple
4519 call to a builtin. HBB is the HSA BB to which the instruction should be
4520 added. Note that nothing will be created if STMT does not have a LHS. */
4521
4522static void
4523gen_hsa_unaryop_for_builtin (BrigOpcode opcode, gimple *stmt, hsa_bb *hbb)
4524{
4525 tree lhs = gimple_call_lhs (stmt);
4526 if (!lhs)
4527 return;
4528 hsa_op_reg *dest = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (lhs);
4529 hsa_op_with_type *op
4530 = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (gimple_call_arg (stmt, 0), hbb);
4531 gen_hsa_unary_operation (opcode, dest, op, hbb);
4532}

4534/* Helper functions to create a call to standard library if LHS of the
4535 STMT is used. HBB is the HSA BB to which the instruction should be
4536 added. */
4537
4538static void
4539gen_hsa_unaryop_builtin_call (gimple *stmt, hsa_bb *hbb)

4542 if (!lhs)
4543 return;

4545 if (gimple_call_internal_p (stmt))
4546 gen_hsa_insns_for_call_of_internal_fn (stmt, hbb);
4547 else
4548 gen_hsa_insns_for_direct_call (stmt, hbb);

4551/* Helper functions to create a single unary HSA operations out of calls to
4552 builtins (if unsafe math optimizations are enable). Otherwise, create
4553 a call to standard library function.
4554 OPCODE is the HSA operation to be generated. STMT is a gimple
4555 call to a builtin. HBB is the HSA BB to which the instruction should be
4556 added. Note that nothing will be created if STMT does not have a LHS. */
4557
4558static void
4559gen_hsa_unaryop_or_call_for_builtin (BrigOpcode opcode, gimple *stmt,
4560 hsa_bb *hbb)
4561{
4562 if (flag_unsafe_math_optimizations)
4563 gen_hsa_unaryop_for_builtin (opcode, stmt, hbb);
4564 else
4565 gen_hsa_unaryop_builtin_call (stmt, hbb);
4566}

4568/* Generate HSA address corresponding to a value VAL (as opposed to a memory
4569 reference tree), for example an SSA_NAME or an ADDR_EXPR. HBB is the HSA BB
4570 to which the instruction should be added. */
4571
4572static hsa_op_address *
4573get_address_from_value (tree val, hsa_bb *hbb)
4574{
4575 switch (TREE_CODE (val))
4576 {
4577 case SSA_NAME:
4578 {
4579 BrigType16_t addrtype = hsa_get_segment_addr_type (BRIG_SEGMENT_FLAT);
4580 hsa_op_base *reg
4581 = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (val)->get_in_type (addrtype, hbb);
4582 return new hsa_op_address (NULL, as_a <hsa_op_reg *> (reg), 0);
4583 }
4584 case ADDR_EXPR:
4585 return gen_hsa_addr (TREE_OPERAND (val, 0), hbb);
4586
4587 case INTEGER_CST:
4588 if (tree_fits_shwi_p (val))
4589 return new hsa_op_address (NULL, NULL, tree_to_shwi (val));
4590 /* fall-through */
4591
4592 default:
4593 HSA_SORRY_ATV (EXPR_LOCATION (val),
4594 "support for HSA does not implement memory access to %E",
4595 val);
4596 return new hsa_op_address (NULL, NULL, 0);
4597 }
4598}
4599
4600/* Expand assignment of a result of a string BUILTIN to DST.
4601 Size of the operation is N bytes, where instructions
4602 will be append to HBB. */
4603
4604static void
4605expand_lhs_of_string_op (gimple *stmt,
4606 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT n, hsa_bb *hbb,
4607 enum built_in_function builtin)
4608{
4609 /* If LHS is expected, we need to emit a PHI instruction. */
4610 tree lhs = gimple_call_lhs (stmt);
4611 if (!lhs)
4612 return;
4613
4614 hsa_op_reg *lhs_reg = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (lhs);
4615
4616 hsa_op_with_type *dst_reg
4617 = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (gimple_call_arg (stmt, 0), hbb);
4618 hsa_op_with_type *tmp;
4619
4620 switch (builtin)
4621 {
4622 case BUILT_IN_MEMPCPY:
4623 {
4624 tmp = new hsa_op_reg (dst_reg->m_type);
4625 hsa_insn_basic *add
4626 = new hsa_insn_basic (3, BRIG_OPCODE_ADD, tmp->m_type,
4627 tmp, dst_reg,
4628 new hsa_op_immed (n, dst_reg->m_type));
4629 hbb->append_insn (add);
4630 break;
4631 }
4632 case BUILT_IN_MEMCPY:
4633 case BUILT_IN_MEMSET:
4634 tmp = dst_reg;
4635 break;
4636 default:
4637 gcc_unreachable ();
4638 }
4639
4640 hbb->append_insn (new hsa_insn_basic (2, BRIG_OPCODE_MOV, lhs_reg->m_type,
4641 lhs_reg, tmp));
4642}
4643
4644#define HSA_MEMORY_BUILTINS_LIMIT 128
4645
4646/* Expand a string builtin (from a gimple STMT) in a way that
4647 according to MISALIGNED_FLAG we process either direct emission
4648 (a bunch of memory load and store instructions), or we emit a function call
4649 of a library function (for instance 'memcpy'). Actually, a basic block
4650 for direct emission is just prepared, where caller is responsible
4651 for emission of corresponding instructions.
4652 All instruction are appended to HBB. */
4653
4654hsa_bb *
4655expand_string_operation_builtin (gimple *stmt, hsa_bb *hbb,
4656 hsa_op_reg *misaligned_flag)
4657{
4658 edge e = split_block (hbb->m_bb, stmt);
4659 basic_block condition_bb = e->src;
4660 hbb->append_insn (new hsa_insn_cbr (misaligned_flag));
4661
4662 /* Prepare the control flow. */
4663 edge condition_edge = EDGE_SUCC (condition_bb, 0);
4664 basic_block call_bb = split_edge (condition_edge);
4665
4666 basic_block expanded_bb = split_edge (EDGE_SUCC (call_bb, 0));
4667 basic_block cont_bb = EDGE_SUCC (expanded_bb, 0)->dest;
4668 basic_block merge_bb = split_edge (EDGE_PRED (cont_bb, 0));
4669
4670 condition_edge->flags &= ~EDGE_FALLTHRU;
4671 condition_edge->flags |= EDGE_TRUE_VALUE;
4672 make_edge (condition_bb, expanded_bb, EDGE_FALSE_VALUE);
4673
4674 redirect_edge_succ (EDGE_SUCC (call_bb, 0), merge_bb);
4675
4676 hsa_cfun->m_modified_cfg = true;
4677
4678 hsa_init_new_bb (expanded_bb);
4679
4680 /* Slow path: function call. */
4681 gen_hsa_insns_for_direct_call (stmt, hsa_init_new_bb (call_bb), false);
4682
4683 return hsa_bb_for_bb (expanded_bb);
4684}
4685
4686/* Expand a memory copy BUILTIN (BUILT_IN_MEMCPY, BUILT_IN_MEMPCPY) from
4687 a gimple STMT and store all necessary instruction to HBB basic block. */
4688
4689static void
4690expand_memory_copy (gimple *stmt, hsa_bb *hbb, enum built_in_function builtin)
4691{
4692 tree byte_size = gimple_call_arg (stmt, 2);
4693
4694 if (!tree_fits_uhwi_p (byte_size))
4695 {
4696 gen_hsa_insns_for_direct_call (stmt, hbb);
4697 return;
4698 }
4699
4700 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT n = tree_to_uhwi (byte_size);
4701
4702 if (n > HSA_MEMORY_BUILTINS_LIMIT)
4703 {
4704 gen_hsa_insns_for_direct_call (stmt, hbb);
4705 return;
4706 }
4707
4708 tree dst = gimple_call_arg (stmt, 0);
4709 tree src = gimple_call_arg (stmt, 1);
4710
4711 hsa_op_address *dst_addr = get_address_from_value (dst, hbb);
4712 hsa_op_address *src_addr = get_address_from_value (src, hbb);
4713
4714 /* As gen_hsa_memory_copy relies on memory alignment
4715 greater or equal to 8 bytes, we need to verify the alignment. */
4716 BrigType16_t addrtype = hsa_get_segment_addr_type (BRIG_SEGMENT_FLAT);
4717 hsa_op_reg *src_addr_reg = new hsa_op_reg (addrtype);
4718 hsa_op_reg *dst_addr_reg = new hsa_op_reg (addrtype);
4719
4720 convert_addr_to_flat_segment (src_addr, src_addr_reg, hbb);
4721 convert_addr_to_flat_segment (dst_addr, dst_addr_reg, hbb);
4722
4723 /* Process BIT OR for source and destination addresses. */
4724 hsa_op_reg *or_reg = new hsa_op_reg (addrtype);
4725 gen_hsa_binary_operation (BRIG_OPCODE_OR, or_reg, src_addr_reg,
4726 dst_addr_reg, hbb);
4727
4728 /* Process BIT AND with 0x7 to identify the desired alignment
4729 of 8 bytes. */
4730 hsa_op_reg *masked = new hsa_op_reg (addrtype);
4731
4732 gen_hsa_binary_operation (BRIG_OPCODE_AND, masked, or_reg,
4733 new hsa_op_immed (7, addrtype), hbb);
4734
4735 hsa_op_reg *misaligned = new hsa_op_reg (BRIG_TYPE_B1);
4736 hbb->append_insn (new hsa_insn_cmp (BRIG_COMPARE_NE, misaligned->m_type,
4737 misaligned, masked,
4738 new hsa_op_immed (0, masked->m_type)));
4739
4740 hsa_bb *native_impl_bb
4741 = expand_string_operation_builtin (stmt, hbb, misaligned);
4742
4743 gen_hsa_memory_copy (native_impl_bb, dst_addr, src_addr, n, BRIG_ALIGNMENT_8);
4744 hsa_bb *merge_bb
4745 = hsa_init_new_bb (EDGE_SUCC (native_impl_bb->m_bb, 0)->dest);
4746 expand_lhs_of_string_op (stmt, n, merge_bb, builtin);
4747}

4750/* Expand a memory set BUILTIN (BUILT_IN_MEMSET, BUILT_IN_BZERO) from
4751 a gimple STMT and store all necessary instruction to HBB basic block.
4752 The operation set N bytes with a CONSTANT value. */
4753
4754static void
4755expand_memory_set (gimple *stmt, unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT n,
4756 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT constant, hsa_bb *hbb,
4757 enum built_in_function builtin)
4758{
4759 tree dst = gimple_call_arg (stmt, 0);
4760 hsa_op_address *dst_addr = get_address_from_value (dst, hbb);
4761
4762 /* As gen_hsa_memory_set relies on memory alignment
4763 greater or equal to 8 bytes, we need to verify the alignment. */
4764 BrigType16_t addrtype = hsa_get_segment_addr_type (BRIG_SEGMENT_FLAT);
4765 hsa_op_reg *dst_addr_reg = new hsa_op_reg (addrtype);
4766 convert_addr_to_flat_segment (dst_addr, dst_addr_reg, hbb);
4767
4768 /* Process BIT AND with 0x7 to identify the desired alignment
4769 of 8 bytes. */
4770 hsa_op_reg *masked = new hsa_op_reg (addrtype);
4771
4772 gen_hsa_binary_operation (BRIG_OPCODE_AND, masked, dst_addr_reg,
4773 new hsa_op_immed (7, addrtype), hbb);
4774
4775 hsa_op_reg *misaligned = new hsa_op_reg (BRIG_TYPE_B1);
4776 hbb->append_insn (new hsa_insn_cmp (BRIG_COMPARE_NE, misaligned->m_type,
4777 misaligned, masked,
4778 new hsa_op_immed (0, masked->m_type)));
4779
4780 hsa_bb *native_impl_bb
4781 = expand_string_operation_builtin (stmt, hbb, misaligned);
4782
4783 gen_hsa_memory_set (native_impl_bb, dst_addr, constant, n, BRIG_ALIGNMENT_8);
4784 hsa_bb *merge_bb
4785 = hsa_init_new_bb (EDGE_SUCC (native_impl_bb->m_bb, 0)->dest);
4786 expand_lhs_of_string_op (stmt, n, merge_bb, builtin);
4787}
4788
4789/* Store into MEMORDER the memory order specified by tree T, which must be an
4790 integer constant representing a C++ memory order. If it isn't, issue an HSA
4791 sorry message using LOC and return true, otherwise return false and store
4792 the name of the requested order to *MNAME. */
4793
4794static bool
4795hsa_memorder_from_tree (tree t, BrigMemoryOrder *memorder, const char **mname,
4796 location_t loc)
4797{
4798 if (!tree_fits_uhwi_p (t))
4799 {
4800 HSA_SORRY_ATV (loc, "support for HSA does not implement memory model %E",
4801 t);
4802 return true;
4803 }
4804
4805 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT mm = tree_to_uhwi (t);
4806 switch (mm & MEMMODEL_BASE_MASK)
4807 {
4808 case MEMMODEL_RELAXED:
4809 *memorder = BRIG_MEMORY_ORDER_RELAXED;
4810 *mname = "relaxed";
4811 break;
4812 case MEMMODEL_CONSUME:
4813 /* HSA does not have an equivalent, but we can use the slightly stronger
4814 ACQUIRE. */
4815 *memorder = BRIG_MEMORY_ORDER_SC_ACQUIRE;
4816 *mname = "consume";
4817 break;
4818 case MEMMODEL_ACQUIRE:
4819 *memorder = BRIG_MEMORY_ORDER_SC_ACQUIRE;
4820 *mname = "acquire";
4821 break;
4822 case MEMMODEL_RELEASE:
4823 *memorder = BRIG_MEMORY_ORDER_SC_RELEASE;
4824 *mname = "release";
4825 break;
4826 case MEMMODEL_ACQ_REL:
4827 *memorder = BRIG_MEMORY_ORDER_SC_ACQUIRE_RELEASE;
4828 *mname = "acq_rel";
4829 break;
4830 case MEMMODEL_SEQ_CST:
4831 /* Callers implementing a simple load or store need to remove the release
4832 or acquire part respectively. */
4833 *memorder = BRIG_MEMORY_ORDER_SC_ACQUIRE_RELEASE;
4834 *mname = "seq_cst";
4835 break;
4836 default:
4837 {
4838 HSA_SORRY_AT (loc, "support for HSA does not implement the specified "
4839 "memory model");
4840 return true;
4841 }
4842 }
4843 return false;
4844}
4845
4846/* Helper function to create an HSA atomic operation instruction out of calls
4847 to atomic builtins. RET_ORIG is true if the built-in is the variant that
4848 return s the value before applying operation, and false if it should return
4849 the value after applying the operation (if it returns value at all). ACODE
4850 is the atomic operation code, STMT is a gimple call to a builtin. HBB is
4851 the HSA BB to which the instruction should be added. If SIGNAL is true, the
4852 created operation will work on HSA signals rather than atomic variables. */
4853
4854static void
4855gen_hsa_atomic_for_builtin (bool ret_orig, enum BrigAtomicOperation acode,
4856 gimple *stmt, hsa_bb *hbb, bool signal)
4857{
4858 tree lhs = gimple_call_lhs (stmt);
4859
4860 tree type = TREE_TYPE (gimple_call_arg (stmt, 1));
4861 BrigType16_t hsa_type = hsa_type_for_scalar_tree_type (type, false);
4862 BrigType16_t mtype = mem_type_for_type (hsa_type);
4863 BrigMemoryOrder memorder;
4864 const char *mmname;
4865
4866 if (hsa_memorder_from_tree (gimple_call_arg (stmt, 2), &memorder, &mmname,
4867 gimple_location (stmt)))
4868 return;
4869
4870 /* Certain atomic insns must have Bx memory types. */
4871 switch (acode)
4872 {
4873 case BRIG_ATOMIC_LD:
4874 case BRIG_ATOMIC_ST:
4875 case BRIG_ATOMIC_AND:
4876 case BRIG_ATOMIC_OR:
4877 case BRIG_ATOMIC_XOR:
4878 case BRIG_ATOMIC_EXCH:
4879 mtype = hsa_bittype_for_type (mtype);
4880 break;
4881 default:
4882 break;
4883 }
4884
4885 hsa_op_reg *dest;
4886 int nops, opcode;
4887 if (lhs)
4888 {
4889 if (ret_orig)
4890 dest = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (lhs);
4891 else
4892 dest = new hsa_op_reg (hsa_type);
4893 opcode = signal ? BRIG_OPCODE_SIGNAL : BRIG_OPCODE_ATOMIC;
4894 nops = 3;
4895 }
4896 else
4897 {
4898 dest = NULL;
4899 opcode = signal ? BRIG_OPCODE_SIGNALNORET : BRIG_OPCODE_ATOMICNORET;
4900 nops = 2;
4901 }
4902
4903 if (acode == BRIG_ATOMIC_ST)
4904 {
4905 if (memorder == BRIG_MEMORY_ORDER_SC_ACQUIRE_RELEASE)
4906 memorder = BRIG_MEMORY_ORDER_SC_RELEASE;
4907
4908 if (memorder != BRIG_MEMORY_ORDER_RELAXED
4909 && memorder != BRIG_MEMORY_ORDER_SC_RELEASE
4910 && memorder != BRIG_MEMORY_ORDER_NONE)
4911 {
4912 HSA_SORRY_ATV (gimple_location (stmt),
4913 "support for HSA does not implement memory model for "
4914 "ATOMIC_ST: %s", mmname);
4915 return;
4916 }
4917 }
4918
4919 hsa_insn_basic *atominsn;
4920 hsa_op_base *tgt;
4921 if (signal)
4922 {
4923 atominsn = new hsa_insn_signal (nops, opcode, acode, mtype, memorder);
4924 tgt = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (gimple_call_arg (stmt, 0), hbb);
4925 }
4926 else
4927 {
4928 atominsn = new hsa_insn_atomic (nops, opcode, acode, mtype, memorder);
4929 hsa_op_address *addr;
4930 addr = get_address_from_value (gimple_call_arg (stmt, 0), hbb);
4931 if (addr->m_symbol && addr->m_symbol->m_segment == BRIG_SEGMENT_PRIVATE)
4932 {
4933 HSA_SORRY_AT (gimple_location (stmt),
4934 "HSA does not implement atomic operations in private "
4935 "segment");
4936 return;
4937 }
4938 tgt = addr;
4939 }
4940
4941 hsa_op_base *op = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (gimple_call_arg (stmt, 1),
4942 hbb);
4943 if (lhs)
4944 {
4945 atominsn->set_op (0, dest);
4946 atominsn->set_op (1, tgt);
4947 atominsn->set_op (2, op);
4948 }
4949 else
4950 {
4951 atominsn->set_op (0, tgt);
4952 atominsn->set_op (1, op);
4953 }
4954
4955 hbb->append_insn (atominsn);
4956
4957 /* HSA does not natively support the variants that return the modified value,
4958 so re-do the operation again non-atomically if that is what was
4959 requested. */
4960 if (lhs && !ret_orig)
4961 {
4962 int arith;
4963 switch (acode)
4964 {
4965 case BRIG_ATOMIC_ADD:
4966 arith = BRIG_OPCODE_ADD;
4967 break;
4968 case BRIG_ATOMIC_AND:
4969 arith = BRIG_OPCODE_AND;
4970 break;
4971 case BRIG_ATOMIC_OR:
4972 arith = BRIG_OPCODE_OR;
4973 break;
4974 case BRIG_ATOMIC_SUB:
4975 arith = BRIG_OPCODE_SUB;
4976 break;
4977 case BRIG_ATOMIC_XOR:
4978 arith = BRIG_OPCODE_XOR;
4979 break;
4980 default:
4981 gcc_unreachable ();
4982 }
4983 hsa_op_reg *real_dest = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (lhs);
4984 gen_hsa_binary_operation (arith, real_dest, dest, op, hbb);
4985 }
4986}
4987
4988/* Generate HSA instructions for an internal fn.
4989 Instructions will be appended to HBB, which also needs to be the
4990 corresponding structure to the basic_block of STMT. */
4991
4992static void
4993gen_hsa_insn_for_internal_fn_call (gcall *stmt, hsa_bb *hbb)
4994{
4995 gcc_checking_assert (gimple_call_internal_fn (stmt));
4996 internal_fn fn = gimple_call_internal_fn (stmt);
4997
4998 bool is_float_type_p = false;
4999 if (gimple_call_lhs (stmt) != NULL
5000 && TREE_TYPE (gimple_call_lhs (stmt)) == float_type_node)
5001 is_float_type_p = true;
5002
5003 switch (fn)
5004 {
5005 case IFN_CEIL:
5006 gen_hsa_unaryop_for_builtin (BRIG_OPCODE_CEIL, stmt, hbb);
5007 break;
5008
5009 case IFN_FLOOR:
5010 gen_hsa_unaryop_for_builtin (BRIG_OPCODE_FLOOR, stmt, hbb);
5011 break;
5012
5013 case IFN_RINT:
5014 gen_hsa_unaryop_for_builtin (BRIG_OPCODE_RINT, stmt, hbb);
5015 break;
5016
5017 case IFN_SQRT:
5018 gen_hsa_unaryop_for_builtin (BRIG_OPCODE_SQRT, stmt, hbb);
5019 break;
5020
5021 case IFN_RSQRT:
5022 gen_hsa_unaryop_for_builtin (BRIG_OPCODE_NRSQRT, stmt, hbb);
5023 break;
5024
5025 case IFN_TRUNC:
5026 gen_hsa_unaryop_for_builtin (BRIG_OPCODE_TRUNC, stmt, hbb);
5027 break;
5028
5029 case IFN_COS:
5030 {
5031 if (is_float_type_p)
5032 gen_hsa_unaryop_or_call_for_builtin (BRIG_OPCODE_NCOS, stmt, hbb);
5033 else
5034 gen_hsa_unaryop_builtin_call (stmt, hbb);
5035
5036 break;
5037 }
5038 case IFN_EXP2:
5039 {
5040 if (is_float_type_p)
5041 gen_hsa_unaryop_or_call_for_builtin (BRIG_OPCODE_NEXP2, stmt, hbb);
5042 else
5043 gen_hsa_unaryop_builtin_call (stmt, hbb);
5044
5045 break;
5046 }
5047
5048 case IFN_LOG2:
5049 {
5050 if (is_float_type_p)
5051 gen_hsa_unaryop_or_call_for_builtin (BRIG_OPCODE_NLOG2, stmt, hbb);
5052 else
5053 gen_hsa_unaryop_builtin_call (stmt, hbb);
5054
5055 break;
5056 }
5057
5058 case IFN_SIN:
5059 {
5060 if (is_float_type_p)
5061 gen_hsa_unaryop_or_call_for_builtin (BRIG_OPCODE_NSIN, stmt, hbb);
5062 else
5063 gen_hsa_unaryop_builtin_call (stmt, hbb);
5064 break;
5065 }
5066
5067 case IFN_CLRSB:
5068 gen_hsa_clrsb (stmt, hbb);
5069 break;
5070
5071 case IFN_CLZ:
5072 gen_hsa_unaryop_for_builtin (BRIG_OPCODE_FIRSTBIT, stmt, hbb);
5073 break;
5074
5075 case IFN_CTZ:
5076 gen_hsa_unaryop_for_builtin (BRIG_OPCODE_LASTBIT, stmt, hbb);
5077 break;
5078
5079 case IFN_FFS:
5080 gen_hsa_ffs (stmt, hbb);
5081 break;
5082
5083 case IFN_PARITY:
5084 gen_hsa_parity (stmt, hbb);
5085 break;
5086
5087 case IFN_POPCOUNT:
5088 gen_hsa_popcount (stmt, hbb);
5089 break;
5090
5091 case IFN_DIVMOD:
5092 gen_hsa_divmod (stmt, hbb);
5093 break;
5094
5095 case IFN_ACOS:
5096 case IFN_ASIN:
5097 case IFN_ATAN:
5098 case IFN_EXP:
5099 case IFN_EXP10:
5100 case IFN_EXPM1:
5101 case IFN_LOG:
5102 case IFN_LOG10:
5103 case IFN_LOG1P:
5104 case IFN_LOGB:
5105 case IFN_SIGNIFICAND:
5106 case IFN_TAN:
5107 case IFN_NEARBYINT:
5108 case IFN_ROUND:
5109 case IFN_ATAN2:
5110 case IFN_COPYSIGN:
5111 case IFN_FMOD:
5112 case IFN_POW:
5113 case IFN_REMAINDER:
5114 case IFN_SCALB:
5115 case IFN_FMIN:
5116 case IFN_FMAX:
5117 gen_hsa_insns_for_call_of_internal_fn (stmt, hbb);
5118 break;
5119
5120 default:
5121 HSA_SORRY_ATV (gimple_location (stmt),
5122 "support for HSA does not implement internal function: %s",
5123 internal_fn_name (fn));
5124 break;
5125 }
5126}
5127
5128/* Generate HSA instructions for the given call statement STMT. Instructions
5129 will be appended to HBB. */
5130
5131static void
5132gen_hsa_insns_for_call (gimple *stmt, hsa_bb *hbb)
5133{
5134 gcall *call = as_a <gcall *> (stmt);
5135 tree lhs = gimple_call_lhs (stmt);
5136 hsa_op_reg *dest;
5137
5138 if (gimple_call_internal_p (stmt))
5139 {
5140 gen_hsa_insn_for_internal_fn_call (call, hbb);
5141 return;
5142 }
5143
5144 if (!gimple_call_builtin_p (stmt, BUILT_IN_NORMAL))
5145 {
5146 tree function_decl = gimple_call_fndecl (stmt);
5147 /* Prefetch pass can create type-mismatching prefetch builtin calls which
5148 fail the gimple_call_builtin_p test above. Handle them here. */
5149 if (DECL_BUILT_IN_CLASS (function_decl)
5150 && DECL_FUNCTION_CODE (function_decl) == BUILT_IN_PREFETCH)
5151 return;
5152
5153 if (function_decl == NULL_TREE)
5154 {
5155 HSA_SORRY_AT (gimple_location (stmt),
5156 "support for HSA does not implement indirect calls");
5157 return;
5158 }
5159
5160 if (hsa_callable_function_p (function_decl))
5161 gen_hsa_insns_for_direct_call (stmt, hbb);
5162 else if (!gen_hsa_insns_for_known_library_call (stmt, hbb))
5163 HSA_SORRY_AT (gimple_location (stmt),
5164 "HSA supports only calls of functions marked with pragma "
5165 "omp declare target");
5166 return;
5167 }
5168
5169 tree fndecl = gimple_call_fndecl (stmt);
5170 enum built_in_function builtin = DECL_FUNCTION_CODE (fndecl);
5171 switch (builtin)
5172 {
5173 case BUILT_IN_FABS:
5174 case BUILT_IN_FABSF:
5175 gen_hsa_unaryop_for_builtin (BRIG_OPCODE_ABS, stmt, hbb);
5176 break;
5177
5178 case BUILT_IN_CEIL:
5179 case BUILT_IN_CEILF:
5180 gen_hsa_unaryop_for_builtin (BRIG_OPCODE_CEIL, stmt, hbb);
5181 break;
5182
5183 case BUILT_IN_FLOOR:
5184 case BUILT_IN_FLOORF:
5185 gen_hsa_unaryop_for_builtin (BRIG_OPCODE_FLOOR, stmt, hbb);
5186 break;
5187
5188 case BUILT_IN_RINT:
5189 case BUILT_IN_RINTF:
5190 gen_hsa_unaryop_for_builtin (BRIG_OPCODE_RINT, stmt, hbb);
5191 break;
5192
5193 case BUILT_IN_SQRT:
5194 case BUILT_IN_SQRTF:
5195 gen_hsa_unaryop_for_builtin (BRIG_OPCODE_SQRT, stmt, hbb);
5196 break;
5197
5198 case BUILT_IN_TRUNC:
5199 case BUILT_IN_TRUNCF:
5200 gen_hsa_unaryop_for_builtin (BRIG_OPCODE_TRUNC, stmt, hbb);
5201 break;
5202
5203 case BUILT_IN_COS:
5204 case BUILT_IN_SIN:
5205 case BUILT_IN_EXP2:
5206 case BUILT_IN_LOG2:
5207 /* HSAIL does not provide an instruction for double argument type. */
5208 gen_hsa_unaryop_builtin_call (stmt, hbb);
5209 break;
5210
5211 case BUILT_IN_COSF:
5212 gen_hsa_unaryop_or_call_for_builtin (BRIG_OPCODE_NCOS, stmt, hbb);
5213 break;
5214
5215 case BUILT_IN_EXP2F:
5216 gen_hsa_unaryop_or_call_for_builtin (BRIG_OPCODE_NEXP2, stmt, hbb);
5217 break;
5218
5219 case BUILT_IN_LOG2F:
5220 gen_hsa_unaryop_or_call_for_builtin (BRIG_OPCODE_NLOG2, stmt, hbb);
5221 break;
5222
5223 case BUILT_IN_SINF:
5224 gen_hsa_unaryop_or_call_for_builtin (BRIG_OPCODE_NSIN, stmt, hbb);
5225 break;
5226
5227 case BUILT_IN_CLRSB:
5228 case BUILT_IN_CLRSBL:
5229 case BUILT_IN_CLRSBLL:
5230 gen_hsa_clrsb (call, hbb);
5231 break;
5232
5233 case BUILT_IN_CLZ:
5234 case BUILT_IN_CLZL:
5235 case BUILT_IN_CLZLL:
5236 gen_hsa_unaryop_for_builtin (BRIG_OPCODE_FIRSTBIT, stmt, hbb);
5237 break;
5238
5239 case BUILT_IN_CTZ:
5240 case BUILT_IN_CTZL:
5241 case BUILT_IN_CTZLL:
5242 gen_hsa_unaryop_for_builtin (BRIG_OPCODE_LASTBIT, stmt, hbb);
5243 break;
5244
5245 case BUILT_IN_FFS:
5246 case BUILT_IN_FFSL:
5247 case BUILT_IN_FFSLL:
5248 gen_hsa_ffs (call, hbb);
5249 break;
5250
5251 case BUILT_IN_PARITY:
5252 case BUILT_IN_PARITYL:
5253 case BUILT_IN_PARITYLL:
5254 gen_hsa_parity (call, hbb);
5255 break;
5256
5257 case BUILT_IN_POPCOUNT:
5258 case BUILT_IN_POPCOUNTL:
5259 case BUILT_IN_POPCOUNTLL:
5260 gen_hsa_popcount (call, hbb);
5261 break;
5262
5263 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_LOAD_1:
5264 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_LOAD_2:
5265 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_LOAD_4:
5266 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_LOAD_8:
5267 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_LOAD_16:
5268 {
5269 BrigType16_t mtype;
5270 hsa_op_base *src;
5271 src = get_address_from_value (gimple_call_arg (stmt, 0), hbb);
5272
5273 BrigMemoryOrder memorder;
5274 const char *mmname;
5275 if (hsa_memorder_from_tree (gimple_call_arg (stmt, 1), &memorder,
5276 &mmname, gimple_location (stmt)))
5277 return;
5278
5279 if (memorder == BRIG_MEMORY_ORDER_SC_ACQUIRE_RELEASE)
5280 memorder = BRIG_MEMORY_ORDER_SC_ACQUIRE;
5281
5282 if (memorder != BRIG_MEMORY_ORDER_RELAXED
5283 && memorder != BRIG_MEMORY_ORDER_SC_ACQUIRE
5284 && memorder != BRIG_MEMORY_ORDER_NONE)
5285 {
5286 HSA_SORRY_ATV (gimple_location (stmt),
5287 "support for HSA does not implement "
5288 "memory model for atomic loads: %s", mmname);
5289 return;
5290 }
5291
5292 if (lhs)
5293 {
5294 BrigType16_t t = hsa_type_for_scalar_tree_type (TREE_TYPE (lhs),
5295 false);
5296 mtype = mem_type_for_type (t);
5297 mtype = hsa_bittype_for_type (mtype);
5298 dest = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (lhs);
5299 }
5300 else
5301 {
5302 mtype = BRIG_TYPE_B64;
5303 dest = new hsa_op_reg (mtype);
5304 }
5305
5306 hsa_insn_basic *atominsn;
5307 atominsn = new hsa_insn_atomic (2, BRIG_OPCODE_ATOMIC, BRIG_ATOMIC_LD,
5308 mtype, memorder, dest, src);
5309
5310 hbb->append_insn (atominsn);
5311 break;
5312 }
5313
5314 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_1:
5315 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_2:
5316 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_4:
5317 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_8:
5318 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_16:
5319 gen_hsa_atomic_for_builtin (true, BRIG_ATOMIC_EXCH, stmt, hbb, false);
5320 break;
5321 break;
5322
5323 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_FETCH_ADD_1:
5324 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_FETCH_ADD_2:
5325 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_FETCH_ADD_4:
5326 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_FETCH_ADD_8:
5327 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_FETCH_ADD_16:
5328 gen_hsa_atomic_for_builtin (true, BRIG_ATOMIC_ADD, stmt, hbb, false);
5329 break;
5330 break;
5331
5332 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_FETCH_SUB_1:
5333 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_FETCH_SUB_2:
5334 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_FETCH_SUB_4:
5335 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_FETCH_SUB_8:
5336 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_FETCH_SUB_16:
5337 gen_hsa_atomic_for_builtin (true, BRIG_ATOMIC_SUB, stmt, hbb, false);
5338 break;
5339 break;
5340
5341 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_FETCH_AND_1:
5342 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_FETCH_AND_2:
5343 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_FETCH_AND_4:
5344 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_FETCH_AND_8:

5348 break;
5349
5350 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_FETCH_XOR_1:
5351 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_FETCH_XOR_2:
5352 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_FETCH_XOR_4:
5353 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_FETCH_XOR_8:
5354 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_FETCH_XOR_16:
5355 gen_hsa_atomic_for_builtin (true, BRIG_ATOMIC_XOR, stmt, hbb, false);
5356 break;
5357 break;
5358
5359 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_FETCH_OR_1:
5360 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_FETCH_OR_2:
5361 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_FETCH_OR_4:
5362 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_FETCH_OR_8:
5363 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_FETCH_OR_16:
5364 gen_hsa_atomic_for_builtin (true, BRIG_ATOMIC_OR, stmt, hbb, false);
5365 break;
5366 break;
5367
5368 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_STORE_1:
5369 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_STORE_2:
5370 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_STORE_4:
5371 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_STORE_8:
5372 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_STORE_16:
5373 /* Since there cannot be any LHS, the first parameter is meaningless. */
5374 gen_hsa_atomic_for_builtin (true, BRIG_ATOMIC_ST, stmt, hbb, false);
5375 break;
5376 break;
5377
5378 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_ADD_FETCH_1:
5379 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_ADD_FETCH_2:
5380 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_ADD_FETCH_4:
5381 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_ADD_FETCH_8:
5382 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_ADD_FETCH_16:
5383 gen_hsa_atomic_for_builtin (false, BRIG_ATOMIC_ADD, stmt, hbb, false);
5384 break;
5385
5386 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_SUB_FETCH_1:
5387 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_SUB_FETCH_2:
5388 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_SUB_FETCH_4:
5389 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_SUB_FETCH_8:
5390 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_SUB_FETCH_16:
5391 gen_hsa_atomic_for_builtin (false, BRIG_ATOMIC_SUB, stmt, hbb, false);
5392 break;
5393
5394 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_AND_FETCH_1:
5395 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_AND_FETCH_2:
5396 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_AND_FETCH_4:
5397 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_AND_FETCH_8:
5398 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_AND_FETCH_16:
5399 gen_hsa_atomic_for_builtin (false, BRIG_ATOMIC_AND, stmt, hbb, false);
5400 break;
5401
5402 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_XOR_FETCH_1:
5403 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_XOR_FETCH_2:
5404 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_XOR_FETCH_4:
5405 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_XOR_FETCH_8:
5406 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_XOR_FETCH_16:
5407 gen_hsa_atomic_for_builtin (false, BRIG_ATOMIC_XOR, stmt, hbb, false);
5408 break;
5409
5410 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_OR_FETCH_1:
5411 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_OR_FETCH_2:
5412 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_OR_FETCH_4:
5413 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_OR_FETCH_8:
5414 case BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_OR_FETCH_16:
5415 gen_hsa_atomic_for_builtin (false, BRIG_ATOMIC_OR, stmt, hbb, false);
5416 break;
5417
5418 case BUILT_IN_SYNC_VAL_COMPARE_AND_SWAP_1:
5419 case BUILT_IN_SYNC_VAL_COMPARE_AND_SWAP_2:
5420 case BUILT_IN_SYNC_VAL_COMPARE_AND_SWAP_4:
5421 case BUILT_IN_SYNC_VAL_COMPARE_AND_SWAP_8:
5422 case BUILT_IN_SYNC_VAL_COMPARE_AND_SWAP_16:
5423 {
5424 tree type = TREE_TYPE (gimple_call_arg (stmt, 1));
5425 BrigType16_t atype
5426 = hsa_bittype_for_type (hsa_type_for_scalar_tree_type (type, false));
5427 BrigMemoryOrder memorder = BRIG_MEMORY_ORDER_SC_ACQUIRE_RELEASE;
5428 hsa_insn_basic *atominsn;
5429 hsa_op_base *tgt;
5430 atominsn = new hsa_insn_atomic (4, BRIG_OPCODE_ATOMIC,
5431 BRIG_ATOMIC_CAS, atype, memorder);
5432 tgt = get_address_from_value (gimple_call_arg (stmt, 0), hbb);
5433
5434 if (lhs != NULL)
5435 dest = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (lhs);
5436 else
5437 dest = new hsa_op_reg (atype);
5438
5439 atominsn->set_op (0, dest);
5440 atominsn->set_op (1, tgt);
5441
5442 hsa_op_with_type *op
5443 = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (gimple_call_arg (stmt, 1), hbb);
5444 atominsn->set_op (2, op);
5445 op = hsa_reg_or_immed_for_gimple_op (gimple_call_arg (stmt, 2), hbb);
5446 atominsn->set_op (3, op);
5447
5448 hbb->append_insn (atominsn);
5449 break;
5450 }
5451
5452 case BUILT_IN_HSA_WORKGROUPID:
5453 query_hsa_grid_dim (stmt, BRIG_OPCODE_WORKGROUPID, hbb);
5454 break;
5455 case BUILT_IN_HSA_WORKITEMID:
5456 query_hsa_grid_dim (stmt, BRIG_OPCODE_WORKITEMID, hbb);
5457 break;
5458 case BUILT_IN_HSA_WORKITEMABSID:
5459 query_hsa_grid_dim (stmt, BRIG_OPCODE_WORKITEMABSID, hbb);
5460 break;
5461 case BUILT_IN_HSA_GRIDSIZE:
5462 query_hsa_grid_dim (stmt, BRIG_OPCODE_GRIDSIZE, hbb);
5463 break;
5464 case BUILT_IN_HSA_CURRENTWORKGROUPSIZE:
5465 query_hsa_grid_dim (stmt, BRIG_OPCODE_CURRENTWORKGROUPSIZE, hbb);
5466 break;
5467
5468 case BUILT_IN_GOMP_BARRIER:
5469 hbb->append_insn (new hsa_insn_br (0, BRIG_OPCODE_BARRIER, BRIG_TYPE_NONE,
5470 BRIG_WIDTH_ALL));
5471 break;
5472 case BUILT_IN_GOMP_PARALLEL:
5473 HSA_SORRY_AT (gimple_location (stmt),
5474 "support for HSA does not implement non-gridified "
5475 "OpenMP parallel constructs.");
5476 break;
5477
5478 case BUILT_IN_OMP_GET_THREAD_NUM:
5479 {
5480 query_hsa_grid_nodim (stmt, BRIG_OPCODE_WORKITEMFLATABSID, hbb);
5481 break;
5482 }
5483
5484 case BUILT_IN_OMP_GET_NUM_THREADS:
5485 {
5486 gen_get_num_threads (stmt, hbb);
5487 break;
5488 }
5489 case BUILT_IN_GOMP_TEAMS:
5490 {
5491 gen_set_num_threads (gimple_call_arg (stmt, 1), hbb);
5492 break;
5493 }
5494 case BUILT_IN_OMP_GET_NUM_TEAMS:
5495 {
5496 gen_get_num_teams (stmt, hbb);
5497 break;
5498 }
5499 case BUILT_IN_OMP_GET_TEAM_NUM:
5500 {
5501 gen_get_team_num (stmt, hbb);
5502 break;
5503 }
5504 case BUILT_IN_MEMCPY:
5505 case BUILT_IN_MEMPCPY:
5506 {
5507 expand_memory_copy (stmt, hbb, builtin);
5508 break;
5509 }
5510 case BUILT_IN_MEMSET:
5511 {
5512 tree c = gimple_call_arg (stmt, 1);
5513
5514 if (TREE_CODE (c) != INTEGER_CST)
5515 {
5516 gen_hsa_insns_for_direct_call (stmt, hbb);
5517 return;
5518 }
5519
5520 tree byte_size = gimple_call_arg (stmt, 2);
5521
5522 if (!tree_fits_uhwi_p (byte_size))
5523 {
5524 gen_hsa_insns_for_direct_call (stmt, hbb);
5525 return;
5526 }
5527
5528 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT n = tree_to_uhwi (byte_size);
5529
5530 if (n > HSA_MEMORY_BUILTINS_LIMIT)
5531 {
5532 gen_hsa_insns_for_direct_call (stmt, hbb);
5533 return;
5534 }
5535
5536 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT constant
5537 = tree_to_uhwi (fold_convert (unsigned_char_type_node, c));
5538
5539 expand_memory_set (stmt, n, constant, hbb, builtin);
5540
5541 break;
5542 }
5543 case BUILT_IN_BZERO:
5544 {
5545 tree byte_size = gimple_call_arg (stmt, 1);
5546
5547 if (!tree_fits_uhwi_p (byte_size))
5548 {
5549 gen_hsa_insns_for_direct_call (stmt, hbb);
5550 return;
5551 }
5552
5553 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT n = tree_to_uhwi (byte_size);
5554
5555 if (n > HSA_MEMORY_BUILTINS_LIMIT)
5556 {
5557 gen_hsa_insns_for_direct_call (stmt, hbb);
5558 return;
5559 }
5560
5561 expand_memory_set (stmt, n, 0, hbb, builtin);
5562
5563 break;
5564 }
5565 case BUILT_IN_ALLOCA:
5566 case BUILT_IN_ALLOCA_WITH_ALIGN:
5567 {
5568 gen_hsa_alloca (call, hbb);
5569 break;
5570 }
5571 case BUILT_IN_PREFETCH:
5572 break;
5573 default:
5574 {
5575 tree name_tree = DECL_NAME (fndecl);
5576 const char *s = IDENTIFIER_POINTER (name_tree);
5577 size_t len = strlen (s);
5578 if (len > 4 && (strncmp (s, "__builtin_GOMP_", 15) == 0))
5579 HSA_SORRY_ATV (gimple_location (stmt),
5580 "support for HSA does not implement GOMP function %s",
5581 s);
5582 else
5583 gen_hsa_insns_for_direct_call (stmt, hbb);
5584 return;
5585 }
5586 }
5587}
5588
5589/* Generate HSA instructions for a given gimple statement. Instructions will be
5590 appended to HBB. */
5591
5592static void
5593gen_hsa_insns_for_gimple_stmt (gimple *stmt, hsa_bb *hbb)
5594{
5595 switch (gimple_code (stmt))
5596 {
5597 case GIMPLE_ASSIGN:
5598 if (gimple_clobber_p (stmt))
5599 break;
5600
5601 if (gimple_assign_single_p (stmt))
5602 {
5603 tree lhs = gimple_assign_lhs (stmt);
5604 tree rhs = gimple_assign_rhs1 (stmt);
5605 gen_hsa_insns_for_single_assignment (lhs, rhs, hbb);
5606 }
5607 else
5608 gen_hsa_insns_for_operation_assignment (stmt, hbb);
5609 break;
5610 case GIMPLE_RETURN:
5611 gen_hsa_insns_for_return (as_a <greturn *> (stmt), hbb);
5612 break;
5613 case GIMPLE_COND:
5614 gen_hsa_insns_for_cond_stmt (stmt, hbb);
5615 break;
5616 case GIMPLE_CALL:
5617 gen_hsa_insns_for_call (stmt, hbb);
5618 break;
5619 case GIMPLE_DEBUG:
5620 /* ??? HSA supports some debug facilities. */
5621 break;
5622 case GIMPLE_LABEL:
5623 {
5624 tree label = gimple_label_label (as_a <glabel *> (stmt));
5625 if (FORCED_LABEL (label))
5626 HSA_SORRY_AT (gimple_location (stmt),
5627 "support for HSA does not implement gimple label with "
5628 "address taken");
5629
5630 break;
5631 }
5632 case GIMPLE_NOP:
5633 {
5634 hbb->append_insn (new hsa_insn_basic (0, BRIG_OPCODE_NOP));
5635 break;
5636 }
5637 case GIMPLE_SWITCH:
5638 {
5639 gen_hsa_insns_for_switch_stmt (as_a <gswitch *> (stmt), hbb);
5640 break;
5641 }
5642 default:
5643 HSA_SORRY_ATV (gimple_location (stmt),
5644 "support for HSA does not implement gimple statement %s",
5645 gimple_code_name[(int) gimple_code (stmt)]);
5646 }
5647}
5648
5649/* Generate a HSA PHI from a gimple PHI. */
5650
5651static void
5652gen_hsa_phi_from_gimple_phi (gimple *phi_stmt, hsa_bb *hbb)
5653{
5654 hsa_insn_phi *hphi;
5655 unsigned count = gimple_phi_num_args (phi_stmt);
5656
5657 hsa_op_reg *dest
5658 = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (gimple_phi_result (phi_stmt));
5659 hphi = new hsa_insn_phi (count, dest);
5660 hphi->m_bb = hbb->m_bb;
5661
5662 tree lhs = gimple_phi_result (phi_stmt);
5663
5664 for (unsigned i = 0; i < count; i++)
5665 {
5666 tree op = gimple_phi_arg_def (phi_stmt, i);
5667
5668 if (TREE_CODE (op) == SSA_NAME)
5669 {
5670 hsa_op_reg *hreg = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (op);
5671 hphi->set_op (i, hreg);
5672 }
5673 else
5674 {
5675 gcc_assert (is_gimple_min_invariant (op));
5676 tree t = TREE_TYPE (op);
5677 if (!POINTER_TYPE_P (t)
5678 || (TREE_CODE (op) == STRING_CST
5679 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (t)) == INTEGER_TYPE))
5680 hphi->set_op (i, new hsa_op_immed (op));
5681 else if (POINTER_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (lhs))
5682 && TREE_CODE (op) == INTEGER_CST)
5683 {
5684 /* Handle assignment of NULL value to a pointer type. */
5685 hphi->set_op (i, new hsa_op_immed (op));
5686 }
5687 else if (TREE_CODE (op) == ADDR_EXPR)
5688 {
5689 edge e = gimple_phi_arg_edge (as_a <gphi *> (phi_stmt), i);
5690 hsa_bb *hbb_src = hsa_init_new_bb (split_edge (e));
5691 hsa_op_address *addr = gen_hsa_addr (TREE_OPERAND (op, 0),
5692 hbb_src);
5693
5694 hsa_op_reg *dest
5695 = new hsa_op_reg (hsa_get_segment_addr_type (BRIG_SEGMENT_FLAT));
5696 hsa_insn_basic *insn
5697 = new hsa_insn_basic (2, BRIG_OPCODE_LDA, BRIG_TYPE_U64,
5698 dest, addr);
5699 hbb_src->append_insn (insn);
5700
5701 hphi->set_op (i, dest);
5702 }
5703 else
5704 {
5705 HSA_SORRY_AT (gimple_location (phi_stmt),
5706 "support for HSA does not handle PHI nodes with "
5707 "constant address operands");
5708 return;
5709 }
5710 }
5711 }
5712
5713 hbb->append_phi (hphi);
5714}

5760/* Initialize OMP in an HSA basic block PROLOGUE. */
5761
5762static void
5763init_prologue (void)
5764{
5765 if (!hsa_cfun->m_kern_p)
5766 return;
5767
5768 hsa_bb *prologue = hsa_bb_for_bb (ENTRY_BLOCK_PTR_FOR_FN (cfun));
5769
5770 /* Create a magic number that is going to be printed by libgomp. */
5771 unsigned index = hsa_get_number_decl_kernel_mappings ();
5772
5773 /* Emit store to debug argument. */

5776}

5792
5793/* Go over gimple representation and generate our internal HSA one. */
5794
5795static void
5796gen_body_from_gimple ()
5797{
5798 basic_block bb;
5799
5800 /* Verify CFG for complex edges we are unable to handle. */
5801 edge_iterator ei;
5802 edge e;
5803
5804 FOR_EACH_BB_FN (bb, cfun)
5805 {
5806 FOR_EACH_EDGE (e, ei, bb->succs)
5807 {
5808 /* Verify all unsupported flags for edges that point
5809 to the same basic block. */
5810 if (e->flags & EDGE_EH)
5811 {
5812 HSA_SORRY_AT (UNKNOWN_LOCATION,
5813 "support for HSA does not implement exception "
5814 "handling");
5815 return;
5816 }
5817 }
5818 }
5819
5820 FOR_EACH_BB_FN (bb, cfun)
5821 {
5822 gimple_stmt_iterator gsi;
5823 hsa_bb *hbb = hsa_bb_for_bb (bb);
5824 if (hbb)
5825 continue;
5826
5827 hbb = hsa_init_new_bb (bb);
5828
5829 for (gsi = gsi_start_bb (bb); !gsi_end_p (gsi); gsi_next (&gsi))
5830 {
5831 gen_hsa_insns_for_gimple_stmt (gsi_stmt (gsi), hbb);
5832 if (hsa_seen_error ())
5833 return;
5834 }
5835 }
5836
5837 FOR_EACH_BB_FN (bb, cfun)
5838 {
5839 gimple_stmt_iterator gsi;
5840 hsa_bb *hbb = hsa_bb_for_bb (bb);
5841 gcc_assert (hbb != NULL);
5842
5843 for (gsi = gsi_start_phis (bb); !gsi_end_p (gsi); gsi_next (&gsi))
5844 if (!virtual_operand_p (gimple_phi_result (gsi_stmt (gsi))))
5845 gen_hsa_phi_from_gimple_phi (gsi_stmt (gsi), hbb);
5846 }
5847
5848 if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
5849 {
5850 fprintf (dump_file, "------- Generated SSA form -------\n");
5851 dump_hsa_cfun (dump_file);
5852 }
5853}
5854
5855static void
5856gen_function_decl_parameters (hsa_function_representation *f,
5857 tree decl)
5858{
5859 tree parm;
5860 unsigned i;
5861
5862 for (parm = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (TREE_TYPE (decl)), i = 0;
5863 parm;
5864 parm = TREE_CHAIN (parm), i++)
5865 {
5866 /* Result type if last in the tree list. */
5867 if (TREE_CHAIN (parm) == NULL)
5868 break;
5869
5870 tree v = TREE_VALUE (parm);
5871
5872 hsa_symbol *arg = new hsa_symbol (BRIG_TYPE_NONE, BRIG_SEGMENT_ARG,
5873 BRIG_LINKAGE_NONE);
5874 arg->m_type = hsa_type_for_tree_type (v, &arg->m_dim);
5875 arg->m_name_number = i;
5876
5877 f->m_input_args.safe_push (arg);
5878 }
5879
5880 tree result_type = TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (decl));
5881 if (!VOID_TYPE_P (result_type))
5882 {
5883 f->m_output_arg = new hsa_symbol (BRIG_TYPE_NONE, BRIG_SEGMENT_ARG,
5884 BRIG_LINKAGE_NONE);
5885 f->m_output_arg->m_type
5886 = hsa_type_for_tree_type (result_type, &f->m_output_arg->m_dim);
5887 f->m_output_arg->m_name = "res";
5888 }
5889}
5890
5891/* Generate the vector of parameters of the HSA representation of the current
5892 function. This also includes the output parameter representing the
5893 result. */
5894
5895static void
5896gen_function_def_parameters ()
5897{
5898 tree parm;
5899
5900 hsa_bb *prologue = hsa_bb_for_bb (ENTRY_BLOCK_PTR_FOR_FN (cfun));
5901
5902 for (parm = DECL_ARGUMENTS (cfun->decl); parm;
5903 parm = DECL_CHAIN (parm))
5904 {
5905 struct hsa_symbol **slot;
5906
5907 hsa_symbol *arg
5908 = new hsa_symbol (BRIG_TYPE_NONE, hsa_cfun->m_kern_p
5909 ? BRIG_SEGMENT_KERNARG : BRIG_SEGMENT_ARG,
5910 BRIG_LINKAGE_FUNCTION);
5911 arg->fillup_for_decl (parm);
5912
5913 hsa_cfun->m_input_args.safe_push (arg);
5914
5915 if (hsa_seen_error ())
5916 return;
5917
5918 arg->m_name = hsa_get_declaration_name (parm);
5919
5920 /* Copy all input arguments and create corresponding private symbols
5921 for them. */
5922 hsa_symbol *private_arg;
5923 hsa_op_address *parm_addr = new hsa_op_address (arg);
5924
5925 if (TREE_ADDRESSABLE (parm)
5926 || (!is_gimple_reg (parm) && !TREE_READONLY (parm)))
5927 {
5928 private_arg = hsa_cfun->create_hsa_temporary (arg->m_type);
5929 private_arg->fillup_for_decl (parm);
5930
5931 BrigAlignment8_t align = MIN (arg->m_align, private_arg->m_align);
5932
5933 hsa_op_address *private_arg_addr = new hsa_op_address (private_arg);
5934 gen_hsa_memory_copy (prologue, private_arg_addr, parm_addr,
5935 arg->total_byte_size (), align);
5936 }
5937 else
5938 private_arg = arg;
5939
5940 slot = hsa_cfun->m_local_symbols->find_slot (private_arg, INSERT);
5941 gcc_assert (!*slot);
5942 *slot = private_arg;
5943
5944 if (is_gimple_reg (parm))
5945 {
5946 tree ddef = ssa_default_def (cfun, parm);
5947 if (ddef && !has_zero_uses (ddef))
5948 {
5949 BrigType16_t t = hsa_type_for_scalar_tree_type (TREE_TYPE (ddef),
5950 false);
5951 BrigType16_t mtype = mem_type_for_type (t);
5952 hsa_op_reg *dest = hsa_cfun->reg_for_gimple_ssa (ddef);
5953 hsa_insn_mem *mem = new hsa_insn_mem (BRIG_OPCODE_LD, mtype,
5954 dest, parm_addr);
5955 gcc_assert (!parm_addr->m_reg);
5956 prologue->append_insn (mem);
5957 }
5958 }
5959 }
5960
5961 if (!VOID_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (cfun->decl))))
5962 {
5963 struct hsa_symbol **slot;
5964
5965 hsa_cfun->m_output_arg = new hsa_symbol (BRIG_TYPE_NONE, BRIG_SEGMENT_ARG,
5966 BRIG_LINKAGE_FUNCTION);
5967 hsa_cfun->m_output_arg->fillup_for_decl (DECL_RESULT (cfun->decl));
5968
5969 if (hsa_seen_error ())
5970 return;
5971
5972 hsa_cfun->m_output_arg->m_name = "res";
5973 slot = hsa_cfun->m_local_symbols->find_slot (hsa_cfun->m_output_arg,
5974 INSERT);
5975 gcc_assert (!*slot);
5976 *slot = hsa_cfun->m_output_arg;
5977 }
5978}

6023/* Return true if switch statement S can be transformed
6024 to a SBR instruction in HSAIL. */
6025
6026static bool
6027transformable_switch_to_sbr_p (gswitch *s)
6028{
6029 /* Identify if a switch statement can be transformed to
6030 SBR instruction, like:
6031
6032 sbr_u32 $s1 [@label1, @label2, @label3];
6033 */
6034
6035 tree size = get_switch_size (s);
6036 if (!tree_fits_uhwi_p (size))
6037 return false;
6038
6039 if (tree_to_uhwi (size) > HSA_MAXIMUM_SBR_LABELS)
6040 return false;
6041
6042 return true;
6043}
