6045/* Structure hold connection between PHI nodes and immediate
6046 values hold by there nodes. */
6047
6048struct phi_definition
6049{
6050 phi_definition (unsigned phi_i, unsigned label_i, tree imm):
6051 phi_index (phi_i), label_index (label_i), phi_value (imm)
6052 {}
6053
6054 unsigned phi_index;
6055 unsigned label_index;
6056 tree phi_value;
6057};
6058
6059/* Sum slice of a vector V, starting from index START and ending
6060 at the index END - 1. */
6061
6062template <typename T>
6063static
6064T sum_slice (const auto_vec <T> &v, unsigned start, unsigned end)
6065{
6066 T s = 0;
6067
6068 for (unsigned i = start; i < end; i++)
6069 s += v[i];
6070
6071 return s;
6072}
6073
6074/* Function transforms GIMPLE SWITCH statements to a series of IF statements.
6075 Let's assume following example:
6076
6077L0:
6078 switch (index)
6079 case C1:
6080L1: hard_work_1 ();
6081 break;
6082 case C2..C3:
6083L2: hard_work_2 ();
6084 break;
6085 default:
6086LD: hard_work_3 ();
6087 break;
6088
6089 The transformation encompasses following steps:
6090 1) all immediate values used by edges coming from the switch basic block
6091 are saved
6092 2) all these edges are removed
6093 3) the switch statement (in L0) is replaced by:
6094 if (index == C1)
6095 goto L1;
6096 else
6097 goto L1';
6098
6099 4) newly created basic block Lx' is used for generation of
6100 a next condition
6101 5) else branch of the last condition goes to LD
6102 6) fix all immediate values in PHI nodes that were propagated though
6103 edges that were removed in step 2
6104
6105 Note: if a case is made by a range C1..C2, then process
6106 following transformation:
6107
6108 switch_cond_op1 = C1 <= index;
6109 switch_cond_op2 = index <= C2;
6110 switch_cond_and = switch_cond_op1 & switch_cond_op2;
6111 if (switch_cond_and != 0)
6112 goto Lx;
6113 else
6114 goto Ly;
6115
6116*/
6117
6118static bool
6119convert_switch_statements (void)
6120{
6121 function *func = DECL_STRUCT_FUNCTION (current_function_decl);
6122 basic_block bb;
6123
6124 bool modified_cfg = false;
6125
6126 FOR_EACH_BB_FN (bb, func)
6127 {
6128 gimple_stmt_iterator gsi = gsi_last_bb (bb);
6129 if (gsi_end_p (gsi))
6130 continue;
6131
6132 gimple *stmt = gsi_stmt (gsi);
6133
6134 if (gimple_code (stmt) == GIMPLE_SWITCH)
6135 {
6136 gswitch *s = as_a <gswitch *> (stmt);
6137
6138 /* If the switch can utilize SBR insn, skip the statement. */
6139 if (transformable_switch_to_sbr_p (s))
6140 continue;
6141
6142 modified_cfg = true;
6143
6144 unsigned labels = gimple_switch_num_labels (s);
6145 tree index = gimple_switch_index (s);
6146 tree index_type = TREE_TYPE (index);
6147 tree default_label = gimple_switch_default_label (s);
6148 basic_block default_label_bb
6149 = label_to_block_fn (func, CASE_LABEL (default_label));
6150 basic_block cur_bb = bb;
6151
6152 auto_vec <edge> new_edges;
6153 auto_vec <phi_definition *> phi_todo_list;
6154 auto_vec <gcov_type> edge_counts;
6155 auto_vec <int> edge_probabilities;
6156
6157 /* Investigate all labels that and PHI nodes in these edges which
6158 should be fixed after we add new collection of edges. */
6159 for (unsigned i = 0; i < labels; i++)
6160 {
6161 tree label = gimple_switch_label (s, i);
6162 basic_block label_bb = label_to_block_fn (func, CASE_LABEL (label));
6163 edge e = find_edge (bb, label_bb);
6164 edge_counts.safe_push (e->count);
6165 edge_probabilities.safe_push (e->probability);
6166 gphi_iterator phi_gsi;
6167
6168 /* Save PHI definitions that will be destroyed because of an edge
6169 is going to be removed. */
6170 unsigned phi_index = 0;
6171 for (phi_gsi = gsi_start_phis (e->dest);
6172 !gsi_end_p (phi_gsi); gsi_next (&phi_gsi))
6173 {
6174 gphi *phi = phi_gsi.phi ();
6175 for (unsigned j = 0; j < gimple_phi_num_args (phi); j++)
6176 {
6177 if (gimple_phi_arg_edge (phi, j) == e)
6178 {
6179 tree imm = gimple_phi_arg_def (phi, j);
6180 phi_definition *p = new phi_definition (phi_index, i,
6181 imm);
6182 phi_todo_list.safe_push (p);
6183 break;
6184 }
6185 }
6186 phi_index++;
6187 }
6188 }
6189
6190 /* Remove all edges for the current basic block. */
6191 for (int i = EDGE_COUNT (bb->succs) - 1; i >= 0; i--)
6192 {
6193 edge e = EDGE_SUCC (bb, i);
6194 remove_edge (e);
6195 }
6196
6197 /* Iterate all non-default labels. */
6198 for (unsigned i = 1; i < labels; i++)
6199 {
6200 tree label = gimple_switch_label (s, i);
6201 tree low = CASE_LOW (label);
6202 tree high = CASE_HIGH (label);
6203
6204 if (!useless_type_conversion_p (TREE_TYPE (low), index_type))
6205 low = fold_convert (index_type, low);
6206
6207 gimple_stmt_iterator cond_gsi = gsi_last_bb (cur_bb);
6208 gimple *c = NULL;
6209 if (high)
6210 {
6211 tree tmp1 = make_temp_ssa_name (boolean_type_node, NULL,
6212 "switch_cond_op1");
6213
6214 gimple *assign1 = gimple_build_assign (tmp1, LE_EXPR, low,
6215 index);
6216
6217 tree tmp2 = make_temp_ssa_name (boolean_type_node, NULL,
6218 "switch_cond_op2");
6219
6220 if (!useless_type_conversion_p (TREE_TYPE (high), index_type))
6221 high = fold_convert (index_type, high);
6222 gimple *assign2 = gimple_build_assign (tmp2, LE_EXPR, index,
6223 high);
6224
6225 tree tmp3 = make_temp_ssa_name (boolean_type_node, NULL,
6226 "switch_cond_and");
6227 gimple *assign3 = gimple_build_assign (tmp3, BIT_AND_EXPR, tmp1,
6228 tmp2);
6229
6230 gsi_insert_before (&cond_gsi, assign1, GSI_SAME_STMT);
6231 gsi_insert_before (&cond_gsi, assign2, GSI_SAME_STMT);
6232 gsi_insert_before (&cond_gsi, assign3, GSI_SAME_STMT);
6233
6234 tree b = constant_boolean_node (false, boolean_type_node);
6235 c = gimple_build_cond (NE_EXPR, tmp3, b, NULL, NULL);
6236 }
6237 else
6238 c = gimple_build_cond (EQ_EXPR, index, low, NULL, NULL);
6239
6240 gimple_set_location (c, gimple_location (stmt));
6241
6242 gsi_insert_before (&cond_gsi, c, GSI_SAME_STMT);
6243
6244 basic_block label_bb
6245 = label_to_block_fn (func, CASE_LABEL (label));
6246 edge new_edge = make_edge (cur_bb, label_bb, EDGE_TRUE_VALUE);
6247 int prob_sum = sum_slice <int> (edge_probabilities, i, labels) +
6248 edge_probabilities[0];
6249
6250 if (prob_sum)
6251 new_edge->probability
6252 = RDIV (REG_BR_PROB_BASE * edge_probabilities[i], prob_sum);
6253
6254 new_edge->count = edge_counts[i];
6255 new_edges.safe_push (new_edge);
6256
6257 if (i < labels - 1)
6258 {
6259 /* Prepare another basic block that will contain
6260 next condition. */
6261 basic_block next_bb = create_empty_bb (cur_bb);
6262 if (current_loops)
6263 {
6264 add_bb_to_loop (next_bb, cur_bb->loop_father);
6265 loops_state_set (LOOPS_NEED_FIXUP);
6266 }
6267
6268 edge next_edge = make_edge (cur_bb, next_bb, EDGE_FALSE_VALUE);
6269 next_edge->probability
6270 = inverse_probability (new_edge->probability);
6271 next_edge->count = edge_counts[0]
6272 + sum_slice <gcov_type> (edge_counts, i, labels);
6273 next_bb->frequency = EDGE_FREQUENCY (next_edge);
6274 cur_bb = next_bb;
6275 }
6276 else /* Link last IF statement and default label
6277 of the switch. */
6278 {
6279 edge e = make_edge (cur_bb, default_label_bb, EDGE_FALSE_VALUE);
6280 e->probability = inverse_probability (new_edge->probability);
6281 e->count = edge_counts[0];
6282 new_edges.safe_insert (0, e);
6283 }
6284 }
6285
6286 /* Restore original PHI immediate value. */
6287 for (unsigned i = 0; i < phi_todo_list.length (); i++)
6288 {
6289 phi_definition *phi_def = phi_todo_list[i];
6290 edge new_edge = new_edges[phi_def->label_index];
6291
6292 gphi_iterator it = gsi_start_phis (new_edge->dest);
6293 for (unsigned i = 0; i < phi_def->phi_index; i++)
6294 gsi_next (&it);
6295
6296 gphi *phi = it.phi ();
6297 add_phi_arg (phi, phi_def->phi_value, new_edge, UNKNOWN_LOCATION);
6298 delete phi_def;
6299 }
6300
6301 /* Remove the original GIMPLE switch statement. */
6302 gsi_remove (&gsi, true);
6303 }
6304 }
6305
6306 if (dump_file)
6307 dump_function_to_file (current_function_decl, dump_file, TDF_DETAILS);
6308
6309 return modified_cfg;
6310}
6311
6312/* Expand builtins that can't be handled by HSA back-end. */
6313
6314static void
6315expand_builtins ()
6316{
6317 function *func = DECL_STRUCT_FUNCTION (current_function_decl);
6318 basic_block bb;
6319
6320 FOR_EACH_BB_FN (bb, func)
6321 {
6322 for (gimple_stmt_iterator gsi = gsi_start_bb (bb); !gsi_end_p (gsi);
6323 gsi_next (&gsi))
6324 {
6325 gimple *stmt = gsi_stmt (gsi);
6326
6327 if (gimple_code (stmt) != GIMPLE_CALL)
6328 continue;
6329
6330 gcall *call = as_a <gcall *> (stmt);
6331
6332 if (!gimple_call_builtin_p (call, BUILT_IN_NORMAL))
6333 continue;
6334
6335 tree fndecl = gimple_call_fndecl (stmt);
6336 enum built_in_function fn = DECL_FUNCTION_CODE (fndecl);
6337 switch (fn)
6338 {
6339 case BUILT_IN_CEXPF:
6340 case BUILT_IN_CEXPIF:
6341 case BUILT_IN_CEXPI:
6342 {
6343 /* Similar to builtins.c (expand_builtin_cexpi), the builtin
6344 can be transformed to: cexp(I * z) = ccos(z) + I * csin(z). */
6345 tree lhs = gimple_call_lhs (stmt);
6346 tree rhs = gimple_call_arg (stmt, 0);
6347 tree rhs_type = TREE_TYPE (rhs);
6348 bool float_type_p = rhs_type == float_type_node;
6349 tree real_part = make_temp_ssa_name (rhs_type, NULL,
6350 "cexp_real_part");
6351 tree imag_part = make_temp_ssa_name (rhs_type, NULL,
6352 "cexp_imag_part");
6353
6354 tree cos_fndecl
6355 = mathfn_built_in (rhs_type, fn == float_type_p
6356 ? BUILT_IN_COSF : BUILT_IN_COS);
6357 gcall *cos = gimple_build_call (cos_fndecl, 1, rhs);
6358 gimple_call_set_lhs (cos, real_part);
6359 gsi_insert_before (&gsi, cos, GSI_SAME_STMT);
6360
6361 tree sin_fndecl
6362 = mathfn_built_in (rhs_type, fn == float_type_p
6363 ? BUILT_IN_SINF : BUILT_IN_SIN);
6364 gcall *sin = gimple_build_call (sin_fndecl, 1, rhs);
6365 gimple_call_set_lhs (sin, imag_part);
6366 gsi_insert_before (&gsi, sin, GSI_SAME_STMT);
6367
6368
6369 gassign *assign = gimple_build_assign (lhs, COMPLEX_EXPR,
6370 real_part, imag_part);
6371 gsi_insert_before (&gsi, assign, GSI_SAME_STMT);
6372 gsi_remove (&gsi, true);
6373
6374 break;
6375 }
6376 default:
6377 break;
6378 }
6379 }
6380 }
6381}

6396/* Generate HSAIL representation of the current function and write into a
6397 special section of the output file. If KERNEL is set, the function will be
6398 considered an HSA kernel callable from the host, otherwise it will be
6399 compiled as an HSA function callable from other HSA code. */
6400
6401static void
6402generate_hsa (bool kernel)
6403{
6404 hsa_init_data_for_cfun ();
6405
6406 if (hsa_num_threads == NULL)
6407 emit_hsa_module_variables ();
6408
6409 bool modified_cfg = convert_switch_statements ();
6410 /* Initialize hsa_cfun. */
6411 hsa_cfun = new hsa_function_representation (cfun->decl, kernel,
6412 SSANAMES (cfun)->length (),
6413 modified_cfg);
6414 hsa_cfun->init_extra_bbs ();
6415
6416 if (flag_tm)
6417 {
6418 HSA_SORRY_AT (UNKNOWN_LOCATION,
6419 "support for HSA does not implement transactional memory");
6420 goto fail;
6421 }
6422
6423 verify_function_arguments (cfun->decl);
6424 if (hsa_seen_error ())
6425 goto fail;
6426
6427 hsa_cfun->m_name = get_brig_function_name (cfun->decl);
6428
6429 gen_function_def_parameters ();
6430 if (hsa_seen_error ())
6431 goto fail;
6432
6433 init_prologue ();
6434
6435 gen_body_from_gimple ();
6436 if (hsa_seen_error ())
6437 goto fail;
6438
6439 if (hsa_cfun->m_kernel_dispatch_count)
6440 init_hsa_num_threads ();
6441
6442 if (hsa_cfun->m_kern_p)
6443 {
6444 hsa_function_summary *s
6445 = hsa_summaries->get (cgraph_node::get (hsa_cfun->m_decl));
6446 hsa_add_kern_decl_mapping (current_function_decl, hsa_cfun->m_name,
6447 hsa_cfun->m_maximum_omp_data_size,
6448 s->m_gridified_kernel_p);
6449 }
6450
6451 if (flag_checking)
6452 {
6453 for (unsigned i = 0; i < hsa_cfun->m_ssa_map.length (); i++)
6454 if (hsa_cfun->m_ssa_map[i])
6455 hsa_cfun->m_ssa_map[i]->verify_ssa ();
6456
6457 basic_block bb;
6458 FOR_EACH_BB_FN (bb, cfun)
6459 {
6460 hsa_bb *hbb = hsa_bb_for_bb (bb);
6461
6462 for (hsa_insn_basic *insn = hbb->m_first_insn; insn;
6463 insn = insn->m_next)
6464 insn->verify ();
6465 }
6466 }
6467
6468 hsa_regalloc ();
6469 hsa_brig_emit_function ();
6470
6471 fail:
6472 hsa_deinit_data_for_cfun ();
6473}
